BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Computers for Beginners 5: Use Windows
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260601T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260601T113000
UID:69d93d43f29b90618efdf8e9@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:A class on essential basic Windows skills for absolute beginne
 rs with little computer experience.\nIn this fifth session you will:\nBeco
 me familiar with the Windows (10) operating system\nPractice using common 
 Windows features: File Explorer\, Desktop\, Taskbar\, Windows\, Applicatio
 ns\nUpon completion of this class students will have a basic understanding
  of how to create and organize files in the Windows environment.\nPrerequi
 sites: Computer for Beginners 1 & 2 or basic mouse and keyboarding skills\
 nFormat: Hands-on with demonstrations\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe
  personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Libr
 ary under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). T
 he information will only be used for event and program registration\, deli
 very and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your informat
 ion can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-
 5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Kennedy/Eglinton\, Youth Hub
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69d93d43f29b90618efdf8e9
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Google AI Essentials: Online Learning Circle
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260506T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260506T120000
UID:69d93eb4129f12743837bc97@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Curious about artificial intelligence or want to learn practic
 al AI skills for work and personal use? Join our staff-facilitated learnin
 g circle to complete the self-paced Google AI Essentials specialization.\n
 This 10-hour introductory-level specialization\, offered through Coursera\
 , is available for free to learning circle participants. It is made up of 
 five courses\, each containing four units that consist of short videos\, a
 rticles\, assignments and a short multiple-choice quiz.\nBy completing the
  specialization\,\nyou will learn:\nHow AI works\nHow to write effective p
 rompts\nHow to use generative AI tools responsibly\nHow to identify AI's p
 otential biases and avoid harm\nHow to stay up to date with AI news\nAfter
  you complete the course\, you earn a Google certificate and a badge to sh
 are with others\nLearning Circles are study groups guided by\nlibrary staf
 f for people who want to complete the Google AI Essentials specialization 
 together in a welcoming space:\nLearners meet weekly and work together thr
 ough course materials.\nParticipants are expected to commit to attending a
 ll four learning circle sessions.\nNo AI experience is required.\nHow to J
 oi\nn a Learning Circle:\nRegister once on the first session of this event
  series\, in order to attend all sessions.\nPlease sign up with a\nvalid e
 mail address\n.\nA valid TPL library card is required for online circles
 .\nAttend all four sessions (online via Zoom\, date: May 6\, May 13\, May 
 20 and May 27)\nRegistration is a two-step procedure. First\, participants
  must complete their registration through this page. After this step\, lib
 rary staff will follow up to request additional information in order to co
 mplete the registration.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal inf
 ormation on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the
  Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The informatio
 n will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and eval
 uation. Questions about how the library handles your information can be di
 rected to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yo
 nge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69d93eb4129f12743837bc97
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Maison des bébés
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260604T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260604T143000
UID:69b4555eb6c4ac1fedc5898a@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Un programme spécialement conçu pour les bébés de 0 à 18 
 mois et leurs accompagnateurs.\nChanter des chansons et des comptines à v
 otre bébé favorise le développement du langage tout en partageant un mo
 ment amusant et chaleureux.\nLes comptines avec gestes encouragent égalem
 ent les tout‑petits à bouger et à explorer selon leur stade de dévelo
 ppement.\nCe programme est offert en partenariat avec le\nCentre francopho
 ne du Grand Toronto.\nAccessibilité:\nLe sous-titrage en direct ou automa
 tique\, l’interprétation en langue des signes\, les services\nd’inter
 venant\, ou les services d’accompagnement sont disponibles sur demande. 
 Veuillez\nsoumettre votre demande au moins deux semaines à l’avance à 
 : tpl.ca/accessibility-events\nA program specially designed for babies age
 d 0 to 18 months and their caregivers.\nSinging songs and rhymes to your b
 aby helps support language development while sharing a fun and warm moment
  together.\nAction rhymes also encourage little ones to move and explore a
 ccording to their developmental stage.\nThis program is offered in partner
 ship with the\nCentre francophone du Grand Toronto.
LOCATION:New Toronto
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b4555eb6c4ac1fedc5898a
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
