DESCRIPTION:May is Asian Heritage Month. Join us for a screening of\nLiz a
 nd the Blue Bird\n(2018)\n. This film's language is Japanese with English
  subtitles.\n"Mizore is shy and soft-spoken\, while her best friend Nozomi
  is outgoing. The two girls grow closer as they practice for their last du
 et before graduating high school. However\, the impending separation may b
 e more than their friendship can handle. Interspersed with their story is 
 the fantasy tale of Liz\, who like Mizore\, seeks a friendship that may be
  too hard to hold onto in this beautiful coming-of-age story."\nDrop in.
