 ed to join.\nJanuary 8 - The Story of Us by Catherine Hernandez\nFebruary 
 5 - Death of the Author by Nnedi Okarofor\nMarch 5 - Wuthering Heights by 
 Emily Bronte\nApril 2 - The Siren's Call by Chris Hayes\nMay 7 - That Time
  I Loved You by Carianne Leung\nJune 4 - Any Other Way: How Toronto Got Qu
 eer by John Lorinc\nJuly 2 - The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy by Dougl
 as Adams\nAugust 6 - Demon Copperhead by Barbara Kingsolver\nSeptember 3 -
  Noopiming by Leanne Betasamosake Simpson\nOctober 1 - Shadow of the Wind 
 by Carlos Ruiz Zafon\nNovember 5 - House Divided by Alex Bozikovic\nDecemb
 er 3 - The Glass Hotel by Emily St. John Mandel\nCopies of our book club p
 icks will be set aside each month at the first-floor desk at Beaches Libra
 ry. These titles are also available as eBooks and eAudiobooks through Libb
 y\, and in alternate formats.
LOCATION:Beaches\, Program Room
