BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Night Sparrow: Celebrating Unsung Jewish Women Erased From His
 tory
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260511T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260511T153000
UID:69ab65c74a9fd98b7f82a5a5@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:The first Jewish female snipers in history fought against the 
 'fascist Nazis' in WWII\, yet their astonishing stories are visually unkno
 wn. Forbidden to speak about their achievements after the war\, these wome
 n were erased by the country they fought to protect.\nDiscover how these i
 ndomitable women changed history in this presentation by author Shelly San
 ders\, whose novel\nThe Night Sparrow\nwas inspired by their recently tran
 slated diaries\, photos\, and frontline stories.
LOCATION:Barbara Frum\, Located in Room B on the third floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69ab65c74a9fd98b7f82a5a5
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
