BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Monthly Movie Screening: Marmalade
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260521T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260521T200000
UID:69961fbcb0595799c09dc5bf@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This month's feature:\nMarmalade\nEnjoy a night at the movies!
  Join us for a free movie on the big screen in our accessible theatre.\nDe
 scription: MARMALADE is an edge-of-the-seat crime-tinged romance tale. Re
 cently incarcerated Baron struck up a friendship with cellmate Otis\, a ma
 n with a well-versed history of prison breaks. As the pair hatch an escape
  plan together\, Baron recalls the story of how he met Marmalade\, the lov
 e of his life\, and their "Bonnie and Clyde" style scheme to rob a bank in
  order to care for his sick mother and give the couple the life they have 
 always dreamed of.\nThis film is rated 14A. 99 minutes. Start time is 6:00
  pm. Drop in. All are welcome!
LOCATION:Palmerston\, Theatre (downstairs)
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69961fbcb0595799c09dc5bf
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
