BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Google AI Essentials: Online Learning Circle
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260520T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260520T120000
UID:69d93eb4129f12743837bc99@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Curious about artificial intelligence or want to learn practic
 al AI skills for work and personal use? Join our staff-facilitated learnin
 g circle to complete the self-paced Google AI Essentials specialization.\n
 This 10-hour introductory-level specialization\, offered through Coursera\
 , is available for free to learning circle participants. It is made up of 
 five courses\, each containing four units that consist of short videos\, a
 rticles\, assignments and a short multiple-choice quiz.\nBy completing the
  specialization\,\nyou will learn:\nHow AI works\nHow to write effective p
 rompts\nHow to use generative AI tools responsibly\nHow to identify AI's p
 otential biases and avoid harm\nHow to stay up to date with AI news\nAfter
  you complete the course\, you earn a Google certificate and a badge to sh
 are with others\nLearning Circles are study groups guided by\nlibrary staf
 f for people who want to complete the Google AI Essentials specialization 
 together in a welcoming space:\nLearners meet weekly and work together thr
 ough course materials.\nParticipants are expected to commit to attending a
 ll four learning circle sessions.\nNo AI experience is required.\nHow to J
 oi\nn a Learning Circle:\nRegister once on the first session of this event
  series\, in order to attend all sessions.\nPlease sign up with a\nvalid e
 mail address\n.\nA valid TPL library card is required for online circles
 .\nAttend all four sessions (online via Zoom\, date: May 6\, May 13\, May 
 20 and May 27)\nRegistration is a two-step procedure. First\, participants
  must complete their registration through this page. After this step\, lib
 rary staff will follow up to request additional information in order to co
 mplete the registration.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal inf
 ormation on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the
  Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The informatio
 n will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and eval
 uation. Questions about how the library handles your information can be di
 rected to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yo
 nge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69d93eb4129f12743837bc99
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:North York Central Library Film Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260520T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260520T161500
UID:69d576cdc1cf6f9a7583d8be@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:The North York Central Library Film Club meets monthly on Wedn
 esdays. There is a short\, informal discussion after the screening\, time 
 permitting. All films begin at 2:00 pm in the Auditorium.\nRegistration is
  not required. Please contact the Browsery Department at 416-395-5672 for 
 more information.\nHamnet (2025)\nRunning time: 125 minutes\nDirector: Chl
 oé Zhao\nStarring: Jessie Buckley\, Paul Mescal\, Emily Watson\, and Joe 
 Alwyn\nWilliam Shakespeare falls for the free-spirited Agnes. Their whirlw
 ind romance leads to marriage and three children\, but as Will's theatrica
 l ambitions draw him to London\, Agnes remains behind to manage the househ
 old. When tragedy strikes\, their bond is deeply tested-but through grief 
 and resilience\, their journey inspires the creation of Shakespeare's time
 less masterpiece\, Hamlet.\nNext dates:\nJune 24 : The Great Escaper
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, Auditorium\, 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69d576cdc1cf6f9a7583d8be
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:FULL - Seniors Digital Literacy
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260504T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260504T160000
UID:69af49d4cbf6405d3569db4a@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This program is\nFULL.\nRichview Library will run Seniors Digi
 tal Literacy again in\nSeptember 2026\n.  If you are interested in attend
 ing the September session\,\nplease visit Richview Library to fill out an 
 application.\nSeniors Digital Literacy\nis a 6-week course designed to bui
 ld your confidence by introducing new skills slowly. At the end of the cou
 rse you will have a solid foundation of new skills and the confidence to c
 ontinue learning.\nIs This Course Right for You?\nFor seniors: beginners\,
  with very limited or no computer experience\n*6 weeks:\nwith 1 class and
  1 practice session weekly\n*This session will not meet the week of May 18
 \, 2026 due to the holiday closure.\nWhat Will You Learn?\nBasic tools suc
 h as the mouse and the keyboard\nHow to search online for information\, se
 rvices and entertainment\nHow to use email to keep in touch with family an
 d friends\nInternet safety\, security and privacy\nInterested participants
  must fill out an application.  Applications are available at Richview L
 ibrary.\nPlease call or visit Richview Library for additional information
 .
LOCATION:Richview\, Learning Centre\, 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69af49d4cbf6405d3569db4a
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
