BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Transforming Garbage: Collage a Postcard
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260508T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260508T150000
UID:69a206a68d5e2d09336219cd@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Gain an understanding of creating art with upcycled materials
  through the art of collage. By using magazines and a card stock surface
 \, participants will start cutting out images and words that relate to the
 ir desired work of art. This workshop will encourage the process of workin
 g with collage as a non-precious material and inspire participants to cr
 eate a piece of art with the materials in their own home/community.\nThis 
 workshop will be delivered by Alysha Rocca\, an emerging artist who holds
  a BFA from OCAD University. Working with the theme of sustainability\, A
 lysha weaves together the threads of feminism and environmental conscious
 ness.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this fo
 rm is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries A
 ct\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used
