BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Finding Recovery Through Exercise Skills and Hope (FRESH): Movie o
 r Walk Tuesdays
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260505T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260505T153000
UID:695ee95c94297d3600a3ec94@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This program helps people stay active\, make friends\, learn n
 ew skills\, and have fun. Meet new folks\, build connections\, and tell us
  about programs and services you would like to see in the neighbourhood!\n
 A feature film will be shown every Tuesday. Connect with others and watch
  something new\, or revisit an old favourite in a safe and friendly settin
 g. Participants can also connect on a neighbourhood walk with a F.R.E.S.H
 . peer.\nDrop-in\, all are welcome. Snacks and refreshments are provided 
 for all participants. Ingredient lists will be available at the program.\n
 This program is in collaboration with\nGerstein Crisis Centre's F.R.E.S.H.
  initiative\n.
LOCATION:Sanderson\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/695ee95c94297d3600a3ec94
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Tea & Entertainment
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T160000
UID:6918e462dff9d93e00d0347a@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy watching DVDs in the Library Auditorium.\nCoffee\, tea a
 nd cookies or snacks will be served after the film.. Ingredient lists will
  be available upon request.\nSurinam: Ghost River\nSurinam Ghost River” 
 follows explorer Steve Backshall and his team as they navigate a previousl
 y unmapped river deep in Surinam’s jungle. Facing shallow waters\, water
 falls\, and dense vegetation\, the expedition tested their endurance as th
 ey dragged boats through rugged terrain. Closed Captions. 50 minutes. 2020
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6918e462dff9d93e00d0347a
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
