BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Youth Hub: Improv for Wellness and Belonging
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T170000
UID:697131da1e64afd01e55c41c@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Laughter is good for the soul! Improv is an opportunity to exp
 lore the value of presence\, acceptance\, collaboration and a sense of hum
 our. Participants are led through creative exercises and games to connect\
 , create and laugh! Want to get ready for a presentation at school? Prep y
 our acting skills for an audition? Or feel more confident in general? Or d
 o you just want to have some fun!? Join us!\nThis program is part of Youth
  Hub service. Youth Hubs are a welcoming place for teens after school and 
 in the summer\, where helpful staff are always available. Free\, nutritiou
 s snacks are offered daily. Drop by a branch with a\nYouth Hub\nor call th
 e branch to find out more.
LOCATION:Cedarbrae\, Youth Hub\, 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/697131da1e64afd01e55c41c
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
