BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Tea & Movies: Now\, Voyager (1942)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260608T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260608T160000
UID:69b1e4d51e64afd01e6178c7@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an afternoon of classic movies. Tea & coffee will 
 be served.\nNow\, Voyager (1942)\nBoston spinster Charlotte has had her li
 fe controlled entirely by her wealthy mother\, Mrs. Henry Vale. Feeling de
 spondent\, she's convinced to spend time in a sanitarium. Soon she is tran
 sformed into a sophisticated\, confident woman. On a cruise to South Ameri
 ca\, Charlotte meets and begins an affair with Jerry Durrance\, a married 
 architect. Six months later\, she returns home and confronts her mother wi
 th her independence.\nNo registration required.
LOCATION:Don Mills\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b1e4d51e64afd01e6178c7
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
