BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:AI in the Production Workflow: Shortening the Distance Between Int
 ent and Creative Output
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260611T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260611T200000
UID:69a8bf7f2866a5b4883ff411@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join our Innovator in Residence\, Joel S. Silver\, in conversa
 tion with Sean Evans about AI in the production workflow.\nSean Evans. Cre
 ative technologist and immersive producer working at the intersection of f
 ilm\, XR\, and AI. Over 25 years building pipelines and productions for VI
 CE\, NFB\, Amazon\, Discovery\, and international festival circuits includ
 ing TIFF\, Venice\, Cannes\, and Sundance. Currently in production with Da
 niel Lanois on an AI-driven interactive installation\, and recently delive
 red The Tragically Hip: No Dress Rehearsal for Amazon Prime—TIFF 2024 Wo
 rld Premiere. Member and Juror for the Academy of Digital Arts & Sciences 
 (Webbys). Speaker at SXSW and SIGGRAPH.\nThis program is part of the Innov
 ator in Residence (AI and Music Production) program\, which is designed to
  help beginner and intermediate learners build knowledge and creative skil
 ls and get hands-on with current AI tools in music production and learn ab
 out the history\, copyright and ethics of generative music. For more infor
 mation and a full list of programs\, visit\ntpl.ca/airesident\n.
LOCATION:Fairview\, Room 201\, 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a8bf7f2866a5b4883ff411
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
