SUMMARY:Birding 101:  Tips for Bird Watching in Toronto
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T193000
UID:69b847dd23b45fff20f221cf@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Birding is fun\, easy and can be done anywhere - in your own b
 ackyard\, or in a local park.  Learn everything you need to know to get s
 tarted\, from choosing binoculars and field guides\, to where and when to 
 bird in your neighbourhood\, and identify the  birds you are likely to fi
 nd in the city.  Find out about clubs and field trips\, birding ethics\, 
 and protection and conservation efforts.  Presented by Monika Croydon\, a
  member of the Toronto Ornithological Club.\nThis is a program for adults.
