BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Painting the Seasons - A Pipa Solo Concert
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260516T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260516T150000
UID:69a59e8d1e64afd01e5f189e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Internationally renowned and Toronto-based Pipa artist Wen Z
 hao\, performs on the ancient Chinese instrument\, the Pipa\, a plucked i
 nstrument similar to the lute\, with over 2\,000 years of history\, intro
 duced through the ancient Silk Road from Central Asia and becoming one of 
 the most significant solo instruments in musical history.\nThis solo conce
 rt celebrates China's rich musical legacy with a traditional and folk mu
 sic repertoire spanning across dynasties\, painting a vivid picture of our
  natural landscape through the four seasons and classical poetry songs. We
 n will also talk about some traditional Chinese Festivals\, such as the Lu
 nar New Year and Dragon Boat festivals.\nWen Zhao is an acclaimed pipa vir
 tuoso\, “a sensitive and lyrical performer”. Born in Beijing\, she beg
 an to learn the Pipa at the age of seven\, having studied under the renown
 ed pipa master Wang Fan Di at the China Conservatory of Music.\nWen is esp
 ecially honoured to be one of the featured musicians for the CBC award-win
 ning documentary film\nThe Four Seasons Mosaic\n. The Toronto Star describ
 ed her as “a virtuoso player who displayed her dexterity and percussive 
 skills on the pipa\,” while a reviewer in WholeNote magazine described h
 er as “the Jimi Hendrix of the pipa."\nInformation Collection Notice:\nT
 he personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Li
 brary under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d).
  The information will only be used for event and program registration\, de
 livery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your inform
 ation can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-39
 7-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Richview\, Auditorium\, Lower Level
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a59e8d1e64afd01e5f189e
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
