BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:SP Book Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260528T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260528T150000
UID:698bc90d8ef687c592a796c6@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Discuss diverse and inclusive titles from a variety of genres 
 on the fourth Thursday of every month!\nThis month we will be discussing\n
 How to Pronounce Knife\nby Souvankham Thammavongsa.\nTold with tendernes
 s and wry humor\, this collection illuminates the lives of characters faci
 ng the sometimes absurd realities of starting over—from a former boxer s
 eeking redemption in a nail salon to a bus driver grappling with betrayal.
  Through stories of unexpected romances and complicated family bonds\, the
  book explores the limits of love and the price of belonging\nPick up a ph
 ysical copy at the branch before the meeting\, or find copies through our 
 website in various formats. Registration is required and begins Apr. 23\, 
 2026.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this fo
 rm is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries A
 ct\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used
  for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions a
 bout how the library handles your information can be directed to Answerlin
 e staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toront
 o ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Spadina Road\, Canoe Table\, center of branch
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698bc90d8ef687c592a796c6
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
