DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260422T150000
UID:6970fd5691e4576f847dd8f3@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:After a gentle alien becomes stranded on Earth\, the being is 
 discovered and befriended by a young boy named Elliott (Henry Thomas). Bri
 nging the extraterrestrial into his suburban California house\, Elliott in
 troduces E.T.\, as the alien is dubbed\, to his brother and his little sis
 ter\, Gertie (Drew Barrymore)\, and the children decide to keep its existe
 nce a secret. Soon\, however\, E.T. falls ill\, resulting in government in
 tervention and a dire situation for both Elliott and the alien.\nRated PG\
 n2 Hours
LOCATION:Cedarbrae\, FCCR (First-Floor Auditorium)
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6970fd5691e4576f847dd8f3
