BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Movie Screening: 12 Angry Men
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260520T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260520T150000
UID:6970fc59c967cb4120832d7b@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Following the closing arguments in a murder trial\, the 12 mem
 bers of the jury must deliberate\, with a guilty verdict meaning death for
  the accused\, an inner-city teen. As the dozen men try to reach a unanimo
 us decision while sequestered in a room\, one juror (Henry Fonda) casts co
 nsiderable doubt on elements of the case. Personal issues soon rise to the
  surface\, and conflict threatens to derail the delicate process that will
  decide one boy's fate.\nSuitable for ages 12+ (No official rating)\n1 Hou
 r 36 Minutes
LOCATION:Cedarbrae\, FCCR (First-Floor Auditorium)
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6970fc59c967cb4120832d7b
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
