UID:69ce747ffca21471b7edfd8f@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:At a Death Café people\, often strangers\, gather to eat cake
 \, drink tea and discuss death. The objective is 'to increase awareness of
  death with a view to helping people make the most of their (finite) lives
 '.\nA Death Café is a group directed discussion of death with no agenda\,
  objectives or themes. It is a discussion group rather than a grief suppor
 t or counselling session.
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, Room 2/3
