BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:FULL - Seniors Digital Literacy
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260525T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260525T160000
UID:69af49d4cbf6405d3569db4c@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This program is\nFULL.\nRichview Library will run Seniors Digi
 tal Literacy again in\nSeptember 2026\n.  If you are interested in attend
 ing the September session\,\nplease visit Richview Library to fill out an 
 application.\nSeniors Digital Literacy\nis a 6-week course designed to bui
 ld your confidence by introducing new skills slowly. At the end of the cou
 rse you will have a solid foundation of new skills and the confidence to c
 ontinue learning.\nIs This Course Right for You?\nFor seniors: beginners\,
  with very limited or no computer experience\n*6 weeks:\nwith 1 class and
  1 practice session weekly\n*This session will not meet the week of May 18
 \, 2026 due to the holiday closure.\nWhat Will You Learn?\nBasic tools suc
 h as the mouse and the keyboard\nHow to search online for information\, se
 rvices and entertainment\nHow to use email to keep in touch with family an
 d friends\nInternet safety\, security and privacy\nInterested participants
  must fill out an application.  Applications are available at Richview L
 ibrary.\nPlease call or visit Richview Library for additional information
 .
LOCATION:Richview\, Learning Centre\, 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69af49d4cbf6405d3569db4c
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
