BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Branch Art Exhibit: Works by Séamus Easton
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260402T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T235959
UID:69c6d7468d5e2d0933680162@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Throughout the month of April\, the works of Séamus Easton 
 are on display at Forest Hill Library.\nSéamus Easton is a photographer\,
  writer\, and creative director\, with over a decade of experience across 
 creative\, professional\, and academic settings. With a diverse career al
 so including acting\, scriptwriting\, instructional design\, and community
  organizing\, Séamus excels at blending creative and documentary styles 
 to fully capture the essence of his subjects. His work has appeared in Pho
 toVogue\, MOB Journal\, SaintEight\, and many others.\n"This series of ima
 ges was captured while working with musician Lucas Penner (subject) to fil
 m the music video for his song\, 'Hope Princeton'. The images reflect the
  content of the song\, half-lamenting\, half-adoring the journey of a solo
  musician touring the country by himself. Now 15 years into his career\, 
 Lucas is returning to emotionally significant places as if in a picture bo
 ok\, showing the audience the landscape that shaped him."\nThis exhibit is
  part of TPL's\nArt Exhibits Space\nprogram. Toronto Public Library provid
 es space for local artists to exhibit their work at locations across the c
 ity. These exhibits aim to reflect the diverse cultural interests of the c
 ity and its neighbourhoods.\nThe exhibit can be viewed during\nForest Hill
 \nbranch open hours.\nFree. All are welcome.\nImage credit: Artist: Séamu
 s Easton\; photography\; Sage Sunrise
LOCATION:Forest Hill
