BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Container Gardening: Supporting Our Local Pollinators in Small Sp
 aces
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260526T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260526T150000
UID:69d7cc775c04bc0fc061da7e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Pollinators need a supply of nectar throughout the growing sea
 son\, so if you are planting up pots for your garden or balcony\, why not 
 choose plants that will attract birds\, bees\, and butterflies? This demon
 stration\, led by a Toronto Master Gardener\, will start with how to choos
 e soil\, plants\, and containers\, and how to arrange them to maximize the
 ir positive impact on the environment. At the end of the demonstration\, m
 aterials will be shared with participants\, while supplies last.\nThis pro
 gram is part of TPL's Our Fragile Planet program series\, supported by Fri
 ends of Toronto Public Library\, South Chapter.
LOCATION:Wychwood
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69d7cc775c04bc0fc061da7e
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
