DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T150000
UID:69b9ba798691052e39e5eeb9@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:By April and May\, spring bird migration is in full swing! Fin
 d out about migratory birds that travel from their tropical winter homes\,
  through Toronto to their northern breeding grounds.​​ Get to know our
  own nesting birds and learn how they raise their families through the sum
 mer.\nPresented by Monika Croydon\, avid birder and photographer\,        
  and member of the Toronto Ornithological Club.\nAll are welcome. Drop-in\
 , no registration is required.
LOCATION:High Park\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b9ba798691052e39e5eeb9
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
