BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Author Presentation\, Story-Behind-The-Story: Man at the Door
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260512T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260512T150000
UID:697e4d691e64afd01e582e3c@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Author Desmond P. Ryan will discuss in detail the true homocid
 e investigation that inspired the crime fiction novel\, "Man at the Door"\
 ; the third in the Mike O'Shea Crime series. He will provide the audience 
 with an opportunity to see where reality and fiction overlap. The story an
 d presentation examine the missteps of the first officers on scene\, the r
 ole of the media in a criminal investigation\, the wild theories offered b
 y the defence\, and the importance of common sense.\nDesmond P. Ryan is a 
 retired Toronto Police Detective with almost 30 years of service with Toro
 nto Police Services before trasitioning to an award-winning crime fiction 
 author.\nMan at the Door
LOCATION:Victoria Village\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/697e4d691e64afd01e582e3c
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
