UID:694432a26724c63d00e78fe9@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Formerly known as Cedarbrae’s Jane Austen Book Club\, we now
  invite you to meet us monthly to discuss works from the 18th-20th centuri
 es\, books about those works and their authors\, and re-tellings and books
  inspired by them. Ask to borrow print copies at the branch or borrow digi
 tal versions online from Libby or Hoopla.\n*At our June meeting we will be
  discussing chapters 20-end of\nJane Eyre\nby Charlotte Brontë*\nInformat
 ion Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is collected
  by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 2
 0(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for event and 
 program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the li
 brary handles your information can be directed to Answerline staff at\nans
 werline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Cedarbrae\, FCCR on main floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/694432a26724c63d00e78fe9
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
