BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Kimbap Workshop with Chef Sang
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260523T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260523T150000
UID:69ce7fec81b67dfe32b09b10@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:TV host and celebrity chef Sang Kim will teach the basics of m
 aking Korean-style kimbap\, exactly like you see them on your favourite K-
 dramas. Participants will roll and cut kimbap using ingredients prepared b
 y the Chef and eat their own creations. A brief history of kimbap\, its di
 fferences from the Japanese sushi roll\, and eating etiquette will also be
  shared. Prizes are also awarded for best kimbap creations.\nIngredients i
 nclude egg and fishcake (which participants do not have to use)\nAll parti
 cipants attending including adults and kids must register for this program
 .\nInformation Collection Notice\n: The personal information on this form 
 is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\
 , sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used fo
 r event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions abou
 t how the library handles your information can be directed to Answerline s
 taff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto O
 N M4W 2G8
LOCATION:Don Mills\, Lower level program room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69ce7fec81b67dfe32b09b10
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:DIY Nights: Craft and Socials
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260522T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260522T190000
UID:6963eb2ac967cb4120814844@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Looking for a fun\, low stress way to try new crafts and meet 
 fellow makers? Join us for DIY Night: Craft & Socials\, a monthly adult cr
 afting program featuring a new project each month. Learn something new\, w
 ork at your own pace\, and enjoy casual conversation in a welcoming space.
  Materials are provided\, and beginners are always welcome.\nRegistration 
 is required due to limited supply. However drop in on the day of is welcom
 ed for vacant spots.\nTime: Fourth Friday of each month from 5-7\nUpcoming
  Events:\nMarch 27: Sticker Scenes\n3DBuild a mini world by layering stick
 ers into a playful\, themed scene\nApril 24: Crepe/Tissue Flowers\nA hand
 s-on program where participants learn to create beautiful\, handcrafted fl
 owers using tissue paper and crepe paper\nInformation Collection Notice:\n
 The personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public L
 ibrary under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d)
 . The information will only be used for event and program registration\, d
 elivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your infor
 mation can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-3
 97-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Sanderson\, Program Room on Main Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6963eb2ac967cb4120814844
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
