BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Amazing! Fantastic! Astounding! Science Fiction and the Pulp Magaz
 ines
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260216T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260503T235959
UID:697268c4491b809c6f1475f4@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us at the Merril Collection for this exhibit on the incre
 dible pulp magazines. The pulps were fiction magazines that dominated Nort
 h America from the 1890s to the 1950s. For over half a century\, they were
  the most affordable source of mass entertainment. And they were also the 
 main source of science fiction.\nExplore the rise and fall of the pulps. C
 elebrate the 100th anniversary of Amazing Stories\, the first science fict
 ion pulp. Discover decades-old pulps\, original pulp art\, books and more.
LOCATION:Lillian H. Smith\, Merril Collection Reading Room\, 3rd Floor. Ex
 hibit is open during the same hours as the branch.
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/697268c4491b809c6f1475f4
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
