BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Matcha Workshop and Mini Japanese Tea Ceremony
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260611T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260611T193000
UID:69b847902b552e8e21b32eef@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Discover more about powdered green tea\, Matcha.  We will exp
 lain all about Matcha:  how/when it is harvested\, and how to make Matcha
  in a traditional way.  Participants will learn how to make traditional M
 atcha\, compare colour/aroma/taste of different grades of Matcha\, and lea
 rn the best types of Matcha to buy.  Participants can also try Japanese t
 raditional sweet Wasanbon (pure sugar treat) which is normally served with
  Matcha.\nOnline registration is required beginning May 25th.\nThis is a p
 rogram for adults.
LOCATION:Mimico Centennial
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b847902b552e8e21b32eef
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
