BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Festival Select: You Can Live Forever (Sarah Watts\, Mark Slutsky\
 , 2022)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260427T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260427T203000
UID:698f951a94297d3600ac1f5e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join the Society and Recreation department of the North York C
 entral Library for monthly screenings of fiction and non-fiction films tha
 t push the boundaries of the medium. This month we are showing Sarah Watts
 ' and Mark Slutsky's\nYou Can Live Forever\n(2022).\nSynopsis (Criterion P
 ictures): When lesbian teen Jaime is sent to live in a Jehovah's Witness 
 community\, she falls hard for a devout Witness girl and the two embark on
  an intense affair with consequences that will reshape the rest of their l
 ives.\nNo registration required.
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, Room 101
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698f951a94297d3600ac1f5e
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
