DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260527T153000
UID:69cd79b9b6c4ac1fedc996a6@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:For beginners.\nLearn basic searches to find records of your a
 ncestors using the popular genealogy database Ancestry Library Edition. Fo
 r those with little or no experience with family history. In this class yo
 u will:-learn the basics of compiling a family tree-use sample searches to
  explore Ancestry records for birth\, marriage\, death and the census-expe
 riment with wildcards to improve your searches.\nPrerequisites: Basic mous
 e and keyboarding skills required.
LOCATION:Northern District\, eLearning Centre
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69cd79b9b6c4ac1fedc996a6
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
