BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Rise and Sprawl: The Condominiumization of Toronto
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T200000
UID:69a489d8db89981d9df846a3@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:In this talk\, the rapid verticalization of our city and specu
 lations on variations and more imaginative alternatives are discussed alon
 g with an examination of the role of developers\, architecture\, marketing
  agencies and governing bodies.\nAlexander Josephson is co-founder of PART
 ISANS\, lecturer at the University of Toronto\, John H. Daniels Faculty of
  Architecture\, Landscape and Design and co-author of\nRise and Sprawl\nwi
 th architectural historian Hans Ibelings.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Beeton Hall
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a489d8db89981d9df846a3
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
