BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Let's Make Toronto More Bird-Friendly
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260420T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260420T190000
UID:69850b4e6724c63d00f0d4c6@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Toronto was one of the first four cities designated as a Bird 
 Friendly City by Nature Canada in 2021\, but what does that mean\, and wha
 t can we do to help birds thrive in our beautiful city?\nIn this presentat
 ion\, learn how Torontonians can help mitigate threats to birds and how To
 ronto's location on Lake Ontario is part of an important bird migratory ro
 ute.\nPresented by\nBird Friendly City Toronto\n\, a volunteer-led environ
 mental organization dedicated to making our beautiful city a safer and bet
 ter place for birds through habitat protection\, threat reduction\, and ed
 ucational resources.\nThis program is part of TPL's\nOur Fragile Planet\np
 rogram series\, supported by Friends of Toronto Public Library\, South Cha
 pter.​
LOCATION:Deer Park\, 2nd Floor\nRoom 204
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69850b4e6724c63d00f0d4c6
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Canadian Film Day: The Apprenticeship of Duddy Kravitz
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T160000
UID:69d69245491b809c6f260aa0@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Canadian Film Day with your local library!\nDuddy Kr
 avitz (Richard Dreyfuss) lives in the shadow of his brother\, whom his fat
 her\, Max (Jack Warden)\, and his Uncle Benjy (Joseph Wiseman) are helping
  to put through medical school. Seeking to rise above his family's poverty
 \, Duddy aspires to purchase and develop lakefront land near the hotel res
 ort he is working at in Quebec's Laurentian Mountains. But Duddy's quest t
 o make something of himself reveals a harsh determination to do whatever h
 e has to in order to make his dream a reality.\nRuntime: 2Hr1Min\nRated PG
LOCATION:Lillian H. Smith\, Basement-Level\, Program Room A
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69d69245491b809c6f260aa0
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
