DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260507T200000
UID:69612a266f926136000f422d@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Come one come all!\nParticipants will get to experience collab
 orative storytelling at its finest.\nIn this limited Campaign\, participan
 ts will be crafting the world\, their characters\, and potentially the dir
 ection of the story.\nThe campaign will begin with a session of worldbuild
 ing\, character creation\, and a democratic vote on themes and setting. Th
 is will be known as our session zero.\nFollowing sessions will see our cha
 racters progress through a short 3 - 4 month campaign. Relationships will 
 be built\, challenges conquered\, and enemies defeated!\nThis program is i
 ntended for a mature audience.*\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe perso
 nal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library un
 der the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The inf
 ormation will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery a
 nd evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your information ca
 n be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\,
  789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Highland Creek\, Meeting Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69612a266f926136000f422d
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
