BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Tea & Entertainment
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T160000
UID:6918e3d22ea1b13000850550@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy watching DVDs in the Library Auditorium.\nCoffee\, tea a
 nd cookies or snacks will be served after the film.. Ingredient lists will
  be available upon request.\nThe Most Powerful Black Holes in the Universe
 \nThis film explores how black holes were discovered\, the science behind 
 them\, and how modern technology made their study possible. Using clear ex
 planations\, archival footage\, and stunning animation\, it makes complex 
 physics accessible to everyone. The film also looks ahead\, asking how pow
 erful these holes can get and what can they may tell us about space & time
 . What will they reveal about the universe\,—and our place within it. 48
  minutes.
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6918e3d22ea1b13000850550
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
