SUMMARY:Pebble Picassos: ROCK PAINTING
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260428T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260428T170000
UID:69b5734167801235ed71f6d0@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a fun and creative rock painting program at the li
 brary! Children will decorate smooth stones using bright paints\, markers\
 , and their imagination. Create colorful patterns\, animals\, inspirationa
 l messages\, or silly faces—there’s no limit to what you can design. P
 ainted rocks can be taken home\, shared with friends\, or hidden around th
 e community for others to find. This hands-on activity encourages creativi
 ty\, self-expression\, and a love of art.\nAll materials will be provided.
  Dress for mess and get ready to create your own tiny masterpiece!
LOCATION:Humber Summit\, Auditorium\, Lower level
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b5734167801235ed71f6d0
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
