BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Branch Art Exhibit: Works by Denise Gracias
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260401T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T235959
UID:69cd625ce2a2952aed0bfd87@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Throughout the month of April\, the wor\nks of artist Denise 
 Gracias are on display at the Morningside Branch\n.\nDenise Gracias is a 
 Scarborough-based visual artist who works in a variety of media. Her first
  artistic ventures began in grade one when she was found to have innate dr
 awing skills\n.\nShe won an art contest and would draw and paint the mural
 s for school plays\n.\nShe did not pursue art after elementary school\, bu
 t returned to it decades later\n\,\ntaking recreational courses. Her first
  solo exhibition was in January/2017 at ArtSquare Cafe\n\,\nfollowed by se
 veral group and solo shows in Canada\, USA and Europe\n"Denise Gracias bel
 ieves that each person has dignity and is a vital part of every community\
 n.\nHer artwork provides a space where the viewer can see each leaf\n\,\nb
 lade of grass is integral to the forest or meadow\n\,\nyet distinct. She i
 s interested in the 'big picture' and the little details\n.\nThis is shown
  in her landscapes which are vast\, yet have the details of the flowers\n\
 ,\ngrass\n\,\ntwigs\n\,\netc\n.\,\nshowing the dignity of all creation\n.\
 nDenise paints from her own photos or en plein air\n."\nThis exhibit is pa
 rt of\nTPL's Art Exhibit\nprogram. Toronto Public Library provides space f
 or local artists to exhibit their work at locations across the city. These
  exhibits aim to reflect the diverse cultural interests of the city and it
 s neighbourhoods. The exhibit can be viewed during the\nMorningside Branch
 \nopen hours. Please check the Morningside Branch page before your visit.\
 nFree. All are welcome.\nImage credit: Denise Gracias\; coloured pencil\;
  Three Apples
LOCATION:Morningside
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69cd625ce2a2952aed0bfd87
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
