DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T153000
UID:699df1c74dacf581ff7d99b2@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join City of Toronto Urban Forestry staff for a presentation o
 n invasive plants commonly found around homes in Toronto. Learn how to ide
 ntify these species\, understand their impact\, and how to manage them. Yo
 u’ll also get tips on supporting local biodiversity through enhancing na
 tive habitats. Perfect for gardeners\, homeowners\, and anyone interested 
 in urban ecology.\nNo registration. Drop-in.
LOCATION:Victoria Village\, Program Room
