BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Conceivable Families: Building 2SLGBTQ+ Families in Toronto
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260610T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260610T190000
UID:69cade061e64afd01e65bce8@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Conceivable Families is a one-hour workshop for 2SLGBTQ+ inten
 ded parents at any stage of their family building journeys. Beginning with
  the basics of what to expect and how to navigate decisions and systems\, 
 it covers emotional and relational realities of fertility and family build
 ing processes. Together\, we’ll explore strategies for clear communicati
 on with partners\, providers\, and support networks\, while also moving as
  well as practical tools for self-care and emotional regulation during wha
 t can be an unpredictable and vulnerable experience.\nLaine Halpern Zisman
  is the Director of Training and Education at Birth Mark and a certified f
 ertility support practitioner and full spectrum doula.\nThis is a program 
 for adults. No registration required. Drop in.
LOCATION:Parkdale\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69cade061e64afd01e65bce8
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
