DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260513T200000
UID:69bc371b1e64afd01e635887@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Experience the transformative power of writing in an inclusive
  space!\nA Writers Collective of Canada (WCC) workshop is unlike any other
 . We write together\, share first drafts in an encouraging environment\, l
 isten deeply to one another\, and receive supportive feedback. Tap into yo
 ur story and explore your voice in an environment of dignity\, courage\, a
 nd respect.\nwcc-cec.org\nNo experience required. Materials are provided.
  Beginners are welcome!\nRegistration opens on April 13\, 2026.
LOCATION:Danforth/Coxwell\, 2nd Floor Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69bc371b1e64afd01e635887
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
