BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:NatureTO: Trees Around the Branch Tour
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T143000
UID:699867dab0595799c09e22a0@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join the City of Toronto Urban Forestry staff at the Danforth/
 Coxwell Library to explore the natural world on a local neighbourhood tou
 r.\nLearn how to recognize different species and acquire fun facts about 
 their cultural and ecological importance.\nThe tour will start and end at 
 the Danforth/Coxwell Library\, Main Floor\, and will be guided by the Cit
 y of Toronto Urban Forestry staff. Children under 12 must be accompanied 
 by a parent/caregiver. There may be uneven\, unpaved surfaces along the r
 oute. Please dress and prepare accordingly for this outdoor program (e.g. 
 gloves/mittens\, hats\, sunscreen\, water\, comfortable shoes). This progr
 am takes place rain or shine. In the event of severe inclement weather\, r
 egistrants will be notified of an alternative date.\nRegister for the even
 t online. For assistance\, visit the branch or call 416-393-7783.
LOCATION:Danforth/Coxwell\, Main Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699867dab0595799c09e22a0
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
