DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260529T113000
UID:69d7fd6d4dacf581ff87afb6@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Participants learn fundamental skills in note-reading\, pitch\
 , dance\, singing\, and Orff/Kodaly percussion techniques\, as well as soc
 ial skills like sharing\, focus\, teamwork\, and listening. Participants s
 ing\, play\, pitched and unpitched percussion instruments\, learn music th
 eory and notation\, and build confidence together to develop a strong musi
 cal foundation. Music and Movement classes will be led by a Sistema Toront
 o Teaching Artist.\nDrop In\n.\nNo Registration Required. For Children Ag
 es 2-5\, along with parent(s)/caregiver(s).
LOCATION:Downsview\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69d7fd6d4dacf581ff87afb6
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
