BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Computers for Beginners 1: Use the Mouse
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260413T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260413T153000
UID:69a064a06724c63d00f55450@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:A class on how to use a mouse for absolute beginners with litt
 le or no computer experience.\nIn this first session you will:\nObserve an
 d practice how to operate a mouse effectively.\nUnderstand various mouse p
 ointers and cursors\nReview basic keyboard functions\nUse the mouse for ba
 sic Windows functions\nUpon completion of this class students will be able
  to use a computer\n mouse at a basic level and will be able to go online 
 for additional \npractice.\nPrerequisites: No computer experience required
 .\nFormat: Hands-on with demonstrations\nInformation Collection Notice:\nT
 he personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Li
 brary under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d).
  The information will only be used for event and program registration\, de
 livery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your inform
 ation can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-39
 7-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Riverdale\, Adult Program Room 1
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a064a06724c63d00f55450
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
