BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Youth for Entrepreneurship: Social Media Marketing
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260428T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260428T193000
UID:69a7230cdb89981d9df8754b@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:From passion project to standout brand — let’s go!\nIn thi
 s interactive workshop\, you’ll learn how to use social media strategica
 lly to grow your brand\, create scroll-stopping content\, and build real a
 udience loyalty — not just followers.\nLevel up your socials into someth
 ing that actually counts.\nRegistration required. Limited spots. This sess
 ion is intended for Young Adults\, but all ages are welcome.\nThis worksho
 p is part of the\nYouth for Entrepreneurship program\nled by the YMCA of G
 reater Toronto. Through hands-on sessions\, you’ll gain the digital tool
 s\, financial knowledge\, and creative strategies needed to build a busine
 ss idea from the ground up.\n----\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe per
 sonal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library 
 under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The i
 nformation will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery
  and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your information 
 can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981
 \, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Founders' Room (1st Floor)
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a7230cdb89981d9df8754b
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Film: La passion de Dodin Bouffant
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T141500
UID:697b7c9b94297d3600a86f5e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:France\, vers 1885. Cela fait 20 ans qu'Eugénie travaille com
 me cuisinière pour le célèbre gastronome Dodin. Le duo concocte des pla
 ts savoureux et uniques qui attirent de nombreux clients du monde entier. 
 Leur collaboration a donné naissance à une passion affectueuse\, même s
 i Eugénie n'a jamais voulu épouser Dodin. Le couple aime recevoir chez e
 ux des amis qui passent leur temps à manger et à discuter\, et il hésit
 e à apprendre les rudiments de leur métier à la jeune Pauline. Lorsqu'E
 ugénie tombe malade\, Dodin décide de cuisiner lui-même pour sa bien-ai
 mée.
LOCATION:Maryvale\, Meeting Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/697b7c9b94297d3600a86f5e
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
