BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:An Ancient Persian Romance: A Retelling of the Haft Paykar of Niza
 mi
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260511T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260511T200000
UID:69ab10292866a5b4884049d6@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Once in Ancient Persia\, there was a king who lived in a palac
 e of seven pavilions\, each dedicated to one of the planets...So begins th
 e story of one of the most celebrated romances in Persian classical litera
 ture\,\nThe Haft Paykar of Nizami.\nBahram Gur\, King of Persia undertakes
  a journey through the seven pavilions of his palace\, where a princess in
  each pavilion tells him a story that teaches him about love and about him
 self.\nCome listen to storyteller Ariel Balevi tell some of the stories th
 at Bahram Gur heard on this journey including: a story that is believed to
  be the earliest version of the 18th century fairy tale that inspired Pucc
 ini's opera\,\nTurandot.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, 1st floor\, Beeton Hall
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69ab10292866a5b4884049d6
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
