BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Seniors' Social - NatureTO's Our Urban Forest!
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260428T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260428T153000
UID:69a5afb48b29ea2800d37550@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Calling all older adults!\nCome join us at Morningside library
  every month (on the last Tuesday of the month) for a seniors' social. Enj
 oy a variety of topics\, guest speakers\, lively conversation\, & fun acti
 vities!\nApril's social is a NatureTO presentation by the City of Toronto 
 Urban Forestry team!\nToronto has one of the largest urban forests in the 
 world. The City of Toronto Urban Forestry team will deliver an informativ
 e presentation on the amazing natural habitat that reaches all corners of 
 Toronto. We will hear about what makes the urban forest so special\, and u
 nderstand the tools needed to explore and understand it better. Bring que
 stions & curiosities! Leave with greater confidence\, as well as a deeper 
 understanding of your City & the natural world around you!\nNo registratio
 n required. Drop-in! Light refreshments will be served.
LOCATION:Morningside\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a5afb48b29ea2800d37550
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
