BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Financial Workshops for Seniors with John Stapleton: Coming to Can
 ada and Leaving Canada
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260528T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260528T140000
UID:69b1f6b38089f23c67617887@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join social policy expert John Stapleton to plan for your fina
 ncial future.\nIf you are a low-income earner or advise low-income earners
 \, this program will help you understand:\nComing to Canada and Leaving Ca
 nada\nLearn what benefits you might be eligible for if you’ve resided in
  Canada for fewer than 40 years between the ages of 18 and 65\, or if you
 ’re planning on emigrating from Canada after retiring.\nThis is a drop-i
 n program. Registration is not required.
LOCATION:Maria A. Shchuka\, First Floor Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b1f6b38089f23c67617887
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
