DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T200000
UID:69bc7ce5ad384e40edb593a4@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Experience the transformative power of writing in an inclusive
  space!\nA Writers Collective of Canada (WCC) workshop is unlike any other
 . We write together\, share first drafts in an encouraging environment\, l
 isten deeply to one another\, and receive supportive feedback. Tap into yo
 ur story and explore your voice in an environment of dignity\, courage\, a
 nd respect. (wcc-cec.org)\nNo experience required. Beginners are welcome. 
 Materials are provided.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal info
 rmation on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the 
 Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information
  will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and evalu
 ation. Questions about how the library handles your information can be dir
 ected to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yon
 ge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Annette Street
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69bc7ce5ad384e40edb593a4
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
