SUMMARY:Finding Recovery Through Exercise Skills and Hope (FRESH): Movie o
 r Walk Tuesdays
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260519T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260519T153000
UID:695ee95c94297d3600a3ec96@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This program helps people stay active\, make friends\, learn n
 ew skills\, and have fun. Meet new folks\, build connections\, and tell us
  about programs and services you would like to see in the neighbourhood!\n
 A feature film will be shown every Tuesday. Connect with others and watch
  something new\, or revisit an old favourite in a safe and friendly settin
 g. Participants can also connect on a neighbourhood walk with a F.R.E.S.H
 . peer.\nDrop-in\, all are welcome. Snacks and refreshments are provided 
 for all participants. Ingredient lists will be available at the program.\n
 This program is in collaboration with\nGerstein Crisis Centre's F.R.E.S.H.
  initiative\n.
LOCATION:Sanderson\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/695ee95c94297d3600a3ec96
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Knit and Unwind
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260508T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260508T190000
UID:696282e791e4576f847bd090@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Bring your knitting\, crocheting\, or other needlework project
 s and join fellow makers for a relaxed evening of stitching and conversati
 on. Whether you?re a seasoned knitter or just starting out\, this is a wel
 coming space to share tips\, trade stories\, and enjoy the company of othe
 rs who love working with yarn. Supplies will be provided for beginners who
  are looking to get started on the hobby.\nTime: Second Friday of each mon
 th 5-7pm
LOCATION:Sanderson\, Main Floor Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/696282e791e4576f847bd090
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wellness Recovery Action Plan (WRAP)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260516T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260516T130000
UID:6968336576261f2800647630@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:WRAP is for\nanyone\nlooking to strengthen their well-being—
 whether you’re supporting your mental health\, managing stress\, or simp
 ly wanting to feel more balanced and resilient in daily life. Participant
 s will receive a\nWRAP certificate\nupon program completion.\nIn an 8-wee
 k WRAP group\, individuals explore:\nself-care tools like peer connections
 \, relaxation and mindfulness techniques\, stress reduction strategies\, a
 nd more\nresources for keeping well and feeling better in difficult times.
 \nInterested in learning more? Drop in for the information session on\nSat
 urday April 11 at 10am.\nThis WRAP Group meets\nevery Saturday\,\nonce a w
 eek for 8 weeks\, April 18-June 6\, 2026\, 10am - 1pm\n. Registration clos
 es after week 3\, or when full.\nTTC Presto tickets will be provided.\nSna
 cks and refreshments are provided for all participants. Ingredient lists w
 ill be available at the program.\nThis program is in collaboration with\n
 Gerstein Crisis Centre's WRAP initiative\n. Gerstein Crisis Centre is sole
 ly responsible for the protection of \npersonal information collected thro
 ugh the program registration \nprocess.
LOCATION:Northern District\, Room 200
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6968336576261f2800647630
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
