BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Excel Basics 3: PivotTables & Conditional Formatting
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260524T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260524T153000
UID:69d51f2366c3387a9d06094c@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Build on your basic Microsoft Excel skills and learn to use Ex
 cel data effectively.\nIn this third session\, you will:\nUse Conditional 
 Formatting to visualize data\nExplore the power of PivotTables for data su
 mmary and analysis\nSort and filter the data in tables and using slicers\n
 Take home practice data to improve your new skills\nUpon completion of thi
 s class\, you will be able to get more from your data using Pivot tables.\
 nPrerequisites:  Excel Basics 1 and 2 or equivalent knowledge. Basic mouse
  and keyboard skills required.\nFormat:  Hands-on with demonstrations\nInf
 ormation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is coll
 ected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, secti
 ons 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for event
  and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how t
 he library handles your information can be directed to Answerline staff at
 \nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2
 G8.
LOCATION:Albert Campbell\, Learning Centre\, 2nd floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69d51f2366c3387a9d06094c
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
