BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:1-on-1 Career Consultations with ACCES Employment Session 3
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260513T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260513T160000
UID:69b2bf75e2a2952aed0793d9@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Are you feeling stuck in your job search? Explore the incredib
 le resources and expertise offered by ACCES Employment. Connect with an Em
 ployment Consultant to get tailored resume reviews\, invaluable interview 
 tips\, and a wealth of additional support. Have a free 30-minute appointme
 nt and embark on a remarkable journey toward your dream job\, like 3-3:30 
 pm\, or 3:30-4 pm.\nPlease bring your finished resume/cover letter to the 
 session & your specific questions during the consultation\, for example e
 diting your resume\, job search\, volunteer opportunities\, or Interview 
 preparation etc.\nPlease cancel as soon as possible if you no longer need 
 the session before the program starts.\nSpace is limited. Help is availabl
 e on a first-come\, first serve basis.\nPlease arrive a few minutes early.
 \nIf no slots are available on your desired consultation date\, contact AC
 CES Employment directly for an appointment at\n416-443-9008\n(North York L
 ocation) /\n416-921-1800\n(Downtown Location). Or visit\naccesemployment.c
 a\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Publi
 c Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20
 (d). The information will only be used for event and program registration\
 , delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your in
 formation can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 41
 6-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Albert Campbell\, Small Meeting Room\, 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b2bf75e2a2952aed0793d9
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
