BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Nirvanna the Band the Show the Movie: National Canadian Film Day S
 creening
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T200000
UID:69b2bf4f81b67dfe32ac0bf8@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:"Based on the hit series\nNirvanna the Band the Show\n\, longt
 ime friends and bandmates Matt (Matt Johnson) and Jay (Jay McCarrol) have 
 been trying for over a dozen years to book a show for their band at The Ri
 voli through zany\, unconventional methods. When their latest (and most ou
 tlandish) effort leads to them accidentally travelling back in time\, they
  get taken on an adventure that threatens to change everything."\nThanks t
 o Reel Canada for providing the screening for this film.\nRunning Time: 95
  minutes
LOCATION:Riverdale\, Program Room 1
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b2bf4f81b67dfe32ac0bf8
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:1-on-1 Career Consultations with ACCES Employment Session 2
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260513T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260513T150000
UID:69b2bf15b6c4ac1fedc53b3c@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Are you feeling stuck in your job search? Explore the incredib
 le resources and expertise offered by ACCES Employment. Connect with an Em
 ployment Consultant to get tailored resume reviews\, invaluable interview 
 tips\, and a wealth of additional support. Have a free 30-minute appointme
 nt and embark on a remarkable journey toward your dream job\, like 2-2:30 
 pm\, or 2:30-3 pm.\nPlease bring your finished resume/cover letter to the 
 session & your specific questions during the consultation\, for example e
 diting your resume\, job search\, volunteer opportunities\, or Interview 
 preparation etc.\nPlease cancel as soon as possible if you no longer need 
 the session before the program starts.\nSpace is limited. Help is availabl
 e on a first-come\, first serve basis.\nPlease arrive a few minutes early.
 \nIf no slots are available on your desired consultation date\, contact AC
 CES Employment directly for an appointment at\n416-443-9008\n(North York L
 ocation) /\n416-921-1800\n(Downtown Location). Or visit\naccesemployment.c
 a\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Publi
 c Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20
 (d). The information will only be used for event and program registration\
 , delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your in
 formation can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 41
 6-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Albert Campbell\, Small Meeting Room\, 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b2bf15b6c4ac1fedc53b3c
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:1-on-1 Career Consultations with ACCES Employment Session 1
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260513T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260513T140000
UID:69b2be43e2a2952aed0793ce@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Are you feeling stuck in your job search? Explore the incredib
 le resources and expertise offered by ACCES Employment. Connect with an Em
 ployment Consultant to get tailored resume reviews\, invaluable interview 
 tips\, and a wealth of additional support. Book a free 30-minute appointme
 nt and embark on a remarkable journey toward your dream job\, like 1-1:30 
 pm\, 1:30-2 pm.\nPlease bring your finished resume/cover letter to the ses
 sion & your specific questions during the consultation\, for example edit
 ing your resume\, job search\, volunteer opportunities\, or Interview pre
 paration etc.\nPlease cancel as soon as possible if you no longer need the
  session before the program starts.\nSpace is limited. Help is available o
 n a first-come\, first serve basis.\nPlease arrive a few minutes early.\nI
 f no slots are available on your desired consultation date\, contact ACCES
  Employment directly for an appointment at\n416-443-9008\n(North York Loca
 tion) /\n416-921-1800\n(Downtown Location). Or visit\naccesemployment.ca\n
 The personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public L
 ibrary under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d)
 . The information will only be used for event and program registration\, d
 elivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your infor
 mation can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-3
 97-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Albert Campbell\, Small Meeting Room\, 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b2be43e2a2952aed0793ce
