DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T200000
UID:69aeecf04a9fd98b7f831d0b@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Conversation is the source of innovation!\nJoin TPL Innovation
  Council member\nZahra Ebrahim\nfor a series of lively book discussions ab
 out how we can build a better world by getting better at talking with eac
 h other.\nAt our April meeting\, we'll discuss the second and third chapte
 rs of\nTalk\n: The Science of Conversation and the Art of Being Ourselves\
 , by Alison Wood Brooks. Learn about:\nChoosing and preparing conversation
 al topics\nAsking good questions (and listening to the answers!)\nWe invit
 e you to jot down and bring five potential conversational topics to this m
 eeting!\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this 
 form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries
  Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be us
 ed for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions
  about how the library handles your information can be directed to Answerl
 ine staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toro
 nto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Bloor/Gladstone\, Program room\, lower level
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69aeecf04a9fd98b7f831d0b
