DESCRIPTION:Have you ever wondered why people believe in conspiracies?\nIn
  this book club\, we will be reading books that explore the social conditi
 ons that make people prone to extreme belief.\nThurs. Feb. 12\, 2:00-4:00p
 m\nA Lot of People Are Saying\nby Russell Muirhead\, Nancy Rosenblum\nThur
 s. Mar. 12\, 2:00-4:00pm\nConspiracy\nby Michael Shermer\nThurs. Apr 9\, 2
 :00-4:00pm\nTrust the Plan\nby Will Sommer\nThurs. May 14\, 2:00-4:00pm\nC
 atch and Kill\nby Ronan Farrow **BOOK CHANGE**\nThurs. Jun. 11\, 2:00-4:00
 pm\nEscaping the Rabbit Hole\nby Mick West
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Founder's Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698e5555707481383709ba64
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
