BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Writing Your Life: How to Tell Your Own Story
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260606T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260606T113000
UID:696fd187cbf6405d3564adc1@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Telling the vital stories of your life matters\, not just to y
 ou\, but to the world.\nAuthor Beth Kaplan will speak about her own experi
 ence publishing intimate details of her life in her memoirs\, and how for 
 over thirty years she has taught others to do so.\nBeth will guide you thr
 ough the process of choosing which life moments to write about\, where to 
 start\, and how to overcome challenges along the way.\nHer books will be a
 vailable for sale.\nBeth Kaplan\nis the author of a biography\, two memoir
 s —\nAll My Loving\nand\nLoose Woman\n— and\nTrue to Life\n\, a textbo
 ok guide to nonfiction writing. She has taught memoir writing for over thr
 ee decades\, is the winner of U of T’s Excellence in Teaching award\, an
 d has also taught at the San Miguel Writers’ Conference in Mexico\, Toro
 nto’s Word on the Street\, and the Kingston WritersFest.\nHer new memoir
 -in-essays\,\nMidlife Solo: writing through chaos to find my way in the wo
 rld\n\, was reviewed as “an extraordinary life\, written with tremendous
  heart\, insight\, and humour.”\nhttps://bethkaplan.ca/\nInformation Col
 lection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the
  Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 
 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for event and program
  registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library h
 andles your information can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline
 @tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.\nKey lin
 ks:
LOCATION:Gerrard/Ashdale\, 2nd floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/696fd187cbf6405d3564adc1
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
