BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Senior's Club Presents: All You Ever Wanted to Know About Black Ho
 les
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T150000
UID:695d3fc54a9fd98b7f75ee35@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Cliffcrest invites all to our Seniors Club! This month Dr. Il
 ana MacDonald of the Dunlap Institute for Astronomy and Physics presents\,
  "All You Ever Wanted to Know About Black Holes"  Black holes are some o
 f the strangest and most mysterious objects in the universe\, objects that
  bend the laws of physics as well as the imagination of scientists and non
 -scientists alike. In this talk\, you will learn about what a black hole i
 s\, where they come from\, and how we know they exist.\nDr. Ilana MacDonal
 d is the Public Outreach\, Communications\, and Events Strategist at the D
 unlap Institute for Astronomy & Astrophysics. She completed her Ph.D. in A
 strophysics at the University of Toronto\, studying the ripples in spaceti
 me that come from two black holes spiraling around each other.\nSeniors Cl
 ub meets on the 3rd week of every month.
LOCATION:Cliffcrest
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/695d3fc54a9fd98b7f75ee35
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
