BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Ontario Cottage: Perfect of Its Kind
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T200000
UID:6985274ed2bbe265eb2c82ad@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:In this illustrated talk\, co-author Lynne DiStefano will shar
 e her fascination with the Ontario Cottage\, one of the most recognizable 
 historic houseforms in the province.\nThe Ontario Cottage\nincludes 75 ful
 l-page photographs and examines the design lineage of the cottage\, its pr
 oportions and distinctive parts\, and the reasons for its enduring appeal.
 \nNo registration required.
LOCATION:Yorkville
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6985274ed2bbe265eb2c82ad
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
