UID:698b599d8d5e2d09335e425c@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:WRAP is for\nanyone\nlooking to strengthen their well-being—
 whether you’re supporting your mental health\, managing stress\, or simp
 ly wanting to feel more balanced and resilient in daily life. Participant
 s will receive a\nWRAP certificate\nupon program completion.\nIn an 8-wee
 k WRAP group\, individuals explore:\nself-care tools like peer connections
 \, relaxation and mindfulness techniques\, stress reduction strategies\, a
 nd more\nresources for keeping well and feeling better in difficult times.
 \nInterested in learning more? Drop in for the\ninformation session\non\nT
 ues. March 24\, 2026\, 5:00 pm - 7:00 pm.\nThis WRAP Group meets\nevery Tu
 esday\,\nonce a week for 8 weeks\, March 31-May 19\, 2026\, 5:00-8:00 pm\n
 . Registration closes after week 3\, or when full.\nTTC Presto tickets wil
 l be provided.\nSnacks and refreshments are provided for all participants.
  Ingredient lists will be available at the program.\nThis program is in c
 ollaboration with\nGerstein Crisis Centre's WRAP initiative\n. Gerstein Cr
 isis Centre is solely responsible for the protection of \npersonal informa
 tion collected through the program registration \nprocess.
LOCATION:Parkdale\, Meeting Room A
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698b599d8d5e2d09335e425c
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
