BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Google AI Essentials: In Person Learning Circle
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T150000
UID:69b443bb2866a5b48841d1bb@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Curious about artificial intelligence or want to learn practic
 al AI skills for work and personal use? Join our staff-facilitated learnin
 g circle to complete the self-paced Google AI Essentials specialization.\n
 This 10-hour introductory-level specialization\, offered through Coursera\
 , is available for free to learning circle participants. It is made up of 
 five courses\, each containing four units that consist of short videos\, a
 rticles\, assignments and a short multiple-choice quiz.\nBy completing the
  specialization\,\nyou will learn:\nHow AI works\nHow to write effective p
 rompts\nHow to use generative AI tools responsibly\nHow to identify AI's p
 otential biases and avoid harm\nHow to stay up to date with AI news\nAfter
  you complete the course\, you earn a Google certificate and a badge to sh
 are with others\nLearning Circles are study groups guided by\nlibrary staf
 f for people who want to complete the Google AI Essentials specialization 
 together in a welcoming space:\nLearners meet weekly and work together thr
 ough course materials.\nParticipants are expected to commit to attending a
 ll four learning circle sessions.\nNo AI experience is required.\nHow to J
 oin\na Learning Circle:\nRegister once on the first session of this event 
 series\, in order to attend all sessions.\nPlease sign up with a\nvalid em
 ail address\n.\nA valid TPL library card is required for online circles.
 \nAttend all four sessions (in person at Pape/Danforth Branch)\nRegistrati
 on is a two-step procedure. First\, participants must complete their regis
 tration through this page. After this step\, library staff will follow up 
 to request additional information in order to complete the registration.\n
 Information Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is c
 ollected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, se
 ctions 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for ev
 ent and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about ho
 w the library handles your information can be directed to Answerline staff
  at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4
 W 2G8.
LOCATION:Pape/Danforth\, Program Room 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b443bb2866a5b48841d1bb
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
