  limitées et que l’\ninscription\nest obligatoire.\nThe Community Conne
 ctions Program of the\nCentre francophone du Grand Toronto\n\, in partners
 hip with the Toronto Public Library\, invites you to take part in bilingua
 l conversation circles. This program offers an excellent opportunity to pr
 actice your English and/or French while encouraging discussion\, and netwo
 rking among participants.  Please note that spaces are limited and\nregi
 stration\nis required.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal infor
 mation on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the P
 ublic Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information 
 will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and evalua
 tion. Questions about how the library handles your information can be dire
 cted to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yong
 e Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.\nACCESSIBILITÉ\nLe sous-titrage en direct 
 ou automatique\, l’interprétation en langue des signes\, les services d
 ’intervenant\, ou les services d’accompagnement sont disponibles sur d
 emande. Veuillez soumettre votre demande au moins deux semaines à l’ava
 nce à : tpl.ca/accessibility-events
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Discussion Room\, 3rd floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/696ea6ba6724c63d00ed0aec
