BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Asian Heritage Month - Guzheng & Erhu 亚裔文化月古筝和二
 胡演奏
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260520T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260520T153000
UID:69b43598ad384e40edb41439@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Experience a dynamic 60‑minute presentation exploring the ri
 ch traditions of Chinese music through the guzheng and the erhu. Participa
 nts will learn about each instrument’s construction\, unique sound quali
 ties\, and historical development within Chinese musical culture. The prog
 ram also introduces key elements of traditional Chinese music\, including 
 melodic patterns\, tonal characteristics\, and folk‑influenced stylistic
  features. Solo and duet performances will showcase how these instruments 
 convey regional folk traditions and classical artistry. A 30‑minute Q&A 
 and discussion will follow.\nOur program will run approximately 60 minutes
  and is designed to be both educational and engaging for a broad library a
 udience. During the presentation\, we will introduce the construction and 
 unique characteristics of the guzheng and the erhu\, helping participants 
 understand how sound is produced and how each instrument developed within 
 Chinese musical history. We will also provide an accessible overview of fu
 ndamental elements of traditional Chinese music\, including common melodic
  patterns\, tonal characteristics\, and stylistic features found in Chines
 e folk music. Through both solo and duet performances\, the guzheng and er
 hu will demonstrate how traditional Chinese musical culture is expressed t
 hrough these instruments. The repertoire will include examples that highli
 ght regional folk influences as well as classical traditions. Following th
 e performance and workshop\, we will offer a 30-minute audience engagement
  session\, including discussion and a Q&A\, encouraging participants to as
 k questions and share reflections in an open and welcoming environment.\nW
 hat can participants expect to gain from this program?: Participants can e
 xpect to gain a deeper understanding of traditional Chinese music and its 
 cultural context. Through live demonstrations and guided explanations\, th
 ey will learn how the guzheng and erhu are constructed\, how they produce 
 sound\, and how musical expression is shaped by Chinese melodic and stylis
 tic traditions."​\n时间：5月20日下午2点\n地点：多伦多图
 书馆 Maria A. Shchuka Branch\, 1745 Eglinton Avenue West
LOCATION:Maria A. Shchuka\, the 1st floor Children's Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b43598ad384e40edb41439
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
