BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Peter Crighton: The Vinyl Diaries
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260611T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260611T200000
UID:69cd7d611e64afd01e6631f3@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:TPL presents author Pete Crighton in conversation at the Toron
 to Reference Library's Jack Rabinovitch Reading Room.\nIn his heartfelt me
 moir\nThe Vinyl Diaries: Sex\, Deep Cuts\, and My Soundtrack to Queer Joy\
 n\, Crighton chronicles what happened when\, in his 40s\, he finally decid
 ed to live his queer life to the fullest. But what makes this memoir sing 
 is how each new connection\, each lover\, is linked to an artist\, song\, 
 or album from his vast record collection. Kate Bush\, the B-52s\, Prince\,
  The Smiths\, Yoko Ono\, and Stevie Nicks provide an extraordinary soundtr
 ack to Crighton's mid-life sexual awakening.\nHow does music become the so
 undtrack to our most intimate moments? What role does it play in helping u
 s understand ourselves and connect with others? And what becomes possible 
 when we finally give ourselves permission to live fully—to embrace desir
 e\, take risks\, and claim the life we were always meant to have?\nJoin To
 ronto author Pete Crighton for a poignant\, funny\, and deeply personal co
 nversation about music\, memory\, and the journey to queer joy.\nQ&A and b
 ook signing to follow. Books available for purchase.\nAbout this event’s
  guests:\nPeter Crighton\nRead More:\nThe Vinyl Diaries\n***\nPLAN YOUR VI
 SIT:\nLocation:\nJack Rabinovitch Reading Room\, Toronto Reference Library
  (789 Yonge Street)\, 4th floor\nTime:\nDoors open 6:00pm\, Event starts 7
 :00pm.\nTickets:\nFree registration required.\nTicket policy:\nWe oversell
  these events to ensure that the greatest number of people have an opportu
 nity to attend. Tickets guaranteed until 6:45pm or until capacity is reach
 ed. Seating first come\, first served\nAccessibility:\nTPL is committed to
  accessibility. If you are Deaf or have a disability and would like to req
 uest accommodation for this event\, please contact accessibleservices@tpl.
 ca or 416-393-7099 at least three weeks prior to the event.\n***\nThis eve
 nt is part of our signature\nSalon Series\n\, where we host local and inte
 rnational authors\, artists and thinkers in conversation about their new b
 ooks and big ideas.\n***\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal inf
 ormation on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the
  Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The informatio
 n will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and eval
 uation. Registrants may be contacted to fill out a brief survey following 
 the program. Questions about how the library handles your information can 
 be directed to Answerline staff at answerline@tpl.ca\, 416-397-5981\, 789 
 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Jack Rabinovitch Reading Room\, Toron
 to Reference Library (789 Yonge Street)\, 4th floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69cd7d611e64afd01e6631f3
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
