DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260515T150000
UID:69b1c22e4a9fd98b7f839a75@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:TV host and celebrity chef Sang Kim will teach the basics of m
 aking Korean-style kimbap\, exactly like you see them on your favourite K-
 dramas. Participants will roll and cut kimbap using ingredients prepared b
 y the Chef and eat their own creations. A brief history of kimbap\, its di
 fferences from the Japanese sushi roll\, and eating etiquette will also be
  shared. Prizes are also awarded for best kimbap creations.\nNB: Ingredien
 ts include egg and fishcake (which participants do not have to use)\nInfor
 mation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is collec
 ted by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, section
 s 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for event a
 nd program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the
