SUMMARY:Youth Hub: DJ-ing 101
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T170000
UID:69c02ca567801235ed73ce46@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Oscar Betancourt aka ​'DJ Grouch' leads this DJ-ing fundame
 ntals workshop where participants will learn the key techniques behind mix
 ing/beatmatching\, scratching and backspinning/looping.\nFundamental techn
 iques taught during this workshop:\nCounting beats\nDropping beats on the 
 one\nStart and stop mixing technique\nBeatmatching by ear\nSyncing\nScratc
 hing Basics\nRecord Control\nCrossfader\nCatching the break\nThis program 
 is part of Youth Hub service. Youth Hubs are a welcoming place for teens a
 fter school and in the summer\, where helpful staff are always available.
  Free\, nutritious snacks are offered daily. Drop by a branch with a\nYo
 uth Hub\nor call the branch to find out more.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Youth Hub\, 1st Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c02ca567801235ed73ce46
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Our Fragile Planet: Create Your Own Nature Reserve – Right at Ho
 me!
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260530T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260530T153000
UID:69d528098ddc1caf5f1b500e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Imagine visiting your favourite park or conservation area – 
 where the sights\, sounds\, and magic of nature fill you with wonder\, pea
 ce and a sense of connection. Now imagine not having to fight traffic and 
 use polluting fuels to get there!\nIn this presentation\, learn how you ca
 n reimagine your current space to bring you that same refreshing and relax
 ing nature vibe at home. Explore the immense potential of natural spaces a
 t home that protect biodiversity and help to mitigate and adapt to climate
  change through careful plant choices\, design\, and maintenance.\nRegistr
 ation required. Please register online. Visit or call the branch if you ne
 ed help with registering.\nPresented by the\nDavid Suzuki Foundation's But
 terfly Rangers\n\, who are community leaders in teaching and inspiring peo
 ple to protect bees\, butterflies\, and wildflowers.\nThis program is part
  of TPL's\nOur Fragile Planet\nprogram series\, supported by Friends of To
 ronto Public Library\, South Chapter.\n​\nInformation Collection Notice:
 \nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public
  Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(
 d). The information will only be used for event and program registration\,
  delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your inf
 ormation can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416
 -397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Riverdale\, Program Room #1
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69d528098ddc1caf5f1b500e
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
