BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Spoken Word Series with Andrea Thompson Workshop 3: Poetry in Per
 formance (REGISTRATION FULL)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260514T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260514T200000
UID:698a3bde4a9fd98b7f7d0baa@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Workshop 1: The Craft of Poetry\nThursday April 30 - Jack Rab
 inovitch Reading Room - Participants will explore the fundamentals of crea
 ting well-crafted\, evocative poetry with the use of techniques like senso
 ry details\, extended metaphor\, figurative language\, sound devices and m
 ore.\nWorkshop 2: Finding Your Voice\nThursday May 7 - Jack Rabinovitch R
 eading Room - Participants will explore strategies to help develop their o
 wn unique poetic voice and write courageously about issues affecting their
  own individual daily lives.\nWorkshop 3: Poetry in Performance\nThursday 
 May 14 - Jack Rabinovitch Reading Room - Participants will focus on strate
 gies and techniques to create powerful poetry performances\, overcome stag
 e fright and bring their writing to life on the stage.\nWorkshop 4: Review
  and Rehearsal\nThursday May 21 - Beeton Hall - Participants will prepare 
 and rehearse for the final showcase event.\nThis program series is present
 ed by Andrea Thompson\, TPL’s Spring 2026 Writer in Residence whose focu
 s is Spoken Word Poetry for an Adult Audience. Learn more about TPL's\nWri
 ter in Residence\nprogram\, including upcoming programs and one-on-one con
 sultation sessions.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Workshops 1-3 will be in the Jack Rab
 inovitch Reading Room (fourth floor). Workshop 4 will be in Beeton Hall (f
 irst floor).
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698a3bde4a9fd98b7f7d0baa
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
