BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Maison des bébés
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T143000
UID:69b4555eb6c4ac1fedc58984@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Un programme spécialement conçu pour les bébés de 0 à 18 
 mois et leurs accompagnateurs.\nChanter des chansons et des comptines à v
 otre bébé favorise le développement du langage tout en partageant un mo
 ment amusant et chaleureux.\nLes comptines avec gestes encouragent égalem
 ent les tout‑petits à bouger et à explorer selon leur stade de dévelo
 ppement.\nCe programme est offert en partenariat avec le\nCentre francopho
 ne du Grand Toronto.\nAccessibilité:\nLe sous-titrage en direct ou automa
 tique\, l’interprétation en langue des signes\, les services\nd’inter
 venant\, ou les services d’accompagnement sont disponibles sur demande. 
 Veuillez\nsoumettre votre demande au moins deux semaines à l’avance à 
 : tpl.ca/accessibility-events\nA program specially designed for babies age
 d 0 to 18 months and their caregivers.\nSinging songs and rhymes to your b
 aby helps support language development while sharing a fun and warm moment
  together.\nAction rhymes also encourage little ones to move and explore a
 ccording to their developmental stage.\nThis program is offered in partner
 ship with the\nCentre francophone du Grand Toronto.
LOCATION:New Toronto
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b4555eb6c4ac1fedc58984
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wellness Recovery Action Plan (WRAP)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T130000
UID:696eca617d180d0d4830c45e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:WRAP is for\nanyone\nlooking to strengthen their well-being—
 whether you’re supporting your mental health\, managing stress\, or simp
 ly wanting to feel more balanced and resilient in daily life. Participant
 s will receive a\nWRAP certificate\nupon program completion.\nIn an 8-wee
 k WRAP group\, individuals explore:\nself-care tools like peer connections
 \, relaxation and mindfulness techniques\, stress reduction strategies\, a
 nd more\nresources for keeping well and feeling better in difficult times.
 \nThis WRAP Group meets\nevery Friday\,\nonce a week for 8 weeks\, March 2
 0-May 15\, 2026\, 10 am - 1 pm\n. There is no session on Friday April 3\, 
 2026 due to Good Friday. Registration closes after week 3\, or when full.
 \nTTC Presto tickets will be provided.\nSnacks and refreshments are provid
 ed for all participants. Ingredient lists will be available at the progra
 m.\nThis program is in collaboration with\nGerstein Crisis Centre's WRAP i
 nitiative\n. Gerstein Crisis Centre is solely responsible for the protecti
 on of \npersonal information collected through the program registration \n
 process.
LOCATION:Sanderson\, Basement Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/696eca617d180d0d4830c45e
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Excel Basics 2: Do More with your Data
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T153000
UID:69af04788d5e2d0933642358@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:An introductory class on Microsoft Excel for beginners with li
 ttle or no Excel experience. Build on your basic Microsoft Excel skills an
 d learn to use Excel data effectively.\nIn this second session\, you will:
 \nPractice data entry and formatting\nManipulate rows and columns\nCreate 
 and copy simple formulas\nConvert data to a Table then sort and filter\nCr
 eate your first chart\nUpon completion of this class\, you will be able to
  get more from your data using tables\, filters and charts.\nPrerequisites
 : Excel Basics Part 1 or equivalent knowledge. Basic mouse and keyboard sk
 ills required.\nFormat:  Hands-on with demonstrations\nPlease arrive a few
  minutes early.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information 
 on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public L
 ibraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will on
 ly be used for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Q
 uestions about how the library handles your information can be directed to
  Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Stree
 t\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Albert Campbell\, Learning Centre\, 2nd floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69af04788d5e2d0933642358
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
