BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Balancing Library Worker Safety with Community Needs
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T153000
UID:69ce81ea1e64afd01e666698@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:National Day of Mourning Event.  This year's theme is:\nLib
 rary Workers Responding to the Opioid Crisis in Public Spaces while Balanc
 ing Staff Safety with Community Needs.\nThe National Day of Mourning is an
 nually marked on April 28. It is dedicated to remembering those who have 
 lost their lives\, suffered injury or illness\, or experienced a tragedy d
 ue to work-related incidents. Additionally\, The National Day of Mourning 
 is a day to collectively renew our commitment to improve health and safety
  in the workplace and prevent further injuries\, illnesses and deaths.\nJo
 in Ray Clark\, Health Promoter with the Homelessness & Addiction Recovery 
 & Treatment (HART) Hub at Parkdale Queen West Community Health Centre. Ray
  will provide an informative talk to staff and members of the public on th
 e challenges from the ongoing opioid crisis is affecting frontline staff\,
  including library workers in supporting vulnerable community members.\nNo
  registration required. Drop in only.\nWednesday\, April 15 2:00-3:30 pm\n
 Toronto Reference Library\n789 Yonge Street\,\nBeeton Hall\nMain Floor\nEv
 ent Link
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Toronto Reference Library \n789 Yonge
  Street\, \nBeeton Hall\nMain Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69ce81ea1e64afd01e666698
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
