DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260509T153000
UID:69ce7fde129f127438361203@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Get ready to mix\, stretch\, and squish! Join us for a hands-o
 n slime-making program where participants will learn the basics of simple 
 science while creating their very own batch of space slime to take home. W
 e’ll explore textures\, colors\, and fun chemical reactions in a safe an
 d supervised environment. All materials will be provided—just bring your
  curiosity and be ready to get a little messy!\nThis program is for ages 6
  to 12 years old.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal informatio
 n on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public
  Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will 
 only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation.
  Questions about how the library handles your information can be directed 
