BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Pitch Showcase
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260516T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260516T153000
UID:69b8312623b45fff20f21d34@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Lily Akagbosu\, Newcomer Entrepreneur in Residence\nThe final 
 session celebrates the progress participants have made throughout the prog
 ram and provides an opportunity to share their entrepreneurial journey. Bu
 ilding a business takes courage\, persistence\, and community support\, an
 d this gathering is designed to recognize that effort.\nParticipants will 
 have the opportunity to present their business ideas\, showcase what they 
 have been working on\, and reflect on the insights they gained throughout 
 the program. The event will also include time for networking\, testimonial
 s\, and connecting with fellow entrepreneurs and community members. By the
  end of the evening\, participants will leave with greater confidence\, st
 ronger connections\, and renewed momentum to continue building their busin
 esses.\nFood and non-alcoholic refreshments will be provided. While we str
 ive to offer allergy-aware options for common dietary needs\, food is prep
 ared and served in shared facilities and we cannot guarantee an allergen-f
 ree environment.\nRegistration is required.\nThis program is part of Toron
 to Public Library’s\nNewcomer Entrepreneur in Residence\nprogram series 
 and\nNewcomer Entrepreneurship Initiative\n\, designed to support newcomer
 s as they explore entrepreneurship and build practical small business skil
 ls. Participants will learn about key topics for starting and growing a bu
 siness in Canada\, with guidance from an experienced entrepreneur in resid
 ence. For more information and a full list of programs\, visit\ntpl.ca/eir
 \n.\nLily Akagbos\nu\nis a Product Manager and entrepreneur with a Master
 ’s degree in Digital Product Management from Queen’s University. She h
 as shaped and delivered products at organizations including IBM\, Shopify\
 , and the Bank of Montreal. Beyond her product work\, she has built hands-
 on business experience through startup ventures\, commerce\, and consultin
 g. Over the years\, Lily has actively engaged in Canada’s entrepreneursh
 ip ecosystem through the University of Toronto’s Black Founders Network\
 , Venture for Canada\, ventureLAB\, and NEXT Canada. She supports entrepre
 neurs and aspiring business owners from idea through launch and growth\, a
 nd delivers talks on leadership and innovation.\nInformation Collection No
 tice:\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto P
 ublic Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, an
 d 20(d). The information will only be used for event and program registrat
 ion\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles you
 r information can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\
 , 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Deer Park\, Room 204
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b8312623b45fff20f21d34
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Understanding Funding\, Grants\, and Preparing to Pitch
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260505T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260505T200000
UID:69b8311f403a4e5652df544e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Lily Akagbosu\, Newcomer Entrepreneur in Residence\nMany entre
 preneurs wonder how to fund their ideas and what financial resources may b
 e available to support their growth. Understanding the different funding p
 athways can help founders make more informed decisions as their business d
 evelops.\nIn this session\, we’ll explore common funding options for ear
 ly-stage businesses\, including grants and other financial opportunities a
 vailable to entrepreneurs. Participants will also learn how to clearly com
 municate their business idea through a concise and compelling pitch. The s
 ession will feature a guest speaker with expertise in grants and funding o
 pportunities\, offering practical insights into how entrepreneurs can prep
 are when seeking financial support.\nRegistration is required.\nThis progr
 am is part of Toronto Public Library’s\nNewcomer Entrepreneur in Residen
 ce\nprogram series and\nNewcomer Entrepreneurship Initiative\n\, designed 
 to support newcomers as they explore entrepreneurship and build practical 
 small business skills. Participants will learn about key topics for starti
 ng and growing a business in Canada\, with guidance from an experienced en
 trepreneur in residence. For more information and a full list of programs\
 , visit\ntpl.ca/eir\n.\nLily Akagbos\nu\nis a Product Manager and entrepre
 neur with a Master’s degree in Digital Product Management from Queen’s
  University. She has shaped and delivered products at organizations includ
 ing IBM\, Shopify\, and the Bank of Montreal. Beyond her product work\, sh
 e has built hands-on business experience through startup ventures\, commer
 ce\, and consulting. Over the years\, Lily has actively engaged in Canada
 ’s entrepreneurship ecosystem through the University of Toronto’s Blac
 k Founders Network\, Venture for Canada\, ventureLAB\, and NEXT Canada. Sh
 e supports entrepreneurs and aspiring business owners from idea through la
 unch and growth\, and delivers talks on leadership and innovation.\nInform
 ation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is collect
 ed by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections
  20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for event an
 d program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the 
 library handles your information can be directed to Answerline staff at\na
 nswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Deer Park\, Room 204
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b8311f403a4e5652df544e
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
