SUMMARY:How to Attract Customers and Grow Your Business
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260425T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260425T120000
UID:69b83111576a13de310b58d8@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Lily Akagbosu\, Newcomer Entrepreneur in Residence\nA great id
 ea is only the beginning. For a business to succeed\, people need to disco
 ver it\, trust it\, and ultimately choose it. Understanding how to reach t
 he right audience and communicate your value clearly is essential for earl
 y growth.\nIn this session\, we’ll explore foundational strategies for a
 ttracting your first customers and building awareness around your business
 . Participants will learn how to identify their target audience\, craft cl
 ear messaging\, and choose practical channels to reach potential customers
 . By the end of the session\, you’ll walk away with simple and actionabl
 e approaches to begin growing your customer base.\nRegistration is require
 d.\nThis program is part of Toronto Public Library’s\nNewcomer Entrepren
 eur in Residence\nprogram series and\nNewcomer Entrepreneurship Initiative
 \n\, designed to support newcomers as they explore entrepreneurship and bu
 ild practical small business skills. Participants will learn about key top
 ics for starting and growing a business in Canada\, with guidance from an 
 experienced entrepreneur in residence. For more information and a full lis
 t of programs\, visit\ntpl.ca/eir\n.\nLily Akagbos\nu\nis a Product Manage
 r and entrepreneur with a Master’s degree in Digital Product Management 
 from Queen’s University. She has shaped and delivered products at organi
 zations including IBM\, Shopify\, and the Bank of Montreal. Beyond her pro
 duct work\, she has built hands-on business experience through startup ven
 tures\, commerce\, and consulting. Over the years\, Lily has actively enga
 ged in Canada’s entrepreneurship ecosystem through the University of Tor
 onto’s Black Founders Network\, Venture for Canada\, ventureLAB\, and NE
 XT Canada. She supports entrepreneurs and aspiring business owners from id
 ea through launch and growth\, and delivers talks on leadership and innova
 tion.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this fo
 rm is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries A
 ct\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used
  for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions a
 bout how the library handles your information can be directed to Answerlin
 e staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toront
 o ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Deer Park\, Room 204
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b83111576a13de310b58d8
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
