BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wellness Recovery Action Plan (WRAP)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260515T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260515T130000
UID:696eca617d180d0d4830c461@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:WRAP is for\nanyone\nlooking to strengthen their well-being—
 whether you’re supporting your mental health\, managing stress\, or simp
 ly wanting to feel more balanced and resilient in daily life. Participant
 s will receive a\nWRAP certificate\nupon program completion.\nIn an 8-wee
 k WRAP group\, individuals explore:\nself-care tools like peer connections
 \, relaxation and mindfulness techniques\, stress reduction strategies\, a
 nd more\nresources for keeping well and feeling better in difficult times.
 \nThis WRAP Group meets\nevery Friday\,\nonce a week for 8 weeks\, March 2
 0-May 15\, 2026\, 10 am - 1 pm\n. There is no session on Friday April 3\, 
 2026 due to Good Friday. Registration closes after week 3\, or when full.
 \nTTC Presto tickets will be provided.\nSnacks and refreshments are provid
 ed for all participants. Ingredient lists will be available at the progra
 m.\nThis program is in collaboration with\nGerstein Crisis Centre's WRAP i
 nitiative\n. Gerstein Crisis Centre is solely responsible for the protecti
 on of \npersonal information collected through the program registration \n
 process.
LOCATION:Sanderson\, Basement Program Room
