DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T143000
UID:69af4b15491b809c6f1f4c79@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:A monthly gathering designed to provide a supportive\, safe\, 
 and welcoming space for parents or caregivers raising children with disabi
 lities. Meetings will include open discussions as well as guest speakers\,
  including professionals and advocates\, to provide valuable insights on r
 elevant topics.\nWhether you're seeking support\, advice\, or simply a spa
 ce to share\, we welcome you to join us. Together we can navigate the chal
 lenges and celebrate the joys of parenting a child with a disability.\nFor
  this\nTenth session\, Jennifer Haynes\, Regional Service Network Speciali
 st at AccessOAP - Toronto Region\nwill be our guest speaker. Monthly Date
 s and Guest Speakers will be announced as they become confirmed.
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, Room 2/3\, 2nd Floor
