BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Google AI Essentials: In Person Learning Circle
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260428T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260428T150000
UID:69b16b746724c63d00f8192c@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Interested in learning about artificial intelligence (AI)? Let
 's learn the basics of AI in a welcoming space.\nWe will meet in person at
 \nLillian H. Smith Branch\non\nApril 7-April 28 from 1-3 pm\n.\nAI Essenti
 als Learning Circles are study groups guided by staff for people who want 
 to take the Google AI Essentials online course together in a welcoming spa
 ce. Learners meet weekly and work together through the course materials. P
 articipants are expected to commit to the duration of the course and atten
 d all learning circle sessions.\nGoogle AI Essentials is designed to help 
 people across roles and industries get essential AI skills to boost their 
 productivity. Zero experience is required.\nAt each session\, you'll discu
 ss the content of the course\, have time to catch up on the course work\, 
 and learn about related library resources.\nGoogle AI Essentials consists 
 of 5 sections and takes approximately 10 hours to complete:\nIntroduction 
 to AI - Learn about foundational concepts such as machine learning and gen
 erative AI.\nMaximize productivity with AI tools - Learn how to use genera
 tive AI tools to increase productivity in completing work tasks.\nDiscover
  the art of prompting - Learn how to write effective prompts to get better
  outputs using AI tools.\nUse AI responsibly - Learn how to lessen harmful
  biases and inaccuracies. Recognize the security risks of using AI in the 
 workplace.\nStay Ahead of the AI Curve - Learn how to stay up-to-date with
  the latest AI news.\nAccess to the course and certification are provided 
 at no cost to individuals who participate in the learning circle.\nLearner
 s who complete the course will be able to:\nearn a certificate to be share
 d on LinkedIn and social media profiles\ndownload a certificate of complet
 ion\nThe registration process is a two-step procedure. First\, participant
 s must complete their registration through this page. After this step\, li
 brary staff will follow up to request additional information in order to c
 omplete the registration.\nParticipants must have a valid Toronto Public L
 ibrary card to register.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal inf
 ormation on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the
  Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The informatio
 n will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and eval
 uation. Questions about how the library handles your information can be di
 rected to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yo
 nge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8
LOCATION:Lillian H. Smith\, Room B/C (basement)
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b16b746724c63d00f8192c
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
