SUMMARY:Fashion for the Planet: Conscious Consumption
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260422T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260422T200000
UID:6984d60d4dacf581ff794829@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:With the rise of fast fashion brands and social media fueled c
 onsumption habits\, the fashion industry ranks as the 3rd most environment
 ally damaging industry. Everyone participates in this in some way\, so it 
 is important that people are given the information and tools to consume cl
 othing responsibly.\nThis session explores Conscious Consumption - Join S
 abrina Rose Capista as she guides us through the fashion industry's impac
 ts & ethics. Discuss consumption habits and update your shopping literacy
 with tips for spotting greenwashing & conscious shopping.\nPresented on Ea
 rth Day\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this 
 form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries
  Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be us
 ed for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions
  about how the library handles your information can be directed to Answerl
 ine staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toro
 nto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Don Mills\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6984d60d4dacf581ff794829
