BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Create Pop Music with AI Tools
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260422T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260422T180000
UID:69a2000b8089f23c675eaf39@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Have you ever had a melody stuck in your head and wished you c
 ould turn it into a real song? AI tools are making it easier than ever to 
 bring your musical experiences to life - but how do you make sure the musi
 c you create is truly yours?\nExplore how to use AI as a creative assistan
 t to build radio-ready pop tracks based on your own original ideas. You'll
  learn how to guide AI tools to serve your vision rather than replace it\,
  and we'll cover Canadian copyright guidelines to ensure the music you mak
 e qualifies as your own intellectual property. No prior music or programm
 ing experience is required.\nRegistration is required.\nThis program is pa
 rt of the Innovator in Residence (AI and Music Production) program\, which
  is designed to help beginner and intermediate learners build knowledge an
 d creative skills and get hands-on with current AI tools in music producti
 on and learn about the history\, copyright and ethics of generative music.
  For more information and a full list of programs\, visit tpl.ca/airesiden
 t.
LOCATION:Fairview\, Digital Innovation Hub\, 3rd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a2000b8089f23c675eaf39
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
