DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260507T110000
UID:69c837b21e64afd01e65536d@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Have you heard of phenology? It is the study of cycles of natu
 ral events\, changes in climate\, including the seasons. What is the natu
 ral world doing right now in Toronto and what does it signal? We'll explor
 e the concept of wildlife as guides and how they can teach us about our o
 wn behaviour. The world is a teacher and we are its students.\nPlease regi
 ster online.\nPresented by\nClementina Consens\n\, TPL's Spring 2026\nEnvi
 ronmentalist in Residence.\nThe Environmentalist in Residence\nis part of 
 TPL's\nOur Fragile Planet\nprogram series\, supported by Friends of Toront
 o Public Library\, South Chapter.​\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe 
 personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Libra
 ry under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). Th
 e information will only be used for event and program registration\, deliv
 ery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your informati
 on can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5
 981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Malvern\, Community Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c837b21e64afd01e65536d
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
