BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Generate Film Scores with AI Tools
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260508T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260508T160000
UID:69a201684dacf581ff7e66db@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Think about the last time a movie made your heart race or brou
 ght you to tears. Chances are\, the music had a lot to do with it. Film sc
 oring is the art of using music to shape how an audience feels\, and AI to
 ols are opening up this craft to anyone with a story to tell.\nIn this ses
 sion\, you'll learn what makes a film score effective\, from recurring mus
 ical themes to choosing the right instruments and timing music to match wh
 at's happening on screen. Then you'll put it all into practice by using AI
  tools to compose an original score for a short film. No prior music or fi
 lm experience is required.\nThis program is part of the Innovator in Resid
 ence (AI and Music Production) program\, which is designed to help beginne
 r and intermediate learners build knowledge and creative skills and get ha
 nds-on with current AI tools in music production and learn about the histo
 ry\, copyright and ethics of generative music. For more information and a 
 full list of programs\, visit\ntpl.ca/airesident\n.
