BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:NatureTO: Trees Around the Branch Tour
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260605T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260605T153000
UID:69b175fc8089f23c676153f8@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:The Hillcrest Library and its neighbourhood is home to a vari
 ety of trees. Join the City of Toronto Urban Forestry staff to explore the
  natural world on a local neighbourhood tour. Learn how to recognize diffe
 rent species and fun facts about their cultural and ecological importance.
 \nChildren under 12 must be accompanied by a parent/caregiver.\nRegistrati
 on is required.\nThe tour will start and end at the Hillcrest Library and 
 will be guided by the City of Toronto Urban Forestry staff. There may be u
 neven\, unpaved surfaces along the route. Please dress and prepare accordi
 ngly for this outdoor program (e.g. gloves/mittens\, hats\, sunscreen\, wa
 ter\, comfortable shoes). This program takes place rain or shine. In the e
 vent of severe inclement weather\, registrants will be notified of an alte
 rnative date.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on
  this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Lib
 raries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only
  be used for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Que
 stions about how the library handles your information can be directed to A
 nswerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\
 , Toronto ON M4W 2G8.\nThis program is part of TPL's\nOur Fragile Planet\n
 program series\, supported by Friends of Toronto Public Library\, South Ch
 apter.​
LOCATION:Hillcrest\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b175fc8089f23c676153f8
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mimico Book Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T120000
UID:69ac35f1ec71a31f5b423fed@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Our book selection for April is A Spell of Good Things by Ayob
 ami Adebayo\, the Booker Prize-nominated novel about modern-day Nigeria. I
 t is a story about the class and political divisions that take over the li
 ves of two families\, one rich\, one poor\, with tragic consequences. It a
 lso provides a glimpse into the importance attached to education in countr
 ies struggling with systemic poverty.\nCopies available at the branch.\nA 
 Spell of Good Things
LOCATION:Mimico Centennial\, Meeting Room
