BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Freestyle Socials: Is This Supposed to be Funny?
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260427T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260427T190000
UID:69cd1e949057005337d1ba2b@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:You've probably noticed that everything is a little… tense r
 ight now. Politics are unhinged. Group chats are landmines. Someone you lo
 ve just sent a "thoughtful" meme that ruined your entire morning. Conversa
 tions where the only goal is winning are ruining the world. We've forgotte
 n how to disagree without triggering each other in the process.\nWhat happ
 ened to having a little fun? After all\, a well-timed joke can still save 
 the night. What gives?\nThis is not your typical library event. This is a 
 playful and fun evening that encourages participation\, conversation and l
 aughter!\nHow to Play\n: The host asks a question. You pick a side. Then e
 veryone shares ideas about why the other side should switch. No winners\, 
 no losers\, just better conversations in three easy steps: Disagree. Laugh
 . Repeat!\nExpect a slightly unhinged\, but secretly very smart and fun ex
 ploration of why we laugh\, when we shouldn't\, and why that might actuall
 y be the point. Because it turns out humor isn't just entertainment—it's
  social glue. Awkwardness isn't failure—it's fertile ground. And "too so
 on?" is sometimes exactly on time.\nAbout Freestyle Socials\n: In a world 
 where conversations focused on winning are tearing us apart\, this game re
 minds us we can laugh\, learn and connect instead with one simple rule: sw
 itch sides if you’re surprised or laughing.\n***\nThis event is part of 
 our signature\nSalon Series\n\, where we host local and international auth
 ors\, artists and thinkers in conversation about their new books and big i
 deas.\nThis event is generously supported by McConnell Foundation.\n***\nP
 LAN YOUR VISIT\n:\nLocation:\nNovella Room\, Toronto Reference Library (78
 9 Yonge Street)\, 2nd floor\, inside the Bram and Bluma Appel Salon\nTime:
 \nDoors open 5:30 PM\, Event starts 6:00 PM.\nTickets:\nFree registration 
 required.\nTicket policy:\nWe oversell these events to make sure that most
  people have an opportunity to attend. Tickets are guaranteed until 5:45pm
  or until capacity is reached. Any remaining space will be opened up to th
 e rush line beginning at 5:45pm.\nFilming Notification: You may be photogr
 aphed or filmed during this program.\nTPL is committed to accessibility. I
 f you are Deaf or have a disability and would like to request accommodatio
 n for this event\, please contact accessibleservices@tpl.ca or 416-393-709
 9 at least three weeks prior to the event.\n***\nInformation Collection No
 tice:\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto P
 ublic Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, an
 d 20(d). The information will only be used for event and program registrat
 ion\, delivery and evaluation.\nRegistrants may be contacted to fill out a
  brief survey following the program\n. Questions about how the library han
 dles your information can be directed to Answerline staff at answerline@tp
 l.ca\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Novella Room\, Toronto Reference Libr
 ary (789 Yonge Street)\, 2nd floor\, inside the Bram and Bluma Appel Salon
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69cd1e949057005337d1ba2b
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Google AI Essentials: Online Learning Circle
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T200000
UID:69b16c096724c63d00f81934@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Interested in learning about artificial intelligence (AI)? Let
 's learn the basics of AI in a welcoming space.\nWe will meet online via Z
 oom on\nApril 9- April 30\, 2026 from 6-8pm.\nAI Essentials Learning Circl
 es are study groups guided by staff for people who want to take the Google
  AI Essentials online course together in a welcoming space. Learners meet 
 weekly and work together through the course materials. Participants are ex
 pected to commit to the duration of the course and attend all learning cir
 cle sessions.\nGoogle AI Essentials is designed to help people across role
 s and industries get essential AI skills to boost their productivity. Zero
  experience is required.\nAt each session\, you'll discuss the content of 
 the course\, have time to catch up on the course work\, and learn about re
 lated library resources.\nGoogle AI Essentials consists of 5 sections and 
 takes approximately 10 hours to complete:\nIntroduction to AI - Learn abou
 t foundational concepts such as machine learning and generative AI.\nMaxim
 ize productivity with AI tools - Learn how to use generative AI tools to i
 ncrease productivity in completing work tasks.\nDiscover the art of prompt
 ing - Learn how to write effective prompts to get better outputs using AI 
 tools.\nUse AI responsibly - Learn how to lessen harmful biases and inaccu
 racies. Recognize the security risks of using AI in the workplace.\nStay A
 head of the AI Curve - Learn how to stay up-to-date with the latest AI new
 s.\nAccess to the course and certification are provided at no cost to indi
 viduals who participate in the learning circle.\nLearners who complete the
  course will be able to:\nearn a certificate to be shared on LinkedIn and 
 social media profiles\ndownload a certificate of completion\nThe registrat
 ion process is a two-step procedure. First\, participants must complete th
 eir registration through this page. After this step\, library staff will f
 ollow up to request additional information in order to complete the regist
 ration.\nParticipants must have a valid Toronto Public Library card to reg
 ister.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this f
 orm is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries 
 Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be use
 d for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions 
 about how the library handles your information can be directed to Answerli
 ne staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toron
 to ON M4W 2G8.
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b16c096724c63d00f81934
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
