SUMMARY:Death Café - Open Conversation About Death
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260605T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260605T200000
UID:69b4516db48451fc3c08af2f@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:At a Death Cafe people\, often strangers\, gather to eat sweet
 s and drink tea or coffee and discuss death. Join us for a welcoming discu
 ssion group where people gather to talk openly about death. This is not a 
 grief support or counselling session\, but a space for meaningful\, though
 tful conversations that many participants find surprisingly profound.\nHos
 ted by Jacqueline\;\nShe is passionate about creating spaces for honest co
 nversations about end-of-life awareness. With 20+ years of experience as a
 n Educator\, Holistic Coach\, and Reiki Master\, she supports individuals 
 and families in approaching end-of-life preparation with awareness\, compa
 ssion\, and grace.\nRegistration is welcome but optional.
LOCATION:S. Walter Stewart\, Meeting Room
