BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:3D Design with TinkerCad
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260420T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260420T170000
UID:69ceb6b1491b809c6f24b732@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:TinkerCad is a web browser based 3D application. Through the c
 reation of simple everyday objects students will learn the tools for objec
 t based 3D Design. In this class we will explore the basics of TinkerCad a
 nd you will get a chance to create your very own keychain! Suitable for ag
 es 8 and up.\nBasic computer and mouse skills require.\nPlease arrive on t
 ime for all programs\n. If you are more than 5 minutes late\, your spot wi
 ll be forfeited.
LOCATION:Albion\, Digital Innovation Hub
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69ceb6b1491b809c6f24b732
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Animation with Piskel for Kids
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260505T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260505T170000
UID:69cd268b213814b1b522a063@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Kids will learn how to make a simple pixel animation using the
  online Piskel app. Piskel can be used to create simple game sprites (i.e.
 \, 2D images overlaid onto a scene)\, GIF animations\, and pixel-art for s
 ocial media.\nThis program was design for children ages 8 and up.\nRegistr
 ation is required.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal informati
 on on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Publi
 c Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will
  only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation
 . Questions about how the library handles your information can be directed
  to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge St
 reet\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Leaside\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69cd268b213814b1b522a063
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
