BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:After School Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T170000
UID:695fe14e4a9fd98b7f765ea0@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Looking for something to do after school? Come out to our Afte
 r School Club and learn new things\, make stuff\, meet other kids and have
  fun!\nFor ages 6-12.\nRegistration is required.\nSnacks are offered durin
 g the After School Club for participants\, beginning at 3:45pm. Ingredient
  lists will be available. Snacks are generously supported\, in part\, by d
 onors.\nUpcoming Topics:\nMarch 6: Dash Robotics\nMarch 13: Collage Poste
 rs\nMarch 27: Games\nApril 10: Sphero Robotics\nApril 17: Planting Seeds
 \nApril 24: Snap Circuits\nMay 1: Crafts\nMay 8: Dash Robotics\nMay 15: 
 Beaded Wire Dragonflies\nMay 22: Marbled Paper\nMay 29: Sphero Robotics\nJ
 une 12: Melt Beads\nJune 19: After School Club Party\nInformation Collecti
 on Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toro
 nto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)
 \, and 20(d). The information will only be used for event and program regi
 stration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handle
 s your information can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.
 ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Gerrard/Ashdale
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/695fe14e4a9fd98b7f765ea0
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wellness Recovery Action Plan (WRAP)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260509T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260509T130000
UID:6968336576261f280064762f@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:WRAP is for\nanyone\nlooking to strengthen their well-being—
 whether you’re supporting your mental health\, managing stress\, or simp
 ly wanting to feel more balanced and resilient in daily life. Participant
 s will receive a\nWRAP certificate\nupon program completion.\nIn an 8-wee
 k WRAP group\, individuals explore:\nself-care tools like peer connections
 \, relaxation and mindfulness techniques\, stress reduction strategies\, a
 nd more\nresources for keeping well and feeling better in difficult times.
 \nInterested in learning more? Drop in for the information session on\nSat
 urday April 11 at 10am.\nThis WRAP Group meets\nevery Saturday\,\nonce a w
 eek for 8 weeks\, April 18-June 6\, 2026\, 10am - 1pm\n. Registration clos
 es after week 3\, or when full.\nTTC Presto tickets will be provided.\nSna
 cks and refreshments are provided for all participants. Ingredient lists w
 ill be available at the program.\nThis program is in collaboration with\n
 Gerstein Crisis Centre's WRAP initiative\n. Gerstein Crisis Centre is sole
 ly responsible for the protection of \npersonal information collected thro
 ugh the program registration \nprocess.
LOCATION:Northern District\, Room 200
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6968336576261f280064762f
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
