BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Loops\, Swoops and Curlicues Exhibition Tour
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T153000
UID:6967f4954a9fd98b7f779e55@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:How well can you read handwritten items? This free guided tour
  of\nLoops\, Swoops and Curlicues: A legacy of handwritten history\nwill l
 ead your through hundreds of years of handwritten items from TPL Special C
 ollections.\nCome test your decoding skills as we explore several hundred 
 years of handwritten words.\nRegistration is encouraged\, but not required
 . There is space for drop-in guests. Please meet at the entrance to the TD
  Gallery.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on thi
 s form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Librari
 es Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be 
 used for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questio
 ns about how the library handles your information can be directed to Answe
 rline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, To
 ronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, TD Gallery\, First Floor of Toronto R
 eference Library
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6967f4954a9fd98b7f779e55
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Macaulay Family Drop-In
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260507T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260507T160000
UID:69aef20d491b809c6f1f216b@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join the Macaulay Child Development Centre Wednesday mornings 
 and Thursday afternoons for Play & Learn! This weekly program is for paren
 ts\, caregivers and their children (ages 0-6) to socialize with others in 
 an interactive learning environment. Children will learn\, explore\, commu
 nicate and understand new concepts to help expand their knowledge through 
 play-based and guided activities. Expect a story time from Annette Street
  Library staff on the first Wednesday and the last Thursday of each month!
LOCATION:Annette Street\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69aef20d491b809c6f1f216b
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
