BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Festival Select: Wendy and Lucy (Kelly Reichardt\, 2008)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260525T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260525T203000
UID:698fa2e794297d3600ac23e5@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join the Society and Recreation department of the North York C
 entral Library for monthly screenings of fiction and non-fiction films tha
 t push the boundaries of the medium. This month we are showing Kelly Reich
 ardt's\nWendy and Lucy\n(2008).\nSynopsis (Criterion Pictures): Proving w
 hy she is one of the most highly-regarded auteurs of current cinema\, Kell
 y Reichardt's (OLD JOY) subtle storytelling technique uses a formal minima
 list style to weave together a unique emotional and political road film. W
 endy Carroll (Michelle Williams) is driving to Ketchikan\, Alaska\, in hop
 es of a summer of lucrative work at the Northwestern Fish cannery\, and th
 e start of a new life with her dog\, Lucy. When her car breaks down in Ore
 gon\, however\, the thin fabric of her financial situation comes apart\, a
 nd she confronts a series of increasingly dire economic decisions\, with f
 ar-ranging repercussions for herself and Lucy. WENDY AND LUCY addresses is
 sues of sympathy and generosity at the edges of American life\, revealing 
 the limits and depths of people's duty to each other in tough times. Based
  on the short story "TRAIN CHOIR" by Jon Raymond.\nNo registration require
 d.
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, Room 101
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698fa2e794297d3600ac23e5
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
