BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Branch Art Exhibit: Fragmented by Kaira Bergstra
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260402T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T235959
UID:69b0a9e1cbf6405d3569fb23@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Throughout the month of April\, works by artist Kaira Bergstra
  are on display at Agincourt Branch in an exhibit titled Fragmented.\nKai
 ra Ol’ga Bergstra is an emerging artist whose work explores memory and i
 dentity\, loss and comfort. After stepping away from a career in IT severa
 l years ago\, she wrote a memoir about her Soviet childhood and emigration
  to Canada. In visual art\, she found new freedom of self-expression that 
 transcends words and languages. Kaira has lived in Moscow\, Toronto\, Mont
 real\, Kitchener\, and Boston. She is now settled in midtown Toronto with 
 her husband and two children.\n"When my inner world felt fragmented\, art 
 allowed me to create tangible homes outside myself for my memories\, feeli
 ngs\, and questions. Art gave me a safe space to reflect\, and others join
 ed me\, bringing their own interpretations and meaning to my work. I work 
 primarily in acrylic\, exploring a variety of subjects that reflect the sp
 heres of personal experience — from street views and nature\, to objects
  of home and comfort\, to inner states of mind. I hope my work brings view
 ers into a space of reflection and reconnection\, offering them warmth and
  company along their own journeys."\nThis exhibit is part of TPL's\nArt Ex
 hibits Space\nprogram. Toronto Public Library provides space for local art
 ists to exhibit their work at locations across the city. These exhibits ai
 m to reflect the diverse cultural interests of the city and its neighbourh
 oods.\nThe exhibit can be viewed during\nAgincourt\nbranch open hours.\nFr
 ee. All are welcome.\nImage credit: Kaira Bergstra\; acrylic\; 11x14\; Mos
 cow #3
LOCATION:Agincourt\, First floor hallway towards Children's Department
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b0a9e1cbf6405d3569fb23
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Kimbap Making for Teens
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T161500
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T171500
UID:69cbe0039057005337d183df@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:TV host and celebrity chef Sang Kim will teach the basics of m
 aking\nKorean-style kimbap\n\, exactly like you see them on your favourite
  K-dramas. Participants will roll and cut kimbap using ingredients prepare
 d by the Chef and eat their own creations. A brief history of kimbap\, its
  differences from the Japanese sushi roll\, and eating etiquette will also
  be shared. Prizes are also awarded for best kimbap creations.\nPlease not
 e: Ingredients include egg and fishcake (which participants do not have t
 o use). This event is for teenagers aged 13-17.
LOCATION:Forest Hill\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69cbe0039057005337d183df
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
