DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260608T200000
UID:6990bdcf94297d3600ac468a@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Each month we will explore and discuss a title that falls into
  one of the TPL Reading Challenge categories.\nThis month we will be discu
 ssing\nHarlem Shuffle\nby Colson Whitehead\nCategory Is – 1960-1969\nFro
 m two-time Pulitzer Prize-winning author Colson Whitehead\, a gloriously e
 ntertaining novel of heists\, shakedowns and rip-offs set in Harlem . Harl
 em Shuffle is driven by an ingeniously intricate plot that plays out in a 
 beautifully recreated Harlem of the early 1960s.\nInformation Collection N
 otice:\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto 
 Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, a
 nd 20(d). The information will only be used for event and program registra
 tion\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles yo
 ur information can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n
 \, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Spadina Road\, Center of branch\, at Canoe Table
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6990bdcf94297d3600ac468a
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
