SUMMARY:Digital Life Skills for Seniors: Using a Cell Phone
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260529T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260529T153000
UID:69ab3f9d4a9fd98b7f829a8e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:For people who are new to cell phones and want a basic underst
 anding of how to use them.  No previous experience is required.  In this
  course we will look at :\n-The parts of a cell phone\n-Safety tips for us
 ing your phone\n-Skills such as turning off your ringtone\, taking a pictu
 re\, sending a text\, and downloading an app\nResource handout provided.\n
 Information Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is c
 ollected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, se
 ctions 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for ev
 ent and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about ho
 w the library handles your information can be directed to Answerline staff
  at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4
 W 2G8.\nAccessibility\nLive or automated closed captioning\, sign language
  interpretation\, intervenor services\, or attendant services are availabl
 e upon request. Please submit your request at least 2 weeks in advance to:
 \ntpl.ca/accessibility-events\n.
LOCATION:S. Walter Stewart\, Learning Centre
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69ab3f9d4a9fd98b7f829a8e
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Optimistic Writing Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T153000
UID:699f4eaa8d5e2d0933619579@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Writing is an excellent way to change our perception of certai
 n moments in our life\, a way to transform them into supporting elements. 
 Optimistic writing is an autobiographical mode of writing\, leading us to 
 focus more on all the little happy events of our daily life\, even the lea
 st perceptible ones.\nThe goal is not to learn how to write in a specific 
 literary style\, but to learn how to shift our gaze away from our problems
  and to get used to approaching life with gratitude.\nPutting the words on
  the paper allows us to better anchor positive emotions in our body. Then 
 follows a moment of sharing with the group\, because happiness is amplifie
 d when it is shared.\nThis workshop helps develop:\nSelf confidence\nImagi
 nation and creativity\nA better perception of our life and our environment
 \nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is
  collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, 
 sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for 
 event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about 
 how the library handles your information can be directed to Answerline sta
 ff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON 
 M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Richview\, Room A\, 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699f4eaa8d5e2d0933619579
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
