BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:NatureTO: Managing Invasive Plants Around Your Home
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T113000
UID:69a0742781b67dfe32a90c3a@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join the\nCity of Toronto Urban Forestry team\nfor a presentat
 ion on invasive plants commonly found around homes in Toronto. Learn how t
 o identify these species\, understand their impact\, and how to manage the
 m. You’ll also get tips on supporting local biodiversity through enhanci
 ng native habitats. Perfect for gardeners\, homeowners\, and anyone intere
 sted in urban ecology.\nFree program for Adults. No registration required.
  For more information\, please contact the branch.\nPresented as part of T
 PL’s environmental program series\, Our Fragile Planet. The series is ge
 nerously supported by Friends of Toronto Public Library\, South Chapter.
LOCATION:Jane/Sheppard
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a0742781b67dfe32a90c3a
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
