SUMMARY:Creative Writing Workshop Group
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260528T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260528T190000
UID:698e2cd47d180d0d48336acb@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Are you a new or experienced writer hoping to have your short 
 stories read and discussed? Lillian H. Smith’s Creative Writing Group is
  just for you!\nWe accept short stories (1000 Words max) of any genre and 
 meet twice a month!\nThe first meeting of each month features a writing ca
 fé\, where we write together and discuss new ideas for stories.\nThen\, m
 embers submit their stories – digitally or physically – to our group L
 ead\, and they will distribute all stories to each member.\nThe second mee
 ting hosts our workshop\, where we arrive ready to discuss the merits of e
 ach piece. It’s a great way to have your stories read and reviewed!\nReg
 istration required — Sign up at TPL.ca\, or with staff now!\nAt Lillian 
 H. Smith Branch (239 College Street)\, First Floor\, Program Room B/C.
LOCATION:Lillian H. Smith\, First Floor\, Program Room B/C
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698e2cd47d180d0d48336acb
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
