BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Investing 101: What You Need to Know
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260526T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260526T200000
UID:69d96885bd9a3c316a522798@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:It’s never too early (or too late) to learn how to invest yo
 ur money!\nLearn the basics of starting an investment portfolio from an in
 dustry expert.\nWhether you are starting out or learning more about your c
 urrent investments\, this seminar will help you make sense of the complex 
 world of investing. We will cover the three asset classes: stocks\, bonds\
 , and cash plus simple ways to get started with investing. In this easy-to
 -understand seminar\, Teri will set out the advantages of each of the thre
 e major tax-sheltered investing plans for Canadians: Tax-Free Savings Acco
 unts (TFSAs)\, Registered Retirement Savings Plans (RRSPs) and the new Fir
 st Home Savings Accounts (FHSAs).\nPresented by\nTeri Courchene\n\, BA\, M
 A\, MEd\, CSC. Teri is a former investing instructor at U of T School of C
 ontinuing Studies and former director of economic research at a major bank
 . One of her current volunteer roles is giving investing and finance talks
  at Toronto Public Library branches.\nRegistration is encouraged\n. Drop-i
 ns welcome until capacity is reached.
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, Room2/3
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69d96885bd9a3c316a522798
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
