DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260608T150000
UID:695c1281992fc18a86dbb2c9@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This\n program helps people stay active\, make friends\, learn
  new skills\, and \nhave fun. It involves peer-led group activities which 
 can include crafts\, games\,\n walking\, yoga\, and more. Meet new folks\
 , build social connections\, and tell us\n about programs and services you
  would like to see in the neighbourhood!\nMondays\, 1-3pm at Spadina Road.
 \nSnacks and refreshments are provided for all participants. Ingredient li
 sts will be available at the program.\nThis program is in collaboration w
 ith\nGerstein Crisis Centre's F.R.E.S.H. initiative\n.
LOCATION:Spadina Road\, Canoe Table at center of branch
