BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Positive Parenting: A Workshop for Parents/Caregivers
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T120000
UID:69c1c15a8d5e2d0933673027@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a Toronto Public Health workshop on Positive Paren
 ting.\nThis workshop will provide an overview about positive parenting and
  review tips on specific ways parents/caregivers can help guide their chil
 dren's behaviours. Topics covered include: temperament\, why children misb
 ehave\, and positive parenting strategies that can be used to reduce diffi
 cult behaviours.\n11:00-11:20\nDrop-in Friday Family Time (stories and son
 gs)\n11:20-11:50 Toronto Public Health Workshop\nChildren are welcome to s
 tay and play or make a craft in the same room during the workshop. Library
  staff will be present to engage with the children.\nPlease register\nfor 
 the workshop so we may plan accordingly.\nThis workshop is the first in a 
 series of three workshops offered by Toronto Public Health.\nFriday March 
 23\, 2026: Positive Parenting\nFriday May 15\, 2026: Food and Mood\nFrida
 y June 12\, 2026: Managing Stress in Children\nInformation Collection Noti
 ce: The personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Publ
 ic Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 2
 0(d). The information will only be used for event and program registration
 \, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your i
 nformation can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 4
 16-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Gerrard/Ashdale\, 2nd Floor Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c1c15a8d5e2d0933673027
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
