SUMMARY:Branch Art Exhibit: Family Ties by Rona Fleising
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260402T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T235959
UID:69b823748d5e2d093365965e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Throughout the month of April\, the works of artist Rona Fleis
 ing are on display at the Yorkville Branch in an exhibit titled Family Ti
 es.\nRona is a folk artist crafting whimsical portraits from retired men's
  ties\, vintage buttons\, and reclaimed notions. She began her studies in 
 Montreal at university followed by studio work in NYC. In Calgary\, she w
 as an education officer at the Glenbow Museum\, tour guide for Arts & Cult
 ure\, freelance art consultant\, and advisor to the mayor's office on publ
 ic art. Now she lives in Toronto where she is pursuing her goal of an exh
 ibition in her golden years.\n"Family Ties refers to the bonds between fam
 ily members which can include emotional connections and practical support.
  Rona breathes new life and purpose into her collection of ties\, buttons
 \, and notions donated by family and friends. Graphic design training insp
 ires her to integrate the colours and patterns of each tie with decorativ
 e elements to develop unique persona. She approaches art as serious fun\, 
 incorporating hand-sewing with visual literacy and a measure of wit."\nTh
 is exhibit is part of TPL's\nArt Exhibits Space\nprogram. Toronto Public L
 ibrary provides space for local artists to exhibit their work at locations
  across the city. These exhibits aim to reflect the diverse cultural inter
 ests of the city and its neighbourhoods.\nThe exhibit can be viewed during
 \nYorkville\nbranch open hours.\nFree. All are welcome.\nImage credit: Art
 ist: Rona Fleising\; Eilish
LOCATION:Yorkville
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b823748d5e2d093365965e
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
