DESCRIPTION:This program helps people stay active\, make friends\, learn n
 ew skills\, and have fun. Meet new folks\, build connections\, and tell us
  about programs and services you would like to see in the neighbourhood!\n
 Come and join the F.R.E.S.H. group for a Saturday screening of popular mov
 ies.\nWe'll be playing the following films\nSaturday\, April 4 –The Apar
 tment\nSaturday\, April 11 – The Color Purple (1985)\nSaturday\, April 1
 8 – Forrest Gump\nSaturday\, April 25 – The Bridge on the River Kwai\n
 Drop in\, no registration is required.\nSnacks and refreshments are provid
 ed for all participants. Ingredient lists will be available at the program
 .\nThis program is in collaboration with\nGerstein Crisis Centre's F.R.E.S
 .H. initiative\n.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, First floor\, Activity Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6931f2a276261f28005d7d4f
