BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wellness Recovery Action Plan (WRAP)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260523T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260523T160000
UID:696a62b9b0595799c096bc3a@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:WRAP is for\nanyone\nlooking to strengthen their well-being—
 whether you’re supporting your mental health\, managing stress\, or simp
 ly wanting to feel more balanced and resilient in daily life. Participant
 s will receive a\nWRAP certificate\nupon program completion.\nIn an 8-wee
 k WRAP group\, individuals explore:\nself-care tools like peer connections
 \, relaxation and mindfulness techniques\, stress reduction strategies\, a
 nd more\nresources for keeping well and feeling better in difficult times.
 \nInterested in learning more? Drop in for the\ninformation session\non\nS
 aturday\, May 16\, 2026 from 1:00pm-3:00pm.\nThis WRAP Group meets\nevery 
 Saturday\, once a week for 8 weeks\, May 23 - July 11\, 2026\, 1:00-4:00
 pm\n. Registration closes after week 3\, or when full.\nTTC Presto tickets
  will be provided.\nSnacks and refreshments are provided for all participa
 nts. Ingredient lists will be available at the program.\nThis program is 
 in collaboration with\nGerstein Crisis Centre's WRAP initiative\n. Gerstei
 n Crisis Centre is solely responsible for the protection of \npersonal inf
 ormation collected through the program registration \nprocess.
LOCATION:Fort York\, Program Room\, Main Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/696a62b9b0595799c096bc3a
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
