DESCRIPTION:Join our book club for engaging discussions\, new book recomme
 ndations\, and a fun way to connect with fellow book lovers! Whether you'r
 e a lifelong reader or just getting started\, we welcome all to share thei
 r thoughts and dive into exciting reads together.\nHere are the upcoming m
 eeting dates and titles:\nApril 18: The silent patient\nMay 16: Vera Wong
 's unsolicited advice for murderers\nJune 20: The sleeping car porter\nJu
 ly 18: The Immoralist\nAugust 15: How it all began\nInformation Collecti
 on Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toro
 nto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)
 \, and 20(d). The information will only be used for event and program regi
 stration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handle
 s your information can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.
 ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Weston\, Youth Hub Area. Main Floor.
