BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:What is Artificial Intelligence?
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T200000
UID:69b1f8c16724c63d00f8460f@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:AI technologies have become increasingly prevalent in many asp
 ects of modern life\, including healthcare\, finance\, transportation\, an
 d entertainment. Some examples of AI applications include virtual assistan
 ts like Siri and Alexa\, self-driving cars\, fraud detection systems\, and
  personalized recommendations in online shopping. Come join this beginner 
 in-person class to learn what AI is\, how it learns and predicts outcomes\
 , considerations when using GenAI applications\, and how the Internet of T
 hings (IOT) applies to AI.\nRegistration is required for this class and be
 gins April 15th\, 2026 at 12:30pm.\nNote: Your spot will not be guaranteed
  after 5 minutes of the start of the program.\nInformation Collection Noti
 ce:\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Pub
 lic Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 
 20(d). The information will only be used for event and program registratio
 n\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your 
 information can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 
 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, 2nd Floor - eLearning Lab
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b1f8c16724c63d00f8460f
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
