BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wellness Recovery Action Plan (WRAP)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T200000
UID:697127ac4a9fd98b7f78e26a@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:WRAP is for\nanyone\nlooking to strengthen their well-being—
 whether you’re supporting your mental health\, managing stress\, or simp
 ly wanting to feel more balanced and resilient in daily life. Participant
 s will receive a\nWRAP certificate\nupon program completion.\nIn an 8-wee
 k WRAP group\, individuals explore:\nself-care tools like peer connections
 \, relaxation and mindfulness techniques\, stress reduction strategies\, a
 nd more\nresources for keeping well and feeling better in difficult times.
 \nInterested in learning more? Drop in for the\ninformation session\non\nF
 riday\, April 24\, 2026.\nThis WRAP Group meets\nevery Friday\,\nonce a we
 ek for 8 weeks\, May 1 - June 19\, 2026\, 5:00-8:00pm\n. Registration clo
 ses after week 3\, or when full.\nTTC Presto tickets will be provided.\nSn
 acks and refreshments are provided for all participants. Ingredient lists 
 will be available at the program.\nThis program is in collaboration with\
 nGerstein Crisis Centre's WRAP initiative\n. Gerstein Crisis Centre is sol
 ely responsible for the protection of \npersonal information collected thr
 ough the program registration \nprocess.
LOCATION:Parliament Street\, 2nd floor\, end of hallway
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/697127ac4a9fd98b7f78e26a
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
