BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Google AI Essentials: Online Learning Circle
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260529T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260529T160000
UID:69d93e25bd5c392c76437489@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Curious about artificial intelligence or want to learn practic
 al AI skills for work and personal use? Join our staff-facilitated learnin
 g circle to complete the self-paced Google AI Essentials specialization.\n
 This 10-hour introductory-level specialization\, offered through Coursera\
 , is available for free to learning circle participants. It is made up of 
 five courses\, each containing four units that consist of short videos\, a
 rticles\, assignments and a short multiple-choice quiz.\nBy completing the
  specialization\,\nyou will learn:\nHow AI works\nHow to write effective p
 rompts\nHow to use generative AI tools responsibly\nHow to identify AI's p
 otential biases and avoid harm\nHow to stay up to date with AI news\nAfter
  you complete the course\, you earn a Google certificate and a badge to sh
 are with others\nLearning Circles are study groups guided by\nlibrary staf
 f for people who want to complete the Google AI Essentials specialization 
 together in a welcoming space:\nLearners meet weekly and work together thr
 ough course materials.\nParticipants are expected to commit to attending a
 ll four learning circle sessions.\nNo AI experience is required.\nHow to J
 oi\nn a Learning Circle:\nRegister once on the first session of this event
  series\, in order to attend all sessions.\nPlease sign up with a\nvalid e
 mail address\n.\nA valid TPL library card is required for online circles
 .\nAttend all four sessions (online via Zoom\, date: May 8\, May 15\, May 
 22 and May 29)\nRegistration is a two-step procedure. First\, participants
  must complete their registration through this page. After this step\, lib
 rary staff will follow up to request additional information in order to co
 mplete the registration.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal inf
 ormation on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the
  Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The informatio
 n will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and eval
 uation. Questions about how the library handles your information can be di
 rected to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yo
 nge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69d93e25bd5c392c76437489
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
