SUMMARY:Sweetgrass Medicine Mist: An Infusion
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260507T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260507T150000
UID:69cd6305213814b1b522a6e7@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:In this workshop\, participants will learn about the significa
 nce of sweetgrass from Indigenous perspective. Participants will also make
  a sweetgrass infusion that will later be strained and bottled to become a
  mist. All supplies are provided.\nDrop-in\, no registration required. Pro
 gram will be capped at the first 15 participants.\nTanya Gluvakov is a mix
 ed Mohawk woman from Toronto with family and "roots" from Six Nations of t
 he Grand River in Oshweken\, Ontario. The founder of Roots and Raven\, Tan
 ya is a herbalist\, a mom\, a teacher\, and auntie\, who teaches several w
 orkshops about medicines from the land and how connecting with them helps 
 us find our way. She also leads several projects that bring the resurgence
  of medicines and accessibility to urban communities.
LOCATION:High Park
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69cd6305213814b1b522a6e7
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
