UID:69a74a09b0595799c0a0adba@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Clean air is essential for good health. We spend most of our t
 ime indoors\, yet there are no laws or regulations that directly govern i
 ndoor air quality. The air in our indoor spaces may not be as safe to bre
 athe as we think but tools are available to improve indoor air quality.\nW
 orkshop Overview:\nWhat is IAQ (Indoor Air Quality)?\nTypes of air pollut
 ion\nThe impact of poor air quality on health\nUnderstanding ventilation a
 nd air filtration\nHow IAQ is monitored and assessed\nTools and methods to
  improve IAQ -\nCO2 Monitors\nPresented by: Clean Indoor Air Toronto
LOCATION:Albert Campbell\, Digital Innovation Hub
