BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Pressed Flowers Necklace Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T150000
UID:69b46dfde2a2952aed07f09e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:For Mother's Day this year\, capture the beauty of the season
 s in this hands-on Flower Pressed Necklace Workshop. Whether you are a jew
 elry enthusiast or a nature lover\, this session offers a creative space 
 to design a wearable piece of art -- for you or your mother -- that lasts 
 forever.\nWhat You Will Discover:\nThe Art of Pressing: Learn the essentia
 l techniques for preserving blooms\, including the best time of day to har
 vest and which flower varieties hold their color and shape best.\nStorage 
 Secrets: Master the professional methods for storing pressed flowers to pr
 event fading and moisture damage.\nJewelry Design: Arrange your choice of 
 delicate petals and greenery into a custom pendant. You will leave with a 
 one-of-a-kind necklace that respects your personal style.\nWorkshop Detail
 s:\nAll inclusive: Your registration covers all materials\; all participan
 ts receive a curated kit by the instructor. Tools are provided by the inst
 ructor and returned at the end of the workshop.\nSkill Level: Perfect for 
 beginners\; no prior experience in jewelry making or gardening is required
 .\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form i
 s collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\,
  sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for
  event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Registrants may
