BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Branch Art Exhibit: Lifeworks of Hedy Catherina Scambia presented 
 by Carmelitta Scambia
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260402T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T235959
UID:69ac997d4a9fd98b7f82d48d@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Throughout the month of April\, an exhibit titled Lifeworks 
 of Hedy Catherina Scambia is on display at North York Central Library bra
 nch.\nHedy Catherina Scambia was born in Austria\, where she graduated fro
 m the Vienna Academy of Art. Among her accomplishments are fashion design
 ing\, graphic arts\, painting and sculpting. Hedy's favourite subjects wer
 e floral still life and portraiture. Her works are found in private and co
 rporate collections and have been exhibited in many juried shows. She beli
 eved 'a day without painting is like a day without sunshine'. Hedy's works
  add colour\, life and light to the many walls that they grace.\n"Hedy Sc
 ambia has left a legacy of work for us to enjoy. Her brilliant florals upl
 ift the energy and atmosphere of any room. In her portraits\, she captures
  the very essence of the soul of each of her subjects. Her landscapes bre
 athe with a calm and earthy charm. Hedy has gifted us with a vibrant body 
 of work\, which will live on and be appreciated by one and all."\nThis ex
 hibit is part of TPL's\nArt Exhibits Space\nprogram. Toronto Public Librar
 y provides space for local artists to exhibit their work at locations acro
 ss the city. These exhibits aim to reflect the diverse cultural interests 
 of the city and its neighbourhoods.\nThe exhibit can be viewed during\nNor
 th York Central Library\nopen hours.\nFree. All are welcome.\nImage credit
 : Artist: Hedy Catherina Scambia\; Mediterranean Village.
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, 2nd floor Art Gallery
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69ac997d4a9fd98b7f82d48d
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
