BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:What is Artificial Intelligence?
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T120000
UID:69b1f7e0b0595799c0a27ff3@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:AI technologies have become increasingly prevalent in many asp
 ects of modern life\, including healthcare\, finance\, transportation\, an
 d entertainment. Some examples of AI applications include virtual assistan
 ts like Siri and Alexa\, self-driving cars\, fraud detection systems\, and
  personalized recommendations in online shopping. Come join this beginner 
 in-person class to learn what AI is\, how it learns and predicts outcomes\
 , considerations when using GenAI applications\, and how the Internet of T
 hings (IOT) applies to AI.\nRegistration is required for this class and be
 gins April 9th\, 2026 at 12:30pm.\nNote: Your spot will not be guaranteed 
 after 5 minutes of the start of the program.\nInformation Collection Notic
 e:\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Publ
 ic Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 2
 0(d). The information will only be used for event and program registration
 \, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your i
 nformation can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 4
 16-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, 2nd Floor - eLearning Lab
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b1f7e0b0595799c0a27ff3
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
