UID:69b2ee806583d22e3c0ec318@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Rachel Phan is a Chinese-Vietnamese Canadian writer whose debu
 t memoir\nRestaurant Kid\nexplores the complexities of growing up as the d
 aughter of refugees who fled the Vietnam War and rebuilt their lives throu
 gh a small-town restaurant in Canada. Through personal stories rooted in r
 esilience\, sacrifice\, and belonging\, Rachel sheds light on the impact o
 f colonialism\, intergenerational trauma\, and the emotional weight of cul
 tural and societal expectations.\nA Q&A and book signing will follow the p
 resentation.\nNo registration required.
LOCATION:Yorkville\, Centre of library
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b2ee806583d22e3c0ec318
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
