BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:How to Teach Kids About Money
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T200000
UID:698506fe491b809c6f17e677@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:From the early years of learning how to count change to budget
 ing in the high school years\, Teri Courchene will share ideas and strateg
 ies for teaching your children the value of money.\nTeri will cover topics
  including how playing board and card games helps children with math\, str
 ategies for giving children allowances\, and giving children more responsi
 bility with money as they get older. She will also cover how to get teenag
 ers started with investing once they turn 18.\nPresented by Teri Courchene
 \, an economist\, math tutor and former investing instructor at the Univer
 sity of Toronto School for Continuing Studies.\nThis program is for adults
  but Teri invites children to attend with their parents.\nDrop-in\, no reg
 istration required.
LOCATION:Danforth/Coxwell
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698506fe491b809c6f17e677
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
