BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Prompt Sounds and Effects with AI Tools
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260605T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260605T200000
UID:69a202eb8089f23c675eb01c@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Musicians and producers spend hours tweaking knobs and sliders
  to get the perfect sound. But what if you could simply describe the sound
  you're looking for - "warm and fuzzy\," "sharp and metallic\," "underwate
 r echo" - and have AI create it for you?\nA new generation of AI-powered t
 ools is making this possible\, letting you build custom sounds and effects
  using plain language descriptions right inside your music software. In th
 is session\, you'll learn the vocabulary that helps AI understand what you
 're after\, then put these tools to the test to see how close they can get
  to the sound in your head. No prior music or programming experience is re
 quired.\nRegistration is required.\nThis program is part of the Innovator 
 in Residence (AI and Music Production) program\, which is designed to help
  beginner and intermediate learners build knowledge and creative skills an
 d get hands-on with current AI tools in music production and learn about t
 he history\, copyright and ethics of generative music. For more informatio
 n and a full list of programs\, visit\ntpl.ca/airesident\n.
LOCATION:Fairview\, Digital Innovation Hub\, 3rd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a202eb8089f23c675eb01c
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
