UID:69d158749057005337d27586@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:​Unlock the secrets to securing government funding in Canada
 .\nThis hands-on workshop guides women entrepreneurs through identifying o
 pportunities\, building strong applications\, and avoiding common mistakes
 . Participants will gain tools\, templates and personalized feedback. They
  will leave with a clear\, actionable roadmap for accessing and sustaining
  funding to grow their businesses.\nAbout the Presenter:\nLucrezia Spagnol
 o\nis the\nFounder and CEO of VESTA. She has successfully secured over $3
 M in funding from a range of funders. Her leadership experience includes s
 erving as Entrepreneur in Residence for organizations such as the Toronto 
 Public Library and the Ashoka Foundation.\nInformation Collection Notice:\
 nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public 
