DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T113000
UID:69a9fb398089f23c6760161f@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Computers for Beginners 1: Use the Mouse\nA class on how to us
 e a mouse for absolute beginners with little or no computer experience.\nI
 n this first session you will:\nObserve and practice how to operate a mous
 e effectively\nUnderstand various mouse pointers and cursors\nReview basic
  keyboard functions\nUse the mouse for basic Windows functions\nUpon compl
 etion of this class students will be able to use a computer mouse at a bas
 ic level and will be able to go online for additional practice.\nPrerequis
 ites: No computer experience required.\nFormat: Hands-on with demonstratio
 ns\nComputers for Beginners 2: Use the Keyboard\nA class on basic keyboard
  functions for absolute beginners with little or no computer experience.\n
 In this second session you will:\nFamiliarize yourself through practice wi
 th the most essential keyboard functions (alphabet\, number and symbol key
 s)\nPractice proper keyboarding posture\nUpon completion of this class stu
 dents will be able to use a keyboard at a beginner level and know how to g
 o online for additional practice.\nPrerequisites: Computer for Beginners 1
  or basic mouse skills\nFormat: Hands-on with demonstrations\nComputers fo
 r Beginners 3: Use Windows\nA class on essential basic Windows skills for 
 absolute beginners with little computer experience.\nIn this third session
  you will:\nBecome familiar with the Windows (10) operating system\nPracti
 ce using common Windows features: File Explorer\, Desktop\, Taskbar\, Wind
 ows\, Applications\nUpon completion of this class students will have a bas
 ic understanding of how to create and organize files in the Windows enviro
 nment.\nPrerequisites: Computer for Beginners 1 & 2 or basic mouse and key
 boarding skills\nFormat: Hands-on with demonstrations\nComputers for Begin
 ners 4: Use the Internet\nAn introductory class on the Internet for absolu
 te beginners with little computer experience.\nIn this fourth session you 
 will:\nUnderstand how to read a web site address\nPractice using web addre
 sses\nSearch for information using a search engine\nExplore a web site in 
 detail to understand its key components\nUpon completion of this class stu
 dents will be able to use the internet at a beginner level and complete si
 mple searches.\nPrerequisites: Computer for Beginners 1 & 2 or basic mouse
  and keyboarding skills\nFormat: Hands-on with demonstrations\nComputers f
 or Beginners 5: Use Google Search and Maps\nA class on using Google's filt
 ers\, tools\, and Maps for absolute beginners with little computer experie
 nce.\nIn this fifth session you will:\nUse Google search tools more effect
 ively to find websites\, images\, and news sites\nExplore Google Maps to f
 ind addresses and get directions for transit and road travel.\nUpon comple
 tion of this class students will be able to use more advanced search engin
 e features and use Google Maps at a basic level.\nPrerequisites: Computers
  for Beginners 1 & 2 or basic mouse\, keyboarding and internet skills\nFor
 mat: Hands-on with demonstrations
LOCATION:McGregor Park
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a9fb398089f23c6760161f
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
