BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Make a Song for Someone You Love
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260420T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260420T160000
UID:69a1ffd74dacf581ff7e669c@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Have you ever wished you could write a song for a friend's bir
 thday\, create a musical thank-you for someone special\, or surprise a lov
 ed one with a one-of-a-kind melody? You don't need any musical training - 
 today's AI tools let you create original music simply by describing what y
 ou want in everyday language.\nIn this beginner-friendly session\, you'll 
 learn how to use free AI music tools to create short\, personalized songs 
 and musical messages. Whether it's a heartfelt love song\, a funny birthda
 y tune\, or a musical inside joke to share with a friend\, you'll walk awa
 y with something you made yourself - and the know-how to make more. No com
 puter or music experience is required.\nThis program is part of the Innova
 tor in Residence (AI and Music Production) program\, which is designed to 
 help beginner and intermediate learners build knowledge and creative skill
 s and get hands-on with current AI tools in music production and learn abo
 ut the history\, copyright and ethics of generative music. For more inform
 ation and a full list of programs\, visit tpl.ca/airesident.
LOCATION:Fairview\, Room 201\, 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a1ffd74dacf581ff7e669c
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
