BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wednesday Afternoon @ the Movies: Rust
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T123000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T150000
UID:698f8da6d34a4e7592859ee0@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us on Wednesday afternoon at the library for a screening 
 of Rust movie.\nA 13 year-old boy\, left to fend for himself and his broth
 er following the death of their parents in 1880s Wyoming\, is taken on a h
 arrowing journey to old Mexico by his long estranged grandfather after he'
 s sentenced to hang for the accidental killing of a local rancher\, with a
  US Marshall and a vicious bounty hunter in pursuit.\nRated 14A. 2 hrs 20
  mins.\nEnglish Subtitles for the Deaf and Hard of Hearing (SDH) when ava
 ilable.
LOCATION:Weston\, Program Room. Lower Level.
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698f8da6d34a4e7592859ee0
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
