BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The True Crime Club at Taylor Memorial
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T200000
UID:6941dc7dfd55fb29005828f1@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This club is for those who enjoy discussing  true crimes from 
 next door to around the world.  Each month we review a case and then we de
 cide which cases we want to look into next month   We investigate the case
 s on our own using a variety of true crime databases\, podcasts\, books et
 c.   We  then meet to discuss the theories and ideas  around the crime wit
 h one another. We are a passionate group and always discuss cases in a res
 pectful manner.  Come and join us on the second Tuesday of the month   for
  an intimate evening of  True Crime.\nThis Month's topic The Zodiac Killer
LOCATION:Taylor Memorial\, Program room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6941dc7dfd55fb29005828f1
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
