BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:I Like Movies: A Film for National Canadian Film Day
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T160000
UID:69b045942866a5b48841181d@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:April 15th is National Canadian Film Day!\nThanks to\nReel Can
 ada\nfor providing the screening of this film.\nThis film is presented by 
 North York Central Library Film Club. At our celebration of the Day\, sna
 cks and refreshments are provided for all participants. Ingredient lists w
 ill be available at the program.\nThe North York Central Library Film Club
  meets monthly on Wednesdays. There is a short\, informal discussion after
  the screening\, time permitting. All films begin at 2:00 pm in the Audito
 rium.\nRegistration is not required. Please contact the Browsery Departmen
 t at 416-395-5672 for more information.\nI Like Movies (2022)\nRunning tim
 e: 99 minutes\nDirector: Chandler Levack\nStarring: Isaiah Lehtinen\, Romi
 na D’Ugo\, and Krista Bridges\nLawrence Kweller\, a socially inept 17-ye
 ar old cinephile\, gets a job at a video store where he forms a complicate
 d friendship with his older store manager\, Alana.\nNext Dates:\nMay 20 : 
 Hamnet\nJun 24 :  The Great Escaper
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, Auditorium\, 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b045942866a5b48841181d
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
