DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T150000
UID:69459404293fe254002a3538@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Do you love reading and talking about books?  Join us for an i
 nformal\, relaxed\, and casual meeting to discuss various books throughout
  the year.  The book club will meet monthly on the following dates:\nJanua
 ry 21:           Foster by Claire Keegan\nFebruary 18:\nThe Strange Eventf
 ul History by Claire Messud\nMarch 18:             The Ride of Her Life by
  Elizabeth Letts\nApril 15:                The Speckled Beauty by Rick Bra
 gg\nMay 20:                 The Librarianist by Patrick Dewitt\nJune 17: 
  Oh William! by Elizabeth Strout\nJuly 15: The Bookish Life of Nina Hill b
 y Abbi Waxman\nAugust 19: Cold Mountain by Charles Frazier\nSeptember 16: 
 Hotel on the Corner of Bitter and Sweet by Jamie Ford\nOctober 21: In the
  Upper Country by Kai Thomas\nNovember 18: Julie Chan is Dead by Liann Zhe
 ng\nDrop in\, no registration required.
LOCATION:Evelyn Gregory
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69459404293fe254002a3538
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
