BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Branch Art Exhibit: Searching Colours for the Stories by Marina Bu
 rke
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260401T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T235959
UID:69b02ade4a9fd98b7f8349ac@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Throughout the month of April\, the works of artist Marina Bur
 ke are on display at Leaside branch in an exhibit titled Searching Colours
  for the Stories.\nMarina is a visual artist who lives and creates in Toro
 nto. She has been an active member of The Artists' Network in the East end
  of the city. She likes to experiment with art thus living in a constant 
 search for the right medium to depict the world inside and out.\n"I am con
 stantly evolving as an artist and as a person. The river of life brings th
 e feeling of flow and it is a fascinating ability to experience it. I like
  depicting people and their faces\, trying to reach out to their inner sel
 f\, to capture their spirits\, and\, in the end\, expressing my own feelin
 gs and visions of each and every model that I have."\nThis exhibit is part
  of\nTPL's Art Exhibit\nprogram. Toronto Public Library provides space for
  local artists to exhibit their work at locations across the city. These e
 xhibits aim to reflect the diverse cultural interests of the city and its 
 neighbourhoods.\nThe exhibit can be viewed during\nLeaside Branch\nopen ho
 urs. Please check the Leaside Branch page before your visit.\nFree. All ar
 e welcome.
LOCATION:Leaside\, Community Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b02ade4a9fd98b7f8349ac
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Enigmatic Elders Mystery Book Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260521T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260521T150000
UID:697d1b6f4dacf581ff77fa70@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This book club is for readers who enjoy reading various types 
 of mysteries.\nOur goal is to have fun and travel the reading journey toge
 ther.\nWe will be covering the following 3 books on the following dates:\n
 The Department of Rare Books and Special Collections\nby Eva Jurczyk (Thur
 sday\, March 19th)\nJourney to Munich by Jacqueline Winspear (Thursday\, A
 pril 16th)\nCity of Darkness & Light by Rhys Bowen (Thursday\, May 21st)\
 nNote\n:\nThe Department of Rare Books and Special Collections\nbook for T
 hursday\, March 19th will be available to pick up at the Reference Desk on
  the 4th floor. Please contact the department\nprior\nto arriving to the 
 library if you want to set aside a copy.\nInformation Collection Notice:\
 nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public 
 Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d
 ). The information will only be used for event and program registration\, 
 delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your info
 rmation can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-
 397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, 3rd floor\, Discussion Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/697d1b6f4dacf581ff77fa70
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
