BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:NatureTO: Managing Invasive Plants Around Your Home
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T153000
UID:69a30ec68d5e2d09336238ab@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join the\nCity of Toronto Urban Forestry\nteam\nfor a presenta
 tion on invasive plants commonly found around homes in Toronto. Learn how 
 to identify these species\, understand their impact\, and how to manage th
 em. You’ll also get tips on supporting local biodiversity through enhanc
 ing native habitats. Perfect for gardeners\, homeowners\, and anyone inter
 ested in urban ecology.\nThis program is part of TPL's\nOur Fragile Planet
 \nprogram series\, supported by Friends of Toronto Public Library\, South 
 Chapter.​
LOCATION:Locke\, Locke program room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a30ec68d5e2d09336238ab
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Misconceptions about the Universe: From Everyday Life to the Big B
 ang
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260425T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260425T150000
UID:69a306032866a5b4883ef48b@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a presentation on astronomy that touches on a w
 ide variety of common misconceptions\, from everyday life (e.g.\, the cau
 se of the seasons) to things in our solar system\, to black holes\, UFOs\,
  and the Big Bang.\nPresented by Dr. John Percy\, Professor Emeritus from 
 the University of Toronto in Astronomy and Astrophysics.\nNo registration 
 is required.
LOCATION:Albion\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a306032866a5b4883ef48b
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
