BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Book Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T200000
UID:694b336b4be11d3d00d9a54d@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Welcome to the Bloor Gladstone Book Club where we discuss boo
 ks in a fun and friendly atmosphere. New members are most welcome! A limit
 ed number of copies are available for pick up at the first floor desk.\nOu
 r titles for 2026 are:\nJanuary:\nOur Homesick Songs\nby Emma Hooper\nFebr
 uary:\nWillie: The Game Changing Story of the NHL's First Black Player\n
 by Willie O’Ree\nMarch:\nFoster\nby Claire Keegan\nApril:\nCrow Lake\nby
  Mary Lawson\nMay:\nThe Headmasters Wager\nby Vincent Lam\nJune:\nKukum\nb
 y Michel Jean (transl.)\nJuly:\nStation Eleven\nby Emily St. John Mandel\
 nAugust:\nYellowface\nby R. F. Kuang\nSeptember:\nRecitatif\n: a story by 
 Toni Morrison\nOctober:\nThe Wife's Tale\nby Aida Edemariam\nNovember:\nRu
 n Towards the Danger: Confrontations With a Body of Memory\nby Sarah Poll
 ey
LOCATION:Bloor/Gladstone\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/694b336b4be11d3d00d9a54d
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
