BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Introduction to 3D Printing
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T190000
UID:69ca7d5c274a65e67a912bc2@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Learn how 3D printers work and how you can print at the Toront
 o Public Library’s Digital Innovation Hubs. This class includes hands-on
  instruction with Prusa Slicer\, the software used to prepare your 3D obje
 ct file for printing on a Prusa MK3S+ 3D printer.\nNote: Customers are no 
 longer required to attend a mandatory 3D printing class prior to using a 3
 D printer at the Toronto Public Library’s Digital Innovation Hubs. This 
 class is for those who are interested in learning more about 3D printing a
 nd how to use the Prusa software.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe per
 sonal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library 
 under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The i
 nformation will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery
  and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your information 
 can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981
 \, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:York Woods\, Digital Innovation Hub\, Main Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69ca7d5c274a65e67a912bc2
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:NatureTO: Trees Around the Branch Tour
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260612T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260612T153000
UID:69d6a435ad384e40edb9ad60@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:The Parkdale branch and its neighbourhood is home to a variety
  of trees. Join the City of Toronto Urban Forestry staff to explore the na
 tural world on a local neighbourhood tour. Learn how to recognize differen
 t species and fun facts about their cultural and ecological importance.\nT
 he tour will start and end at the Parkdale branch in the branch lobby area
  and will be guided by the City of Toronto Urban Forestry staff. This pro
 gram takes place rain or shine. In the event of severe inclement weather\,
  registrants will be notified of an alternative date.\nThere may be uneven
 \, unpaved surfaces along the route. Please dress and prepare accordingly 
 for this outdoor program (e.g. gloves/mittens\, hats\, sunscreen\, water\,
  comfortable shoes).\nChildren under 12 must be accompanied by a parent/ca
 regiver. Registration is required.
LOCATION:Parkdale\, Meeting point is in branch lobby.
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69d6a435ad384e40edb9ad60
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Northern District Book Club—Evenings
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T200000
UID:6952bded491b809c6f0fd7cc@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a friendly\, spirited discussion of a different bo
 ok on the third Wednesday of each month. We read an eclectic mix of mostly
  contemporary fiction.\nThere is also an afternoon session to discuss the 
 same book on the second Wednesday of each month at 2:00 p.m.  You are we
 lcome at either or both!\nApril 15\, 2026:\nThe Mountains Sing\nby Phan Q
 uế Mai Nguyễn\nMay 20\, 2026:\nSea of Tranquility\nby Emily St. John 
 Mandel\nJune 17\, 2026:\nPrairie Edge\nby Conor Kerr\nJuly 15\, 2026:\nLib
 eration Day\nby George Saunders\nSeptember 16\, 2026:\nOrbital\nby Samanth
 a Harvey\nOctober 21\, 2026:\nMaybe You Should Talk to Someone\nby Lori Go
 ttlieb\nNovember 18\, 2026:\nStone Yard Devotional\nby Charlotte Wood\nDec
 ember 16\, 2026:\nThe Laundryman's Boy\nby Edward Y. C. Lee
LOCATION:Northern District\, Main Floor Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6952bded491b809c6f0fd7cc
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
