BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Between the Lines Bookclub
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T200000
UID:6962837f91e4576f847bd0fe@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Become a page-turner by joining the Between the Lines Book Clu
 b! Here\, we embark on a new chapter with every read\, diving into a world
  of endless possibilities. From gripping thrillers to heartwarming coming-
 of-age tales\, or a sprinkle of fantasy adventures\, there's something for
  everyone. Whether you're a die-hard fan of one genre or love mixing thing
 s up\, you'll find a place here to discuss\, share\, and connect with fell
 ow readers. Ready to explore different worlds and discover your next favor
 ite book? Join us and let?s turn the page together!\nFriday April 17:\nThe
  Seven Husbands of Evelyn Hugo by Taylor Jenkins Reid\nA reclusive Holly
 wood legend finally tells her story—on her own terms. The Seven Husbands
  of Evelyn Hugo pulls readers into the dazzling and ruthless world of old 
 Hollywood\, where fame comes at a price and love is rarely simple. As Evel
 yn recounts her rise to stardom and the truth behind her seven marriages\,
  long-buried secrets begin to surface. It’s a story of ambition\, identi
 ty\, sacrifice\, and a love that defies expectations—perfect for a book 
 club ready to discuss glamour\, heartbreak\, and what it really means to l
 ive authentically.\nIf you need help getting a copy of the book or have an
 y questions\, please contact us at sastaff@tpl.ca or 416-393-7653. Copies 
 of the monthly titles are available at the circulation desk.
LOCATION:Sanderson\, Main Floor Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6962837f91e4576f847bd0fe
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
