DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260506T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260506T200000
UID:698f490f8b29ea2800cfd8b0@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Independent filmmaker\nCameron Tingley\npresents Life As We K
 now It\, a one-of-a-kind presentation using humorous short films to get 
 people talking about how mass culture shapes our relationships with each o
 ther\, with society at large\, and with the natural world. The films are p
 roduced with the theatrical troupe The Flying Spot Players. Many of the th
 emes deal with environmental issues\, media awareness\, and social civilit
 y.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form 
 is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\
 , sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used fo
