BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:What Our Buildings Say About Us
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260528T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260528T193000
UID:69b3544cb48451fc3c088c7b@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Professor Shannon Kyles discusses the history of architecture 
 in Ontario and what it says about the people who have built this province.
  Starting with the Indigenous people\, going through the first century of 
 European contact\, through the 20th century wars\, democratic policies tha
 t resulted\, and finally onto the 21st century speculative housing practic
 e.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form 
 is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\
 , sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used fo
 r event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions abou
 t how the library handles your information can be directed to Answerline s
