BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wellness Recovery Action Plan (WRAP)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260601T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260601T200000
UID:69960daf4a9fd98b7f7ed8ef@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:WRAP is for\nanyone\nlooking to strengthen their well-being—
 whether you’re supporting your mental health\, managing stress\, or simp
 ly wanting to feel more balanced and resilient in daily life. Participant
 s will receive a\nWRAP certificate\nupon program completion.\nIn an 8-wee
 k WRAP group\, individuals explore:\nself-care tools like peer connections
 \, relaxation and mindfulness techniques\, stress reduction strategies\, a
 nd more\nresources for keeping well and feeling better in difficult times.
 \nInterested in learning more? Drop in for the information session on Mon
 day\, May 25 from 5-7 PM.\nThis WRAP Group meets\nevery Monday\,\nonce a w
 eek for 8 weeks\, June 1 - July 20\, 2026\, 5-8pm\n. Registration closes 
 after week 3\, or when full.\nTTC Presto tickets will be provided.\nSnacks
  and refreshments are provided for all participants. Ingredient lists will
  be available at the program.\nThis program is in collaboration with\nGer
 stein Crisis Centre's WRAP initiative\n. Gerstein Crisis Centre is solely
  responsible for the protection of personal information collected through
  the program registration process.
LOCATION:High Park\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69960daf4a9fd98b7f7ed8ef
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
