BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Winter Light: The Memoir of a Child of Holocaust Survivors
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260609T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260609T150000
UID:69d6d5332866a5b488475bb1@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Winter Light\n: The Memoir of a Child of Holocaust Survivors i
 s about a sequence of serendipitous rescues—an emotional rags-to-riches 
 story.\nGrace Feuerverger\, professor emerita of the University of Toronto
 \, will share her story of hope and gratitude which adds a radically diffe
 rent piece to the mosaic of post-Holocaust literature. At the core of her 
 memoir stands a little girl struggling to find a path toward the Life forc
 e and to escape from the demons of despair that permeated her home.
LOCATION:Barbara Frum\, Located in Room B on the third floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69d6d5332866a5b488475bb1
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
