BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Working With Procrastination
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T150000
UID:69989e014a9fd98b7f7f4e13@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Psychotherapist Ann Schnurr looks at procrastination through a
  new lens. What makes us procrastinate and what is the emotional toll on d
 epression and anxiety? Ways to re-engage and overcome procrastination will
  be discussed.\nIn this talk\, you’ll learn:\nWhy procrastination is an 
 emotional response\, not a character flaw\nHow the nervous system and emot
 ional body contribute to avoidance\nCommon emotional patterns behind chron
 ic delaying\nHow unprocessed emotions show\nGentle\, practical ways to wor
 k\nwith\nyour emotions instead of fighting them
LOCATION:Richview\, Room A\, 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69989e014a9fd98b7f7f4e13
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
