DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260525T150000
UID:6999dadf8b29ea2800d1889b@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Are you looking for subsidized housing in Toronto?\nThis sessi
 on will cover:\n- An overview of the RGI application process\n- Eligibilit
 y requirements\n- Steps for submitting and updating applications\n- Inform
 ation on priority access\n- The choice-based cycle housing offer process a
 nd the Single Offer Rule\n- Financial assistance programs to help the tena
 nts/home owners\nWhether you are a first-time applicant or seeking assista
 nce with an existing application\, this session will empower you with the 
 knowledge needed to navigate the Rent Geared to Income housing system.\nPr
 esented by The Housing Help Centre (THHC)\, a registered non-profit agency
  whose mandate is to help people access and maintain affordable and safe m
 arket rent accommodation.\nPlease arrive a few minutes early.\nThe persona
 l information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library unde
 r the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The infor
 mation will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and
  evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your information can 
 be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 7
 89 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Albert Campbell\, Learning Centre\, 2nd floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6999dadf8b29ea2800d1889b
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
