SUMMARY:Finding Recovery Through Exercise Skills and Hope (FRESH)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260608T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260608T150000
UID:69bc6d822866a5b48843385e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This\n program helps people stay active\, make friends\, learn
  new skills\, and \nhave fun. It involves peer-led group activities which 
 can include crafts\, games\,\n walking\, yoga\, and more. Meet new folks\
 , build social connections\, and tell us\n about programs and services you
  would like to see in the neighbourhood!\nJoin us at the crafts & games ta
 ble\, or for a community walk (weather permitting).\nVisit with a therapy 
 dog!\nHippie is here on Feb 23\, Mar 2\, 16\, 30. Ozzy is here on Mar 9\, 
 23.\nSnacks and refreshments are provided for all participants. Ingredient
  lists will be available at the program.\nThis program is in collaboratio
 n with\nGerstein Crisis Centre's F.R.E.S.H. initiative\n.
LOCATION:High Park\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69bc6d822866a5b48843385e
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
