END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sea of Life: Documentary for National Canadian Film Day
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T193000
UID:699b3fd74dacf581ff7d12e7@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Sea of Life is a 2017 documentary film about filmmaker Julia B
 arnes' journey around the world to save the ecosystems we depend on\, as 
 we come closer to causing a mass extinction in the oceans.\nScheduled for 
 the day after National Canadian Film Day\, in this documentary\, Barnes t
 akes a deep dive into how actions by governments\, businesses and ordinary
  people can all have a drastic impact on sustainability\nThanks to\nReel C
 anada\nfor providing the screening of this film.\nRun time: 88 minutes
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, Room 1
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699b3fd74dacf581ff7d12e7
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Seniors E-Connect
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T150000
UID:69ac4c946583d22e3c0e3e1d@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Seniors E-Connect is an intergenerational program that matche
 s older adults with a teen volunteer to provide tech help\, under the guid
 ance of library staff. Learn the basics of using computers\, tablets\, and
  smartphones such as internet browsing\, eBooks\, streaming video\, and us
 ing apps\n.\nGet one-on-one support in a welcoming and friendly environmen
 t.\nDrop-ins welcome until capacity is reached.\nInformation Collection No
 tice:\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto P
 ublic Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, an
 d 20(d). The information will only be used for event and program registrat
 ion\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles you
 r information can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\
 , 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, eLearning lab\, 2nd floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69ac4c946583d22e3c0e3e1d
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wellness Recovery Action Plan (WRAP)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T160000
UID:699c90798089f23c675d8b55@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:WRAP is for\nanyone\nlooking to strengthen their well-being—
 whether you’re supporting your mental health\, managing stress\, or simp
 ly wanting to feel more balanced and resilient in daily life. Participant
 s will receive a\nWRAP certificate\nupon program completion.\nIn an 8-wee
 k WRAP group\, individuals explore:\nself-care tools like peer connections
 \, relaxation and mindfulness techniques\, stress reduction strategies\, a
 nd more\nresources for keeping well and feeling better in difficult times.
 \nThis WRAP Group meets\nevery Saturday\, once a week for 8 weeks\, Feb 28
  - April 25\, 1-4pm\n. WRAP will not be holding a session April 4\, 2026.
  Registration closes after week 3\, or when full.\nTTC Presto tickets wil
 l be provided.\nSnacks and refreshments are provided for all participants.
  Ingredient lists will be available at the program.\nThis program is in c
 ollaboration with\nGerstein Crisis Centre's WRAP initiative\n. Gerstein Cr
 isis Centre is solely responsible for the protection of \npersonal informa
 tion collected through the program registration \nprocess.
LOCATION:Bloor/Gladstone\, Bloor/Gladstone Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699c90798089f23c675d8b55
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
