BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:NatureTO: Trees Around the Branch Tour
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T153000
UID:699caa026724c63d00f4a371@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:The Ethennonnhawahstihnen’ branch and its neighbourhood is h
 ome to a variety of trees. Join the\nCity of Toronto Urban Forestry\nteam\
 nto explore the natural world on a local neighbourhood tour. Learn how to 
 recognize different species and fun facts about their cultural and ecologi
 cal importance.\nFree program. Children under 12 must be accompanied by a 
 parent/caregiver. Registration is required. To register and for more infor
 mation\, visit www.tpl.ca/locations/[EN]\nPresented as part of TPL’s env
 ironmental program series\, Our Fragile Planet. The series is generously s
 upported by Friends of Toronto Public Library\, South Chapter.\nInformatio
 n Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is collected b
 y the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(
 a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for event and pr
 ogram registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the libr
 ary handles your information can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswe
 rline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8
LOCATION:Ethennonnhawahstihnen'
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699caa026724c63d00f4a371
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
