BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Coffee and Conversation
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260515T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260515T160000
UID:699caa9cb48451fc3c0498a4@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Coffee and Conversation is a chance to get to learn about comm
 unity services\, grab a drink and some light refreshments and talk to libr
 ary staff. Different Community Partners visit each month to share resource
 s.\nCoffee and Conversation happens at Bloor/Gladstone Library on the thir
 d Friday of every month. Drop in no registration required.\nMarch's Guest 
 is: Sistering\nApril's Guest is: Seniors Safety Line
LOCATION:Bloor/Gladstone\, 2nd Floor Magazine Area
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699caa9cb48451fc3c0498a4
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:How Pleasant to Know Mr. Lear
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260512T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260512T193000
UID:699870534a9fd98b7f7f4274@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Dennis Duffy discusses the genius of Edward Lear as a painter 
 and poet\, the great joiner of oil painting and printed nonsense.\nLear wa
 s a singular eccentric in his bespoke but loosely-fitting suits and his ru
 ncible hat\, he created work placing him among the finest of graphic carto
 onists and satirists. This presentation explores that jagged world that he
  made up for himself\, in order to preserve his own complex selfhood.\n​
 Presented by Dennis Duffy\, Professor Emeritus\, Department of English\, U
 niversity of Toronto.\nRegistration is recommended. Register online\, or\
 , for assistance\, visit or call the branch.
LOCATION:Danforth/Coxwell\, 2nd Floor Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699870534a9fd98b7f7f4274
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
