DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260612T160000
UID:69a0932eec71a31f5b4155df@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This\n program helps people stay active\, make friends\, learn
  new skills\, and \nhave fun. It involves peer-led group activities which 
 can include crafts\, games\,\n walking\, yoga\, and more. Meet new folks\
 , build social connections\, and tell us\n about programs and services you
  would like to see in the neighbourhood!\nVisit with therapy dog\nRuby\nal
 ternating Fridays\, 2:30-3:30 pm. Upcoming visits are April 10\,  24\, 
 May 8\, 22\, June 5\, 19.\nSnacks and refreshments are provided for all pa
 rticipants. Ingredient lists will be available at the program.\nThis prog
 ram is in collaboration with\nGerstein Crisis Centre's F.R.E.S.H. initiati
 ve\n.
LOCATION:Northern District\, Main Floor Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a0932eec71a31f5b4155df
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
