BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Northern District Book Club—Afternoons
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260610T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260610T150000
UID:69971db881b67dfe32a75f16@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a friendly\, spirited discussion of a different bo
 ok on the second Wednesday of each month. We read an eclectic mix of mostl
 y contemporary fiction.\nThere is also an evening session to discuss the s
 ame book on the third Wednesday of each month at 7:00 p.m.  You are welc
 ome at either or both!\nApril 8\, 2026:\nThe Mountains Sing\nby Phan Qu
 ế Mai Nguyễn\nMay 13\, 2026:\nSea of Tranquility\nby Emily St. John M
 andel [\nNote:\nthis is a change.]\nJune 10\, 2026:\nPrairie Edge\nby Cono
 r Kerr\nJuly 8\, 2026:\nLiberation Day\nby George Saunders\nSeptember 9\, 
 2026:\nOrbital\nby Samantha Harvey\nOctober 14\, 2026:\nMaybe You Should T
 alk to Someone\nby Lori Gottlieb\nNovember 11\, 2026:\nStone Yard Devotion
 al\nby Charlotte Wood\nDecember 9\, 2026:\nThe Laundryman's Boy\nby Edward
  Y. C. Lee
LOCATION:Northern District\, Main Floor Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69971db881b67dfe32a75f16
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
