BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:NatureTO: Trees Around the Branch Tour
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260428T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260428T200000
UID:699f588e4dacf581ff7de5a3@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:The Highland Creek Branch and its neighbourhood is home to a v
 ariety of trees. Join the City of Toronto Urban Forestry staff to explore 
 the natural world on a local neighbourhood walking tour. Learn how to reco
 gnize different species and fun facts about their cultural and ecological 
 importance. The tour will start and end at the Highland Creek Branch. Ther
 e may be uneven\, unpaved surfaces along the route. Please dress and prepa
 re accordingly for this outdoor program (e.g. gloves/mittens\, hats\, suns
 creen\, water\, comfortable shoes). This program takes place rain or shine
 . In the event of severe inclement weather\, registrants will be notified 
 of an alternative date. Children under 12 must be accompanied by a parent/
 caregiver.\nThis program is part of TPL's\nOur Fragile Planet\nprogram ser
 ies\, supported by Friends of Toronto Public Library\, South Chapter.​\n
 The personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public L
 ibrary under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d
 ). The information will only be used for event and program registration\,
  delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your in
 formation can be directed to Answerline staff at answerline@tpl.ca\, 416-3
 97-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Highland Creek\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699f588e4dacf581ff7de5a3
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
