BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Chinese Canadian Pioneers in Aviation
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T200000
UID:69c5b9f5bf48d63c596ce604@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:In 1950\, few Torontonians were aware that the largest flying 
 school in Canada was on the Toronto Island Airport (now Billy Bishop Toron
 to City Airport)\, a short ferry ride away from the foot of Bathurst. Owne
 d and managed by two brothers\, Robert and Tommy Wong\, it trained over 80
 00 pilots by the time they retired in 1982. Robert and Tommy were posthumo
 usly inducted into Canada's Aviation Hall of Fame\, the first Asian Canadi
 ans\, in 2024. Evelyn Wong\, Robert's daughter\, will present the story of
  these pioneering Chinese Canadians\, and stories behind her children's pi
 cture book\nReach for the Sky: How Two Brothers Built An Airplane in Chi
 natown\n.\nDoors open at 6:30pm\nPresented in collaboration with North Tor
 onto Historical Society.
LOCATION:Northern District\, Room 200
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c5b9f5bf48d63c596ce604
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Kimjang: Communal kimchi making with Chef Sang Kim
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T200000
UID:699f98408d5e2d093361ad29@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join TV host and celebrity chef Sang Kim in a communal kimchi-
 making experience\, called Kimjang\, named UNESCO’s Intangible Culture H
 eritage. Participants will learn about the origins and history of traditio
 nal poggi kimchi and the rituals of Kimjang. They will then chop vegetable
 s and prepare the kimchi* to take home for fermentation. Recipes will also
  be distributed.\n*Kimchi paste contains fish sauce and fermented baby shr
 imp.\nFood allergy notice: Please be aware that food will be used in this 
 program. Certain food ingredients may cause allergic reactions in some peo
 ple. This program uses a Kimchi paste that contains fish sauce and ferment
 ed baby shrimp\nThis is an in-person program for\nAdults\n.  Space is limi
 ted.\n*Registration opens April 4 2026.   Register online or call 416-396-
 3975.\nMeeting Room\, S. Walter Stewart Library\n------------\nInformation
  Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is collected by
  the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a
 )\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for event and pro
 gram registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the libra
 ry handles your information can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswer
 line@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:S. Walter Stewart\, Meeting Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699f98408d5e2d093361ad29
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
