BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Building Wealth in Canada
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T180000
UID:69a0946d491b809c6f1cb007@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Smart Money Management & Financial Planning in Canada\nThis wo
 rkshop helps participants take control of their finances with confidence. 
 You will learn to create a realistic budget\, manage cash flow\, and devel
 op habits that successful money managers use. Participants will define a 
 personal financial plan\, distinguish “wants” from “needs\,” under
 stand good vs. bad debt\, and learn how RRSPs\, RESPs\, and TFSAs can supp
 ort long-term goals. Practical steps to put the plan into action and acces
 s resources will also be provided. By the end of the session\, you will h
 ave clear strategies to manage your money and take actionable steps toward
  your financial goals.\nThe session will be led by a CPA volunteer and wil
 l feature a guided presentation\, interactive activities\, and practical h
 andouts and worksheets.\nRegistration is encouraged\n. Drop-ins welcome un
 til capacity is reached.
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, Room101
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a0946d491b809c6f1cb007
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
