SUMMARY:NatureTO:  Trees Around the Branch Tour
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T163000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T180000
UID:69a09edc2866a5b4883e9420@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:The Jones Branch and its neighbourhood is home to a variety of
  trees. Join the City of Toronto Urban Forestry team to explore the natura
 l world on a local neighbourhood tour. Learn how to recognize different sp
 ecies and fun facts about their cultural and ecological importance.\nFree 
 program. Children under 12 must be accompanied by a parent/caregiver. Regi
 stration is required and will open 1 month before the program date (March 
 17 2026).\nThe tour will start and end at the Jones Branch and will be gu
 ided by the City of Toronto Urban Forestry staff. There may be uneven\, un
 paved surfaces along the route. Please dress and prepare accordingly for t
 his outdoor program (e.g. gloves/mittens\, hats\, sunscreen\, water\, comf
 ortable shoes). This program takes place rain or shine. In the event of se
 vere inclement weather\, registrants will be notified of an alternative da
 te.\nPresented as part of TPL’s environmental program series\, Our Fragi
 le Planet. The series is generously supported by Friends of Toronto Public
  Library\, South Chapter.\nIf you identify as a person with a disability a
 nd require an accessibility accommodation to participate in this program\,
  please contact Accessibility Services by email\, accessibleservices@tpl.c
 a\, or voicemail\, 416-393-7099\, to make a request. Please contact us at 
 least three weeks in advance.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe persona
 l information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library unde
 r the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The infor
 mation will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and
  evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your information can 
 be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 7
 89 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Jones
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a09edc2866a5b4883e9420
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
