UID:69a0af074a9fd98b7f80c90f@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Authors Genevieve Graham\, Kate Hilton and Heather Marshall di
 scuss their new historical fictions novels.\nTaking us from a turn-of-the-
 century archaeological dig to a 1920s hotel and a midcentury newsroom\, be
 stselling writers Graham (\nThe Chambermaid's Key\n)\, Hilton (\nCity of t
 he Muse\n) and Marshall (\nLiberty Street\n) share three riveting new hist
 orical fiction stories brimming with mystery and suspense.\nThe authors sp
 eak with arts and life reporter Aparita Bhandari about their new books\, t
 he art of writing about a bygone era and the eternal appeal of travelling 
 back in time by book.\nQ&A and book signing to follow. Books available for
