BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Anakana Schofield: Library of Brothel
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260528T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260528T200000
UID:69a0af504a9fd98b7f80c941@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Celebrated author Anakana Schofield shares her long-anticipate
 d and wildly-inventive new novel.\nIn\nLibrary of Brothel\ntakes us into a
 n eponymous building where no one has a job\, no one can find a date\, and
  many struggle just to be housed. Rumours swirl around the crumbling struc
 ture and rapacious developers have their eyes on it. But what we find insi
 de is a unique economy: customers take shelter\, workers love their jobs\,
  and each room offers a new kind of intellectual stimulation. How can such
  a precarious place survive?\nAnakana Schofield speaks with journalist and
  critic Michelle Dean about her dazzling new novel\, a cri de coeur for h
 uman connection and the right to meaningful work.\nQ&A and book signing to
  follow. Books available for purchase.\nAbout this event’s guests:\nAnak
 ana Schofield\nMichelle Dean\nRead more:\nLibrary of Brothel : A Novel\nBi
 na\n***\nPLAN YOUR VISIT:\nLocation:\nBram and Bluma Appel Salon\, Toronto
  Reference Library (789 Yonge Street)\, 2nd floor\nTime:\nDoors open 6:00p
 m\, Event starts 7:00pm.\nTickets:\nFree registration required.\nTicket po
 licy:\nWe oversell these events to ensure that the greatest number of peop
 le have an opportunity to attend. Tickets guaranteed until 6:45pm or until
  capacity is reached. Seating first come\, first served.\nBar:\nBeer/wine 
 available for purchase (debit/credit only).\n***\nThis event is part of ou
 r signature\nSalon Series\n\, where we host local and international author
 s\, artists and thinkers in conversation about their new books and big ide
 as.\n***\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this
  form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Librarie
 s Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be u
 sed for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Registra
 nts may be contacted to fill out a brief survey following the program. Que
 stions about how the library handles your information can be directed to A
 nswerline staff at answerline@tpl.ca\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, T
 oronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Bram & Bluma Appel Salon\, 2nd floor
