BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Melissa Rombout: Yousuf Karsh\, Life & Work
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260413T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260413T190000
UID:69a0ba3b491b809c6f1cbdf0@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:When Yousuf Karsh arrived in Canada as a survivor of the Armen
 ian genocide\, no one could have predicted that he would one day revolutio
 nize the field of portrait photography. Paul Robeson\, Christian Dior\, Au
 drey Hepburn – these are just a small sample of the figures whom Karsh w
 ould immortalize with his timeless photographic technique.\nIn\nYousuf Kar
 sh: Life & Work\n\, curator and historian Melissa Rombout not only examine
 s the famed photographer’s aesthetic and technical choices but also offe
 rs a fresh perspective on what his work means to a twenty-first-century au
 dience. Joined by Sara Angel\, founder of the Art Canada Institute\, Rombo
 ut will explore Karsh's heroic life and enigmatic art\, with dynamic sampl
 es of his brilliant portraiture.\nABOUT THIS EVENT'S GUESTS:\nMelissa Romb
 out\nis an independent curator and lecturer on histories of photography. S
 he received her PhD from the Amsterdam School for Cultural Analysis for co
 nsidering the political performativity of historical and contemporary phot
 ographic collage. Active as an advisor for arts administration and museum 
 planning projects\, Rombout has had a prolific consulting career working w
 ith public agencies\, museums\, libraries\, and archives in Canada and int
 ernationally\, including the Department of Canadian Heritage\, Royal Ontar
 io Museum\, Canadian War Museum\, Global Affairs Canada Visual Art Collect
 ion\, City of Ottawa\, and U.S. National Park Service.\nSara Angel\nis the
  Founder\, Executive Director and Publisher of the Art Canada Institute (A
 CI). In 2024\, Angel received the Order of Canada in recognition of her co
 ntribution to the Canadian art world. She holds a PhD from the University 
 of Toronto\, where she received a Trudeau Doctoral Scholarship\, the most 
 prestigious award of its kind in Canada\, given to support innovative idea
 s that help solve issues of critical importance. She has been an arts comm
 entator for CBC and writes for publications including\nMaclean’s\n\,\nAr
 tNews\n\,\nThe Walrus\n\, and the\nGlobe and Mail\n.\n***\nThis event is p
 art of our signature\nSalon Series\n\, where we host local and internation
 al authors\, artists and thinkers in conversation about their new books an
 d big ideas.\n***\nPLAN YOUR VISIT:\nLocation:\nBram and Bluma Appel Salon
 \, Novella Room\, Toronto Reference Library (789 Yonge Street)\, 2nd floor
 \nTime:\nDoors open 5:30pm\, Event starts 6:00pm.\nTickets:\nFree registra
 tion required.\nTicket policy:\nWe oversell these events to make sure that
  the greatest number of people have an opportunity to attend. Tickets are 
 guaranteed until 6:45pm or until capacity is reached. Any remaining space 
 will be opened up to the rush line beginning at 6:45pm. Seating first come
 \, first served. Tickets do not guarantee seats.\nAccessibility:\nTPL is c
 ommitted to accessibility. If you are Deaf or have a disability and would 
 like to request accommodation for this event\, please contact accessiblese
 rvices@tpl.ca or 416-393-7099 at least three weeks prior to the event.\n**
 *\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form i
 s collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\,
  sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for
  event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation.\nRegistrants ma
 y be contacted to fill out a brief survey following the program\n. Questio
 ns about how the library handles your information can be directed to Answe
 rline staff at answerline@tpl.ca\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toron
 to ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Bram and Bluma Appel Salon\, 2nd Floo
 r
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a0ba3b491b809c6f1cbdf0
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
