DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260505T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260505T170000
UID:69a8c194b48451fc3c06bf4e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:For ages 8-12.\nJoin us for 4 weeks of goofy\, musical fun! Ou
 r Innovator in Residence\, Joel S. Silver\, will show you how AI works to 
 help you create music. Create songs with the silliest lyrics you can think
  of\, create a soundtrack for your own skits\, even write a theme song fo
 r the library! No music or computer experience needed - just bring your cr
 eativity!\nDrop-in. No registration required\, but space is limited.\nThis
  program is part of the Innovator in Residence (AI and Music Production) p
 rogram\, which is designed to help beginner and intermediate learners buil
 d knowledge and creative skills and get hands-on with current AI tools in 
 music production and learn about the history\, copyright and ethics of gen
 erative music. For more information and a full list of programs\, visit\nt
 pl.ca/airesident\n.
LOCATION:Fairview\, Room 201\, 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a8c194b48451fc3c06bf4e
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
