END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Vibe-Code with AI for Music Generation
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260609T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260609T160000
UID:69a203164dacf581ff7e677a@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:What if you could describe the kind of music tool you want in 
 plain English and have AI build it for you - no coding experience needed? 
 This approach\, known as "vibe-coding\," lets you design custom music-gene
 rating tools simply by having a conversation with AI.\nIn this session\, y
 ou'll use AI to help you design and build your own small music-generating 
 programs that can create melodies\, rhythms\, and patterns on the fly. You
 'll learn best practices for communicating with AI to get usable results\,
  and discover how to connect multiple tools together for more complex musi
 cal possibilities. No prior music or programming experience is required.\n
 Registration is required.\nThis program is part of the Innovator in Reside
 nce (AI and Music Production) program\, which is designed to help beginner
  and intermediate learners build knowledge and creative skills and get han
 ds-on with current AI tools in music production and learn about the histor
 y\, copyright and ethics of generative music. For more information and a f
 ull list of programs\, visit\ntpl.ca/airesident\n.
LOCATION:Fairview\, Digital Innovation Hub\, 3rd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a203164dacf581ff7e677a
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
