BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Exhibit Tour of Amazing! Fantastic! Astounding! Science Fiction an
 d the Pulp Magazines
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260425T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260425T113000
UID:69bafe6a491b809c6f2169db@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a guided tour of our current exhibit\,\nAmazing! F
 antastic! Astounding!\nThis Merril Collection exhibit looks at the incredi
 ble pulp magazines. The pulps were fiction magazines that dominated North 
 America from the 1890s to the 1950s. For over half a century\, they were t
 he most affordable source of mass entertainment. And they were also the ma
 in source of science fiction.\nExplore the rise and fall of the pulps with
  our knowledgeable staff. Celebrate the 100th anniversary of Amazing Stori
 es\, the first science fiction pulp. Discover decades-old pulps\, original
  pulp art\, books and more.
LOCATION:Lillian H. Smith\, Merril Collection Reading Room\, 3rd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69bafe6a491b809c6f2169db
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
