DESCRIPTION:This\n program helps people stay active\, make friends\, learn
  new skills\, and \nhave fun. It involves peer-led group activities which 
 can include crafts\, games\,\n walking\, yoga\, and more. Meet new folks\
 , build social connections\, and tell us\n about programs and services you
  would like to see in the neighbourhood!\nFor our upcoming sessions\, we w
 ill be screening the following films in Program Room A:\nApril 1:\nThe Not
 ebook\n(2005)\nApril 8:\nThe Terminal\n(2004)\nApril 15:\nLegally Blonde\n
 (2001)\nApril 22:\nHugo\n(2012)\nApril 29:\nGreen Book\n(2019)\nDrop in. N
 o registration required.\nSnacks and refreshments are provided for all par
 ticipants. Ingredient lists will be available at the program.\nThis progr
 am is in collaboration with\nGerstein Crisis Centre's F.R.E.S.H. initiativ
 e\n.
LOCATION:Maria A. Shchuka\, Program Room A
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69bb137c8d5e2d093366265b
