BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Ibram X. Kendi: Chain of Ideas
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T200000
UID:69bbf42dbfe6da1042248bdd@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:TPL presents National Book Award winning author Dr. Ibram X. K
 endi at the Toronto Reference Library's Appel Salon.\nAt the heart of our 
 authoritarian age lies "great replacement theory"\, the claim that shadowy
  elites are orchestrating the demographic and cultural displacement of whi
 te majorities through immigration\, diversity initiatives\, and declining 
 birth rates. In his urgent new book\nChain of Ideas: The Origins of Our Au
 thoritarian Age\n\, internationally bestselling historian Ibram X. Kendi t
 races how this conspiracy theory has mutated and spread across continents\
 , repackaging age-old prejudices in the language of a digital age.\nWhat m
 ade this fringe idea go mainstream? Kendi reveals how replacement theory c
 onnects to the deep roots of slavery\, segregation\, colonialism\, and Naz
 ism. But this isn't a book about extremists on the margins. It's about how
  reactionary ideas have been repackaged as common sense\, how they've cros
 sed borders and inspired terror\, and how they now political movements wor
 ldwide.\nHow do we recognize the warning signs when conspiracy becomes pol
 icy? What does it mean when the fringe becomes the centre? And how do we c
 hallenge ideas that offer simple answers to complex anxieties?\nBooks avai
 lable for purchase.\nAbout this event’s guests:\nIbram X. Kendi\nRead mo
 re:\nChain Of Ideas\nHow to Be An Antiracist\n***\nPLAN YOUR VISIT:\nLocat
 ion:\nBram and Bluma Appel Salon\, Toronto Reference Library (789 Yonge St
 reet)\, 2nd floor\nTime:\nDoors open 6:00pm\, Event starts 7:00pm.\nTicket
 s:\nFree registration required.\nTicket policy:\nWe oversell these events 
 to ensure that the greatest number of people have an opportunity to attend
 . Tickets guaranteed until 6:45pm or until capacity is reached. Seating fi
 rst come\, first served\nBar:\nBeer/wine available for purchase (debit/cre
 dit only).\nAccessibility:\nTPL is committed to accessibility. If you are 
 Deaf or have a disability and would like to request accommodation for this
  event\, please contact accessibleservices@tpl.ca or 416-393-7099 at least
  three weeks prior to the event.\n***\nThis event is part of our signature
 \nSalon Series\n\, where we host local and international authors\, artists
  and thinkers in conversation about their new books and big ideas.\nThis e
 vent is also part of TPL's\nBlack History and Culture Series\n.\nPresentin
 g Sponsor of Heritage Programs: TD Bank Group\, through the TD Ready Commi
 tment.\n***\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on t
 his form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libra
 ries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only b
 e used for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Regis
 trants may be contacted to fill out a brief survey following the program. 
 Questions about how the library handles your information can be directed t
 o Answerline staff at answerline@tpl.ca\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\
 , Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Bram and Bluma Appel Salon\, Toronto 
 Reference Library (789 Yonge Street)\, 2nd floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69bbf42dbfe6da1042248bdd
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
