BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Branch Art Exhibit: Summer Sketches in Ontario Provincial Parks by
  Jean-Marie Boutot
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260401T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T235959
UID:69bc3589567ba1dd31fddca0@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Throughout the month of April\, the works of artist Jean-Marie
  Boutot are on display at Richview Branch in an exhibit titled Summer Sk
 etches in Ontario Provincial Parks.\nJean-Marie Boutot is a Toronto-based 
 visual artist and OCAD graduate. She creates large-scale oil paintings tha
 t reflect urban community life and the northern landscapes she explores ea
 ch summer. Recently\, her practice has expanded to include small ink and w
 atercolour works inspired by Ontario's provincial parks.\n"This series of 
 small watercolours\, painted during summer explorations of Ontario’s pro
 vincial parks\, began as sketches for larger oil paintings but has grown 
 into a practice of its own. Their immediacy captures fleeting light and st
 illness\, reflecting both personal connection to nature and the imagery th
 at continues to inspire my studio."\nThis exhibit is part of TPL's\nArt Ex
 hibit Space\nprogram. Toronto Public Library provides space for local arti
 sts to exhibit their work at locations across the city. These exhibits aim
  to reflect the diverse cultural interests of the city and its neighbourho
 ods.\nThe exhibit can be viewed during Richview branch's open hours. Pleas
 e check the\nRichview branch\npage before you visit.\nFree. All are welcom
 e.\nImage credit: Artist: Jean-Marie Boutot\; Awenda Provincial Park Sketc
 h.
LOCATION:Richview\, 2nd Floor Gallery
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69bc3589567ba1dd31fddca0
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
