BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Breast Cancer Screening: Understanding the Benefits\, Risks and La
 test Evidence
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T190000
UID:69bc3f708d5e2d0933665ab9@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:1 in 8 Canadian women will be diagnosed with breast cancer in 
 their lifetime. Early detection through screening with mammograms can impr
 ove outcomes and save lives\, but it also raises important questions about
  who should be screened\, when screening should begin\, and how to balance
  the potential benefits and harms. Understanding the latest evidence helps
  support informed decisions about breast cancer screening and prevention.\
 nWhat to expect:\nThe Basics of Breast Cancer:\nLearn how breast cancer de
 velops\, how it is diagnosed\, and how the patterns of the disease have ch
 anged over time.\nRisk Factors:\nExplore the factors that influence a woma
 n’s risk of developing breast cancer\, including genetics\, hormonal fac
 tors and lifestyle.\nBreast Cancer Screening:\nUnderstand how mammography 
 screening works\, what the scientific evidence shows about its benefits an
 d potential harms\, and how screening programs are currently implemented i
 n Canada.\nVasily Giannakeas is a scientist at Women’s College Hospital 
 Research and Innovation Institute and an assistant professor at the Dalla 
 Lana School of Public Health\, University of Toronto. He combines his expe
 rtise in engineering\, epidemiology and public health and focuses on resea
 rch in breast and ovarian cancer.\nAbout the Series\nBridging Minds: Healt
 h & Science Conversations is a partnership between the Toronto Public Libr
 ary and Women’s College Hospital. Through monthly discussions led by exp
 erts from across different clinical areas and scientific disciplines\, thi
 s series provides attendees with the opportunity to engage directly with o
 ur topics and speakers and empowers communities to navigate health and sci
 ence topics confidently\, inspiring a future of informed decision-making.\
 nLearn more:\nhttps://www.womenscollegehospital.ca/bridging-minds/\nReserv
 e Your Spot Today!\nThis virtual event is free to join but registration is
  required.\nPlease register on Eventbrite\n.\nOnce registered\, you’ll r
 eceive an email with details on how to join the session.\nWe can’t wait 
 to see you there!
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69bc3f708d5e2d0933665ab9
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
