DESCRIPTION:Please note the April 21 meeting of the Danforth Book Club h
 as been postponed to May 21.\nJoin us to meet other readers and talk about
  the monthly book!\nThe\nApril\nMay book is Carol Rifka Brunt’s debut no
 vel\,\nTell The Wolves I’m Home\n. Books will be available for borrowin
 g at the front desk from March 26 onward.\nThe one person who truly under
 stood fourteen-year-old June Elbus was her Uncle Finn. When he dies of an 
 illness no one will speak about\, June's world is turned upside down. But 
 his death brings a surprise acquaintance into June's life--someone who wil
 l help her to heal\, and to question what she thinks she knows about her f
 amily.\nDrop-in\, no registration necessary. New club members are welcome!
LOCATION:Danforth/Coxwell\, 2nd Floor Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69bc5818491b809c6f21aa6d
