BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:I Like Movies: National Canadian Film Day Screening
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T154500
UID:69bc7c1867801235ed7350c1@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:April 15 is National Canadian Film Day. Join us for the screen
 ing of I Like Movies.\nLawrence (Lehtinen)\, an awkward and anxious 17-yea
 r-old cinephile living in Burlington\, ON\, in the early 2000s\, believes 
 that he is on the path to a legendary filmmaking career – but at this po
 int\, it’s only gotten him as far as a job at the local video store. His
  blind ambition\, combined with his unique worldview\, confounds even thos
 e closest to him\, and he soon starts to alienate his new manager Alana (D
 ’Ugo) and even his best friend (Hynes White)\, forcing him to decide wha
 t he’s willing to sacrifice on the road to success.\nRated 14A\n99 minut
 es\nDrop-in.\nThanks to Reel Canada for providing the screening of this fi
 lm.
LOCATION:Dufferin/St.Clair\, Earlscourt Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69bc7c1867801235ed7350c1
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
