BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Brother: National Canadian Film Day Screening
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T160000
UID:69bc7b24b6c4ac1fedc6f0be@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:April 15 is National Canadian Film Day. Join us for the screen
 ing of Brother.\nThe latest film from director Clement Virgo\, Brother is 
 a beautifully shot master work of subtle\, affecting storytelling. Adapted
  from David Chariandy’s award-winning novel of the same name\, Brother t
 ells the story of Francis and Michael\, two Black Canadian brothers growin
 g up in Scarborough in the early 1990s. Recently immigrated to Canada\, th
 e brothers navigate the challenges of growing up outsiders\, with feet in 
 two worlds.\nRated 14A\n119 minutes\nDrop-in.\nThanks to Reel Canada for p
 roviding the screening of this film.
LOCATION:Dufferin/St.Clair\, Earlscourt Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69bc7b24b6c4ac1fedc6f0be
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
