BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Breast and Cervical Cancer Information Session
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T150000
UID:69bd5e742866a5b488435289@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Breast and cervical cancer are among the most common cancers a
 ffecting women\, but early detection and prevention can significantly impr
 ove outcomes. Understanding your risk\, knowing when to get screened\, and
  being aware of available supports are key steps in protecting your health
 .\nWhat to Expect:\nPrevention and Early Detection:\nLearn why screening m
 atters and how it can help detect cancer at earlier\, more treatable stage
 s.\nScreening Services:\nGet an overview of available breast and cervical 
 cancer screening options and what to expect from the process.\nAccessing C
 are and Support:\nLearn how to connect with local services\, including pri
 mary care and other community supports.\nThis session will be led by Commu
 nity Health Workers\, who will provide practical information and guidance 
 to help you better understand your options and take the next steps.\nThis 
 program is presented by Toronto Public Library in collaboration with the W
