BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Heart Health Conversations
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260422T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260422T170000
UID:69bd823b8d5e2d093366963b@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Heart-related illnesses remain one of the leading causes of de
 ath in Canada\, yet many of the factors that influence heart health are wi
 thin our control. Understanding these factors and knowing what steps you c
 an take to manage them can play an important role in supporting long-term 
 cardiovascular health.\nWhat to Expect:\nUnderstanding Risk Factors:\nLear
 n about common factors that can impact heart health and how to recognize t
 hem.\nPrevention Strategies:\nExplore practical steps that can help suppor
 t heart health and reduce risk.\nHealthy Lifestyle Practices:\nLearn about
  practices that contribute to overall cardiovascular well-being.\nAccessin
 g Resources and Support:\nLearn about available services and supports that
  can help you maintain and support your heart health.\nThis session will b
 e led by Community Health Workers\, who will provide practical information
  and guidance to help you better understand your heart health and ways to 
 support it.\nThis program is presented by Toronto Public Library in collab
 oration with the West Toronto Ontario Health Team (OHT)\, a network of ove
 r 40 local health and social service providers working together to improve
  the health and well-being of communities in West Toronto.\nReserve Your S
 pot Today!\nThis free\, in-person event is part of Toronto Public Library
 ’s\nYour Health Matters\ninitiative.\nRegistration is preferred\, but dr
 op-ins are welcome.\nRegister on Eventbrite to reserve your spot.\nWe can
 ’t wait to see you there!
LOCATION:New Toronto
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69bd823b8d5e2d093366963b
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
