BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Beginner Guitar Jam
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T193000
UID:69bec77e1e64afd01e63c4ed@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Strum\, sing\, and jam with other beginner guitarists in a fun
 \, relaxed group setting. Over four weeks\, you will build confidence\, le
 arn classic progressions\, and experience the energy of sounding like a ba
 nd together. No experience required! The library will provide guitars for 
 participants to borrow for the duration of the program. Please make sure y
 ou can attend all four sessions (Fridays April 10\, 17\, 24\, and May 1)
  before registering.\nThis program is facilitated in partnership with the
  Toronto Blues Society.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal info
 rmation on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the 
 Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information
  will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and evalu
 ation. Questions about how the library handles your information can be dir
 ected to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yon
