BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Merilyn Simonds: Walking with Beth
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260521T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260521T200000
UID:69c158ab07a74a47597a6b54@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:TPL presents acclaimed author and Governor General's Award fin
 alist Merilyn Simonds in conversation with journalist and author Moira We
 lsh at the Toronto Reference Library's Jack Rabinovitch Reading Room.\nIn 
 her intimate and profoundly moving book Walking with Beth: Conversations w
 ith My Hundred-Year-Old Friend\, national bestselling author Merilyn Simon
 ds invites us into three years of weekly walks with Beth Robinson\, her ne
 ighbour and friend. When they began in the spring of 2021\, Simonds had ju
 st turned 70\, still active\, still writing\, but entering what struck her
  as a mysterious and frightening stage of life. Beth\, a former dancer and
  occupational therapist who worked until age 99\, was already a centenaria
 n: vibrant\, sharp\, and as awake to the world as someone half her age. Wh
 o better to ask what might come next?\nWhat emerges is neither a conventio
 nal memoir nor a straightforward biography\, but something more fluid: a m
 editation on friendship between women across generations\, on mortality an
 d meaning\, on the passions that sustain us through life's least understoo
 d passage.\nQ&A and book signing to follow. Books available for purchase.\
 nAbout this event’s guests:\nMerilyn Simonds\nRead More:\nWalking With B
 eth\nThe Convict Lover\nAstonishing Lives of Older Women : How to Create P
 leasure Over Peril in Peak Longevity\n***\nPLAN YOUR VISIT:\nLocation:\nJa
 ck Rabinovitch Reading Room\, Toronto Reference Library (789 Yonge Street)
 \, 4th floor\nTime:\nDoors open 6:00pm\, Event starts 7:00pm.\nTickets:\nF
 ree registration required.\nTicket policy:\nWe oversell these events to en
 sure that the greatest number of people have an opportunity to attend. Tic
 kets guaranteed until 6:45pm or until capacity is reached. Seating first c
 ome\, first served\nAccessibility:\nTPL is committed to accessibility. If 
 you are Deaf or have a disability and would like to request accommodation 
 for this event\, please contact accessibleservices@tpl.ca or 416-393-7099 
 at least three weeks prior to the event.\n***\nThis event is part of our s
 ignature\nSalon Series\n\, where we host local and international authors\,
  artists and thinkers in conversation about their new books and big ideas.
 \n***\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this fo
 rm is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries A
 ct\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used
  for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Registrants
  may be contacted to fill out a brief survey following the program. Questi
 ons about how the library handles your information can be directed to Answ
 erline staff at answerline@tpl.ca\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toro
 nto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Jack Rabinovitch Reading Room\, Toron
 to Reference Library (789 Yonge Street)\, 4th floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c158ab07a74a47597a6b54
