BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Darragh McGee: Imitation Games
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260609T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260609T200000
UID:69c15d2e07a74a47597a6ba1@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:TPL presents sociologist and BBC New Generation Thinker Darrag
 h McGee in conversation with at the Toronto Reference Library's Atrium.\nI
 n his eye-opening new book\nImitation Games: How the Gambling Industry Hij
 acked Sport\n\, University of Bath sociologist Darragh McGee travels the w
 orld to tell the incredible story of how online gambling transformed from 
 a provincial cottage industry twenty-five years ago into a billion dollar 
 business. He traces the individuals and companies who brought this brave n
 ew world of betting into being\, and got very rich doing so. But he also d
 ocuments the devastation left behind: the inadequate safeguards\, the brok
 en lives\, the moment when the fun stops.\nWhat does this mean for the fut
 ure of sport and society? As Canada embraces legal online gambling\, with 
 Ontario leading the charge\, we're seeing the same patterns that devastate
 d problem gamblers elsewhere\, now playing out here. The industry profits 
 only when people lose\, yet it has successfully rebranded gambling as harm
 less entertainment\, fan engagement\, a way to feel closer to the action. 
 Meanwhile\, vulnerable populations\, young men especially\, face unprecede
 nted risk of addiction.\nQ&A and book signing to follow. Books available f
 or purchase.\nAbout this event’s guests:\nDarragh McGee\nRead more:\nImi
 tation Games : How Gambling Hijacked Sports\n***\nThis event is part of ou
 r signature\nSalon Series\n\, where we host local and international author
 s\, artists and thinkers in conversation about their new books and big ide
 as.\n***\nPLAN YOUR VISIT:\nLocation:\nAtrium\, Toronto Reference Library 
 (789 Yonge Street)\, 1st floor\nTime:\nDoors open 6:00pm\, Event starts 7:
 00pm.\nTickets:\nFree registration required.\nTicket policy:\nWe oversell 
 these events to make sure that the greatest number of people have an oppor
 tunity to attend. Tickets are guaranteed until 6:45pm or until capacity is
  reached. Any remaining space will be opened up to the rush line beginning
  at 6:45pm. Seating first come\, first served. Tickets do not guarantee se
 ats.\nAccessibility:\nTPL is committed to accessibility. If you are Deaf o
 r have a disability and would like to request accommodation for this event
 \, please contact accessibleservices@tpl.ca or 416-393-7099 at least three
  weeks prior to the event.\n***\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe perso
 nal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library un
 der the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The inf
 ormation will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery a
 nd evaluation.\nRegistrants may be contacted to fill out a brief survey fo
 llowing the program\n. Questions about how the library handles your inform
 ation can be directed to Answerline staff at answerline@tpl.ca\, 416-397-5
 981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Atrium\, Toronto Reference Library (7
 89 Yonge Street)\, 1st floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c15d2e07a74a47597a6ba1
