BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Making Zines with Adobe InDesign
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T200000
UID:69c167931e64afd01e642360@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Adobe InDesign is the industry-leading page design and layout 
 app lets you create\, preflight\, and publish beautiful documents for prin
 t and digital media. InDesign CC has everything you need to make posters\,
  books\, digital magazines\, eBooks\, interactive PDFs\, and more. In this
  beginner's class\, we will work on a small magazine utilizing the common 
 tools in InDesign.\nNote:\nyou will need to have your own working copy of 
 Adobe InDesign for this class. The instructor will be using the Creative C
 loud 2024 version. It is okay if you have a different version but there ma
 y be some small differences.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal
  information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under
  the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The inform
 ation will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and 
 evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your information can b
 e directed to Answerline staff at answerline@tpl.ca\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Y
 onge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c167931e64afd01e642360
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:After School Crafts: Thaumatrope
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T170000
UID:69c1682de2a2952aed0a0676@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us in making a thaumatrope to take home! All materials pr
 ovided.\nA thaumatrope is an optical toy and creates the illusion of motio
 n with the “persistence of vision”.\nAges 6-12\n. Registration is not 
 required\, this is a d\nrop-in program.
LOCATION:Lillian H. Smith\, Room BC
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c1682de2a2952aed0a0676
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Branch Art Exhibit: Herstory: Spirit of Filipina Struggle\, Story 
 and Mythology by Jenniffer Twu
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260401T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T235959
UID:69c168bf567ba1dd31fe4320@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Throughout the month of April\, works by artist Jenniffer Twu
  are on display at Bloor Gladstone Library in an exhibit titled Herstory:
  Spirit of Filipina Struggle\, Story and Mythology.\nJenniffer Twu is a se
 lf-taught Canadian painter. She has exhibited her works at the Toronto Cen
 tre for the Arts. Her works are displayed at the North York General Hospi
 tal\, Sunnybrook Hospital and CAMH.\n"My collection of paintings are from 
 an eye of someone who witnessed Filipina struggles\, stories and mythologi
 es. 'Kasaysayan' is Herstory and 'Diwa' is Spirit. I paint of the colourfu
 lness of a culture\, the staunchness of a heritage and the intricateness o
 f its story-telling. It is in my roots that I’ve grown into a Canadian 
 artist."\nThis exhibit is part of TPL's\nArt Exhibit Space\nprogram. Toron
 to Public Library provides space for local artists to exhibit their work a
 t locations across the city. These exhibits aim to reflect the diverse cul
 tural interests of the city and its neighbourhoods.\nThe exhibit can be vi
 ewed during Bloor/Gladstone branch's open hours. Please check the\nBloor/
 Gladstone branch\npage before you visit.\nFree. All are welcome.\nImage cr
 edit: Jenniffer Twu\; Herstory: Spirit\; Medium: Acrylic
LOCATION:Bloor/Gladstone\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c168bf567ba1dd31fe4320
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:LSP: Healing Letters - Mindfulness and Basic Modern Calligraphy
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T191500
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T201500
UID:69c16ba34dacf581ff83d761@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:In this Free Workshop\, you will:\nlearn about mindfulness and
  its impact to mental health\nexplore simple and easy ways you can do to p
 ractice mindfulness\ntry a mindfulness activity: basic modern calligraphy 
 using a brush pen\ndiscover other newcomer settlement information\nFor mor
 e information and to register\, contact LSP Program Worker Shane at saquin
 o@culturelink.ca or 416-931-6536\nIn partnership with Immigration\, Refuge
 es and Citizenship Canada\, CultureLink Settlement & Community Services & 
 Toronto Public Library.
LOCATION:Eatonville
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c16ba34dacf581ff83d761
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Vector Design with Affinity
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T200000
UID:69c1715d8089f23c6764138b@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Learn the ins and outs of vector design using Affinity. We wil
 l talk about the differences between vector and raster images\, explore so
 me of the beginner tools at our disposal\, and then use these tools to des
 ign a small vector drawing.\nThis class is for beginners but assumes you h
 ave a basic understanding of computer skills.\nInformation Collection Noti
 ce:\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Pub
 lic Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 
 20(d). The information will only be used for event and program registratio
 n\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your 
 information can be directed to Answerline staff at answerline@tpl.ca\, 416
 -397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c1715d8089f23c6764138b
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Python Essentials 1 Online Learning Circle
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260505T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260505T153000
UID:69b1951a4dacf581ff812983@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Interested in learning Python? Let's take a free online course
  together in a welcoming space!\nPython is a computer programming language
  used by startups and tech giants alike\, including Google\, Facebook\, Ne
 tflix and more.\nIn this 8-week learning circle\, we will work through ded
 icated course content together. The Python Essentials 1 course from the Op
 enEDG Python Institute teaches in-demand computer programming skills\, inc
 luding how to design\, develop\, and improve computer programs using the P
 ython programming language.\nWe will meet online every Tuesday afternoon\,
 \nMay 5 - June 23\n\, 2-3:30 PM\n.\nParticipants are expected to commit to
  the duration of the course and attend all learning circle sessions.\nLear
 ners who complete the course will be able to:\nEarn a digital badge\nDownl
 oad a certificate of completion\nReceive a 20% discount for the PCEP certi
 fication exam
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b1951a4dacf581ff812983
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
