BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Author Talk with Kath Jonathan
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T200000
UID:69c194eb4dacf581ff83e580@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:The Bloor/Gladstone Library with hosting author Kath Jonathan\
 , writer of\nThe Resistance Painter\n(2025)\n.\nKath Jonathan will do a re
 ading of their book and provide a talk about the themes and characters in
  the book\, along with the real-life inspiration of the novel. In fact\, o
 ne of the real-life inspirations for the novel include Jonathan's mother-
 in-law\, Janina Zaborowska\, who fought in the Armia Krajowa\, the Polish 
 resistance army struggling against the Nazi occupation of Poland.\nThe Res
 istance Painter\nis a dual-narrative novel\, following the stories of Iren
 a in WWII-era Poland\, and Jo\, granddaughter of Irena\, in Toronto during
  the 2010s.\nWe hope you can make it!\nThis is a drop-in program\, no regi
 stration is required. The author will be selling copies of the novel at th
 e program if you wish you own your own copy\, or you can borrow the book f
 rom our catalogue.
LOCATION:Bloor/Gladstone\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c194eb4dacf581ff83e580
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:What is Artificial Intelligence?
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T113000
UID:69c19642b48451fc3c0ac73e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:AI technologies have become increasingly prevalent in many asp
 ects of modern life\, including healthcare\, finance\, transportation\, an
 d entertainment. Some examples of AI applications include virtual assistan
 ts like Siri and Alexa\, self-driving cars\, fraud detection systems\, and
  personalized recommendations in online shopping. Come join this beginner 
 in-person class to learn what AI is and how it learns and predicts outcome
 s.\nThis is a drop-in program\, space is limited.
LOCATION:Parliament Street\, Second Floor Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c19642b48451fc3c0ac73e
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
