DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260425T113000
UID:69c19929b48451fc3c0ac880@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:An introductory class on Microsoft Word for absolute beginners
 .\nIn this class\, you will:\nUnderstand how to use Word’s Tabs\, Groups
 \, and Commands\nCreate\, save\, print and delete Word documents\nPractice
  basic text formatting and style features\nUpon completion of this class\,
  you will be able to use Microsoft Word at a basic level.\nPrerequisites: 
 Basic keyboarding and mouse skills required.\nFormat: Hands-on with demons
 trations\nThis is a drop-in program\, space is limited.
LOCATION:Parliament Street\, Second Floor Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c19929b48451fc3c0ac880
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
