UID:69ab2ee2cbf6405d356993a0@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Learn to use Gmail\, Google’s free web-based email service.\
 nIn this sixth session you will:\nPractice basic email functions: send\, r
 ead\, reply\, forward\, delete email\, and attach files\nReview how spam a
 nd junk mail work\nUpon completion of this class students will have a basi
 c understanding of how to use email.\nInstructions on how to set up and ma
 nage your own free Gmail account are included in the handout.\nPrerequisit
 es: Basic keyboarding and mouse skills required.\nFormat: Hands-on with de
 monstrations
LOCATION:Brentwood\, Learning Centre\, 2nd floor.
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69ab2ee2cbf6405d356993a0
