BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Food and Mood: A Workshop for Parents/Caregivers
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260515T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260515T120000
UID:69c1c3ed2866a5b48843fd73@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a Toronto Public Health workshop for parents/careg
 ivers on\nFood and Mood.\nThe workshop will begin at 11:20\, immediately a
 fter our Family Time (stories and songs).\n“We are what we eat”. Healt
 hy eating is essential for overall health. Participants will be introduce
 d to the\nrelationship between food and mood. They will be able to identi
 fy common foods from Canada’s Food\nGuide that support positive mood\, u
 nderstand how mood can affect food choices and apply concepts of\nmindful
  eating to make family mealtimes with young children less stressful.\nPle
 ase register\nfor the workshop so we may plan accordingly.\n11:00-11:20am 
  Drop-in Family Time with stories and songs for children age 0-5 and their
  parents/caregivers\n11:20-11:50am  Stay for the Toronto Public Health wor
 kshop on Food and Mood. Children are welcome to stay and play or make a cr
 aft in the same room during the workshop. Library staff will be present to
  engage with the children.\nThis workshop is the second in a series of thr
 ee workshops offered by Toronto Public Health.\nFriday March 23\, 2026: Po
 sitive Parenting\nFriday May 15\, 2026: Food and Mood\nFriday June 12\, 2
 026: Managing Stress in Children\nInformation Collection Notice: The perso
 nal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library un
 der the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The inf
 ormation will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery a
 nd evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your information ca
 n be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\,
  789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Gerrard/Ashdale\, 2nd Floor Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c1c3ed2866a5b48843fd73
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Managing Stress in Children: A Workshop for Parents/Caregivers
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260612T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260612T120000
UID:69c1cd108d5e2d093367330c@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a Toronto Public Health workshop on\nManaging Stre
 ss in Children.\nPLEASE NOTE that our drop-in Family Time takes place dire
 ctly before this workshop.\nThis workshop will help participants understan
 d the different kinds of stress\, explain what happens to children's bodi
 es and minds during stress and how to identify signs and symptoms of str
 ess in young children. It will also provide strategies to help children c
 ope with and manage stress.\nPlease register\nfor the workshop so we may p
 lan accordingly.\n11:00-11:20am  Drop-in Family Time with stories and song
 s for children age 0-5 and their parents/caregivers\n11:20-11:50am  Stay f
 or the Toronto Public Health workshop on Managing Stress in Children. Chil
 dren are welcome to stay and play or make a craft in the same room during 
 the workshop.\nThis workshop is the third in a series of three workshops o
 ffered by Toronto Public Health.\nFriday March 23\, 2026: Positive Parenti
 ng\nFriday May 15\, 2026: Food and Mood\nFriday June 12\, 2026: Managing 
 Stress in Children\nInformation Collection Notice: The personal informatio
 n on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public
  Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will 
 only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation.
  Questions about how the library handles your information can be directed 
 to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Str
 eet\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Gerrard/Ashdale\, 2nd Floor Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c1cd108d5e2d093367330c
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
