BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Excel Basics
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T200000
UID:69c2c2185a2d780f42c496e6@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Excel Basics 1: Create a Simple Spreadsheet\nAn introductory c
 lass on Microsoft Excel for absolute beginners with little or no Excel exp
 erience.\nIn this first session\, you will:\nLearn the basic function and 
 design of Excel files\nPractice basic data entry for text\, numbers\, and 
 basic functions: Sum\, AutoSum and Average\nCreate and save your first wor
 kbook and worksheets\nUpon completion of this class\, you will be able to 
 use Excel at a basic level.\nPrerequisites: Basic mouse and keyboard skill
 s are required.\nFormat: Hands-on with demonstrations\nExcel Basics 2: Do 
 More with your Data\nAn introductory class on Microsoft Excel for beginner
 s with little or no Excel experience. Build on your basic Microsoft Excel 
 skills and learn to use Excel data effectively.\nIn this second session\, 
 you will:\nPractice data entry and formatting\nManipulate rows and columns
 \nCreate and copy simple formulas\nConvert data to a Table then sort and f
 ilter\nCreate your first chart\nUpon completion of this class\, you will b
 e able to get more from your data using tables\, filters and charts.\nPrer
 equisites: Excel Basics Part 1 or equivalent knowledge. Basic mouse and ke
 yboard skills required.\nFormat: Hands-on with demonstrations\nExcel Basic
 s 3: PivotTables & Conditional Formatting\nBuild on your basic Microsoft E
 xcel skills and learn to use Excel data effectively.\nIn this third sessio
 n\, you will:\nUse Conditional Formatting to visualize data\nExplore the p
 ower of PivotTables for data summary and analysis\nSort and filter the dat
 a in tables and using slicers\nTake home practice data to improve your new
  skills\nUpon completion of this class\, you will be able to get more from
  your data using Pivot tables.\nPrerequisites: Excel Basics 1 and 2 or equ
 ivalent knowledge. Basic mouse and keyboard skills required.\nFormat: Hand
 s-on with demonstrations\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal inf
 ormation on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the
  Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The informatio
 n will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery and eval
 uation. Questions about how the library handles your information can be di
 rected to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yo
 nge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:York Woods\, ELC
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c2c2185a2d780f42c496e6
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
