BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Native Plants: Why You Need Them & They Need You
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260512T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260512T200000
UID:69cebe05b48451fc3c0ce952@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Native Plants: Why You Need Them… & They Need You! Hosted by
  Toronto Master Gardeners.\nEverything old is new again\, and native plant
  gardens are now all the rage. And for good reason! A Toronto Master Garde
 ner will go over:\n- Why native plants are best adapted to (thus more succ
 essful in) our climatic conditions\;\n- How they support biodiversity by p
 roviding food and shelter for birds and pollinators\n- How they enhance th
 e beauty of our gardens.\nYou have everything to gain and nothing to lose 
 by adding more native plants to your garden… come and learn how!\nThis p
 rogram is part of TPL's Our Fragile Planet program series\, supported by F
 riends of Toronto Public Library\, South Chapter.
LOCATION:Morningside\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69cebe05b48451fc3c0ce952
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
