BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Nourish Your Best Weight
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260428T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260428T190000
UID:69c5506db6c4ac1fedc84705@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to build a healthier relationship with food\, unders
 tand weight bias\, and support long-term health in this interactive sessio
 n.\nWeight is often at the centre of conversations about health\, but buil
 ding a sustainable and supportive relationship with food and your body goe
 s far beyond the number on the scale. This session offers a thoughtful\, e
 vidence-based approach to nutrition\, focusing on long-term habits\, self-
 awareness\, and overall well-being.\nWhat to Expect:\nUnderstanding Weight
  Bias:\nLearn how weight bias can impact health\, self-care\, and the way 
 we approach nutrition.\nYour Relationship with Food:\nReflect on your pers
 onal relationship with food and how it shapes your eating habits.\nRethink
 ing Health and Wellness:\nExplore a broader perspective on health that goe
 s beyond the number on the scale.\nBuilding Sustainable Habits:\nLearn pra
 ctical strategies to support long-term nourishment and well-being\, rather
  than quick fixes.\nAbout the Speaker\nThis interactive session will be le
 d by Catherine Cai\, Registered Dietitian and Certified Diabetes Educator 
 at Crosstown Family Health Team\, who will provide practical information a
 nd guidance to help you better understand your relationship with food and 
 how to support your health.\nThis program is presented by Toronto Public L
 ibrary in collaboration with the West Toronto Ontario Health Team (OHT)\, 
 a network of over 40 local health and social service providers working tog
 ether to improve the health and well-being of communities in West Toronto.
 \nYour Health Matters\nThis program is part of Toronto Public Library’s\
 nYour Health Matters\ninitiative\, which offers trusted health programs an
 d resources to help people make informed decisions about their health. Lea
 rn more by exploring the\nYour Health Matters web page\n.\nReserve Your Sp
 ot Today!\nThis virtual event is free to join but registration is required
 .\nPlease register on Eventbrite\n.\nOnce registered\, you’ll receive an
  email with details on how to join the session.\nWe can’t wait to see yo
 u there!
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c5506db6c4ac1fedc84705
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
