BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Branch Art Exhibit: Trees by Bernardo Cioppa
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260402T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T235959
UID:69c56480491b809c6f2310ed@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Throughout the month of April\, works by artist Bernardo Ciop
 pa are on display at Northern District Library branch in an exhibit title
 d Trees.\nBernardo Cioppa began photography at age 10 with a Kodak Brownie
  camera. He mainly focuses on street photography but also creates landscap
 es. Through the York Arts Guild\, he exhibits his work around Toronto and 
 is currently showing at the Tranzac Club. He has sold several photos\, par
 ticipated in various exhibitions\, and won second place in Visual Arts Mis
 sissauga’s 2025 “Why Do You Create?” juried exhibition\n"I’m inspi
 red by people's incidents of being or doing intriguing things. As such\, s
 treet photography speaks to me. My approach is more inspirational rather t
 han technical. I'm creating a one frame movie. The photo will tell a story
  or prompt questions about the scene or behaviour of people and capture th
 at poignant moment before forever gone. You need to be decisive\, taking i
 nto consideration composition\, direction of light\, and subject matter\, 
 and mixed with some luck\, hopefully catch the moment."\nThis exhibit is p
 art of TPL's\nArt Exhibits Space\nprogram. Toronto Public Library provides
  space for local artists to exhibit their work at locations across the cit
 y. These exhibits aim to reflect the diverse cultural interests of the cit
 y and its neighbourhoods.\nThe exhibit can be viewed during\nNorthern Dist
 rict\nLibrary open hours.\nFree. All are welcome.\nImage credit: Bernardo
  Cioppa\; photography\; Today's Favourite
LOCATION:Northern District\, 2nd floor Gallery space
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c56480491b809c6f2310ed
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
