DESCRIPTION:Throughout March\, works by artist Andrew Johnston are on disp
 lay at Mimico Centennial branch.\nAndrew Johnston is largely self-taught\,
  and enjoys being surrounded by nature and in other interactive milieu.\n"
 I make fine art. My voyage of self-discovery has brought me this far. I ha
 ve the desire to create more."\nThis exhibit is part of TPL's\nArt Exhibit
 s Space\nprogram. Toronto Public Library provides space for local artists 
 to exhibit their work at locations across the city. These exhibits aim to 
 reflect the diverse cultural interests of the city and its neighbourhoods.
 \nThe exhibit can be viewed during\nMimico Centennial\nbranch open hours.\
 nFree. All are welcome.\nImage credit: Andrew Johnston\; acrylic\; white 
