BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Access To Housing: Information Session
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T160000
UID:69c58e38deee9abd8ee5f141@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Do you need information about applying for Rent-Geared-to-Inco
 me Housing or assistance with your application? Join Margaret's Housing an
 d Community Support Services staff for drop-in sessions on the 3\nrd\nTue
 sday of each month\, from 2-4pm.\nThis session will cover:\nAn overview of
  the RGI application process\nEligibility requirements\nSteps for submitti
 ng and updating applications\nInformation on priority access\nThe choice-b
 ased cycle housing offer process and the Single Offer Rule\nFinancial assi
 stance programs to help the tenants/home owners\nWhether you are a first-t
 ime applicant or seeking assistance with an existing application\, this se
 ssion will empower you with the knowledge needed to navigate the Rent Gear
 ed to Income housing system.\nPresented by Margaret's Housing and Communit
 y Support Services\, a multi-service agency that provides housing options 
 to women living with mental illness and substance abuse\, and community-ba
 sed support services for individuals experiencing intersectional issues ti
 ed to mental health challenges and homelessness.\nPlease arrive a few minu
 tes early.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Learning Centre 1 (1st floor)
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c58e38deee9abd8ee5f141
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
