BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:SP Book Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T150000
UID:698bc87f7074813837097fb8@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Discuss diverse and inclusive titles from a variety of genres 
 on the fourth Thursday of every month!\nThis month we will be discussing\n
 Little Fires Everywhere\nby Celeste Ng.\nIn the orderly\, planned communit
 y of Shaker Heights\, the arrival of enigmatic artist Mia Warren challenge
 s the carefully constructed existence of rule-following matriarch Elena Ri
 chardson. When a divisive custody battle pits the two mothers against one 
 another\, Elena’s obsession with uncovering Mia’s secrets threatens to
  ignite a devastating chain of events. This gripping novel explores the we
 ight of hidden pasts\, the ferocious pull of motherhood\, and the dangerou
 s belief that following the rules can avert disaster.\nPick up a physical 
 copy at the branch before the meeting\, or find copies through our website
  in various formats. Registration is required and begins Mar 26\, 2026.\nI
 nformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is co
 llected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sec
 tions 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for eve
 nt and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how
  the library handles your information can be directed to Answerline staff 
 at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W
  2G8.
LOCATION:Spadina Road\, Canoe Table\, center of branch
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698bc87f7074813837097fb8
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
