BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:BlackBerry (2023): National Canadian Film Day Screening
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T200000
UID:69c6cfb6ad384e40edb73440@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:From its humble origins in Waterloo\, nobody expected the mass
 ive global success that the world’s first smartphone would become. Based
  loosely on the true story of the extraordinary development and spectacula
 r demise of the BlackBerry\, this high-stakes comedy featuring an all-star
  cast is a bona fide crowd pleaser and critical darling.  Rated R.\nRefre
 shments will be served or feel free to bring your own!\nThanks to Reel Can
 ada for providing the screening for this film.
LOCATION:Pape/Danforth\, Second floor program room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c6cfb6ad384e40edb73440
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:L'Heure du conte / French Storytime
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260602T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260602T110000
UID:69c6d129b48451fc3c0baaae@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Rejoignez-nous pour des histoires\, des chansons et des compti
 nes en français pour les enfants âgés de 0 à 5 ans\, accompagnés de l
 eurs parents et responsables. Les familles sont invitées à rester et à 
 jouer pour 30 minutes supplémentaires après la conclusion du programme.\
 nEnjoy stories\, songs and rhymes in French at a staff-led story time for
  children age 0-5 with their parents and caregivers. Families are welcome 
 to "stay and play" for an additional 30 minutes following the program.\n--
 -------\nLe sous-titrage en direct ou automatique\, l’interprétation en
  langue des signes\, les services d’intervenant\, ou les services d’a
 ccompagnement sont disponibles sur demande. Veuillez soumettre votre dema
 nde au moins deux semaines à l’avance à : tpl.ca/accessibility-events.
LOCATION:S. Walter Stewart\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c6d129b48451fc3c0baaae
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
