BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Resilience Reads: a climate neighbourhood reading party
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T200000
UID:69c6f8d3deee9abd8ee60c77@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us to share the joy of reading\, while building climate r
 esilience knowledge. Members are invited to discuss a book they are readin
 g\, tell stories\,  and empower each other to explore community-driven sol
 utions. Each party will start with a quiet read and reflect time\, with op
 portunities to join group discussions later on over refreshments.\nAPRIL-L
 earning from trees for Earth Month\nThe Overstory\nby Richard Power\nMAY 
 – All women are water defenders\nMemory of Water\nby Emmi Itaranta or yo
 ur favourite book featuring water!\nJUNE – Righting our relationship wit
 h land\nEarth Keeper\nby N. Scott Momaday or your favourite book that shar
 es how words are medicine!\nJULY – Climate migration or the borders betw
 een us are not lines that divide us\, but seams that connect us\nGun Islan
 d\n/\nThe Hungry Tide\nby Amitav Ghosh or your favourite island setting su
 mmer read!\nCopies are available in the branch to pick up\, while supplies
  last.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this f
 orm is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries 
 Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be use
 d for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions 
 about how the library handles your information can be directed to Answerli
 ne staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toron
 to ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Parkdale\, Auditorium A
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c6f8d3deee9abd8ee60c77
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Film Club: Sinners (2025)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260413T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260413T143000
UID:69c6fbc9b48451fc3c0bb622@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join Risa Shuman\, film historian and former Executive Produce
 r of Saturday Night at the Movies for a monthly film viewing with subtitle
 s and discussion\n.\nThis month's film will be\nSinners\n(rated R).\nSinne
 rs\n(2025) is a supernatural horror thriller directed by Ryan Coogler\, fe
 aturing Michael B. Jordan as twin brothers who return to 1930s Mississippi
  to escape their criminal past. While trying to build a new life\, they op
 erate a juke joint that attracts supernatural evil\, leading to a fight fo
 r survival. The film blends period drama with folklore and vampire element
 s.\nRuntime: 2hr 17min\nEnglish with English subtitles.
LOCATION:Richview\, Auditorium\, Lower Level
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c6fbc9b48451fc3c0bb622
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
