BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:An Anarchist Queen and Her Radiant Protégé: Emma Goldman and Mar
 ie Tiboldo in Interwar Toronto
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T163000
UID:69c7ed7ae2a2952aed0b2ca3@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Please join us for an engaging talk presented by Kensington Ma
 rket Historical Society and Toronto Public Library.\nEmma Goldman was an a
 narchist and anti-war activist who was instrumental in mentoring other act
 ivists during her time in Toronto. After Goldman’s death\, protégés li
 ke Marie Tiboldo continued her work. Join presenters Cynthia Wright and Fr
 anca Iacovetta to learn more about their impact on interwar Toronto.\nRefr
 eshments will be offered following the talk.\nCynthia Wright is Associate 
 Professor in the School of Gender\, Sexuality\, and Women’s Studies at Y
 ork University. Franca Iacovetta is Professor Emerita\, University of Toro
 nto\, and co-editor of Studies in Gender and History at University of Toro
 nto Press.
LOCATION:Lillian H. Smith\, Room B/C
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c7ed7ae2a2952aed0b2ca3
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
