BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Connecting with Nature: A Pathway to Joy - How to Create a Pollina
 tor
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T200000
UID:69a308ad4dacf581ff7e8c04@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Establishing a pollinator garden composed of native plants pro
 vides considerable advantages for fostering beneficial insects and birds i
 n residential settings. By thoughtfully selecting and positioning appropri
 ate native species\, one can create a robust habitat that attracts bees\, 
 butterflies\, birds\, and other essential pollinators. You will find more 
 enjoyment in your yard and advance both biodiversity visual appeal of the 
 property.\n​\nPresented by Jim Mackiewicz. He holds a Canadian Federal G
 overnment Permit for Ornithological Research - Banding Birds\, is the owne
 r of Wild Birds Unlimited and is a Certified Bird Feeding Specialist and C
 ertified Instructor in Project Wild/Project Zero.
LOCATION:Don Mills\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a308ad4dacf581ff7e8c04
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
