BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Finding Recovery Through Exercise Skills and Hope (FRESH)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260506T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260506T150000
UID:69cab8d781b67dfe32afefde@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This\n program helps people stay active\, make friends\, learn
  new skills\, and \nhave fun. It involves peer-led group activities which 
 can include crafts\, games\,\n walking\, yoga\, and more. Meet new folks\
 , build social connections\, and tell us\n about programs and services you
  would like to see in the neighbourhood!\nFor our upcoming sessions\, we w
 ill be screening the following films in Program Room A:\nMay 6:\nParenthoo
 d\n(1998)\nMay 13:\nMoonlight\n(2017)\nMay 20:\nThe Reader\n(2009)\nMay 27
 :\nBack to the Future\n(1985)\nDrop in. No registration required.\nSnacks 
 and refreshments are provided for all participants. Ingredient lists will 
 be available at the program.\nThis program is in collaboration with\nGers
 tein Crisis Centre's F.R.E.S.H. initiative\n.
LOCATION:Maria A. Shchuka\, Program Room A
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69cab8d781b67dfe32afefde
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
