DESCRIPTION:Looking for something to do after school? Come out to our Afte
 r School Club and learn new things\, make stuff\, meet other kids and have
  fun!\nFrom 3:30 - 4:000 pm\, snacks are offered during the After School C
 lub for participants.  Ingredient lists will be available. Snacks are gen
 erously supported\, in part\, by donors.\nUpcoming programs:\nApril 2:\nU 
 of T's Dunlap Institute presents an entertaining workshop about astronomy
  for kids.  For children ages 6 and up.\nApril  9:\nBoard Games.  For 
 children ages 4 and up. Parents and caregivers are welcome to play too!\nA
 pril 16:\nFun with Robots:  enjoy coding and other activities with Dash 
 and/or Sphero Bolt.  Two sessions:\n3:45 - 4:25 pm: JUNIORS\n(ages 6 and 
 7)\n4:30 - 5:15 PM:  SENIORS\n(ages 8 and up)\nApril 23\, April 30\, May 
 7\, and May 21: 4-Part Film Workshop for Kids\nA 4-week series of filmmaki
 ng workshops led by a local filmmaking experts will engage children to wri
 te and create their own films\, using stop-motion\, live action\, or other
  methods of filmmaking.  For children ages 6 -13.  REGISTRATION IS REQUI
 RED.  PLEASE CALL OR VISIT THE BRANCH TO REGISTER.\nInformation Collectio
 n Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toron
