UID:69cafee781b67dfe32b00212@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Seniors E-Connect matches older adults with a teen volunteer t
 o provide tech help\, under the guidance of library staff. Seniors will re
 ceive one-on-one support with their phone\, tablet\, or other device in a
  welcoming and friendly environment.\nThis program will take place on the 
 2nd floor\, which is accessible via stairs or a staff-operated elevator.\n
 To register\, please click on the "Register" button on the top right corne
 r of this page. If you need any assistance registering\, we would be happy
  to help you. Please call us at 416-393-7717 or drop by the branch for ass
 istance.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this
  form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Librarie
 s Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be u
 sed for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Question
 s about how the library handles your information can be directed to Answer
 line staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Tor
 onto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Gerrard/Ashdale\, 2nd Floor
