BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wellness Recovery Action Plan (WRAP)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T160000
UID:69cbc969b6c4ac1fedc94549@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:WRAP is for\nanyone\nlooking to strengthen their well-being—
 whether you’re supporting your mental health\, managing stress\, or simp
 ly wanting to feel more balanced and resilient in daily life. Participant
 s will receive a\nWRAP certificate\nupon program completion.\nIn an 8-wee
 k WRAP group\, individuals explore:\nself-care tools like peer connections
 \, relaxation and mindfulness techniques\, stress reduction strategies\, a
 nd more\nresources for keeping well and feeling better in difficult times.
 \nThere will be no session on\nFriday\, April 3\nbecause the library will 
 be closed in observance of Good Friday.\nTTC Presto tickets will be provid
 ed.\nSnacks and refreshments are provided for all participants. Ingredient
  lists will be available at the program.\nThis program is in collaboratio
 n with\nGerstein Crisis Centre's WRAP initiative\n.\nGerstein Crisis Centr
 e is solely responsible for the protection of \npersonal information colle
 cted through the program registration \nprocess.
