BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Faith and Fear\, Repression and Resilience in Medieval Norwich
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260525T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260525T193000
UID:69cc6577b6c4ac1fedc968b6@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:David Townsend presents and reads excerpts from his historical
  novel\,\nThe Ram in the Thicket\n\, (Palmetto Publishing\, 2025) prefaced
  with some historical background.\nSet in medieval Norwich\, England\, the
  plot centres on the meeting of two major figures in women's literary hist
 ory\, Julian of Norwich and Margery Kempe\, and on the remnants of the cit
 y's Jewish population\, which was officially expelled from England generat
 ions earlier.\nPlease register so we can anticipate attendance size.\nInfo
 rmation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is colle
 cted by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sectio
 ns 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for event 
 and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how th
 e library handles your information can be directed to Answerline staff at\
 nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G
 8.
LOCATION:Palmerston\, Lower level
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69cc6577b6c4ac1fedc968b6
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
