BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Python Essentials 2 Learning Circle
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260507T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260507T120000
UID:69bad17f8089f23c676308cb@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Take an intermediate Python course to advance your programmi
 ng skills. This learning circle will meet on Thursday mornings\, 10:30-12
 pm from May 7 to June 25.  Learning circles are study groups guided by s
 taff for people who want to take a free online course together in a welcom
 ing space. Learners meet weekly to complete the course together. Participa
 nts are expected to commit to the duration of the course and attend all le
 arning circle sessions.\nPython Essentials 2\nis designed for learners who
  are already familiar with the essentials of Python\, including programmin
 g concepts like data types\, containers\, functions\, conditions\, and loo
 ps.\nRequired: completion of the\nPython Essentials 1\ncourse\, or equival
 ent experience.\nPython Essentials 2 is the second in a 2-course series th
 at will prepare you for the\nPCAP – Certified Associate in Python Progra
 mming\ncertification exam at Pearson VUE. This intermediate-level course c
 overs\nadvanced aspects of Python programming\n\, including modules\, pack
 ages\, exceptions\, file processing\, as well as general coding techniques
  and object-oriented programming (OOP).\nFor more information about the Py
 thon Essentials 2 learning circle\, please contact\nnetworkingacademy@tpl
 .ca\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form
  is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act
 \, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used f
 or event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions abo
 ut how the library handles your information can be directed to Answerline 
 staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto 
 ON M4W 2G8.
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69bad17f8089f23c676308cb
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
